            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3144,
            "text": "The satans are barred from listening to anything from the heavens.",
            "numberInSurah": 212,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3145,
            "text": "(Muhammad), do not worship anything besides God lest you suffer the punishment.",
            "numberInSurah": 213,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3146,
            "text": "Warn your close relatives",
            "numberInSurah": 214,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3147,
            "text": "and be kind to your believing followers.",
            "numberInSurah": 215,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3148,
            "text": "If they disobey you, tell them, 'I condemn your disobedient deeds'.",
            "numberInSurah": 216,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3149,
            "text": "Have trust in the Majestic and All-merciful God,",
            "numberInSurah": 217,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3150,
            "text": "who can see whether you stand up",
            "numberInSurah": 218,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3151,
            "text": "or move during your prostration with the worshippers.",
            "numberInSurah": 219,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3152,
            "text": "He is All-hearing and All-knowing.'",
            "numberInSurah": 220,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3153,
            "text": "Should I tell you to whom the satans come?",
            "numberInSurah": 221,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3154,
            "text": "They come to every sinful liar.",
            "numberInSurah": 222,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3155,
            "text": "The satans try to listen to the heavens but many of them are liars.",
            "numberInSurah": 223,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3156,
            "text": "Only the erring people follow the poets.",
            "numberInSurah": 224,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3157,
            "text": "Have you not seen them wandering and bewildered in every valley",
            "numberInSurah": 225,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3158,
            "text": "and preaching what they themselves never practice.",
            "numberInSurah": 226,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3159,
            "text": "The righteously striving believers among them who remember God very often and use their talent to seek help after they have been wronged are the exceptional. The unjust will soon know how terrible their end will be.",
            "numberInSurah": 227,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 376,
            "ruku": 326,
            "hizbQuarter": 150,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 27,
        "name": "سُورَةُ النَّمۡلِ",
        "englishName": "An-Naml",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Ant",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 3160,
            "text": "Ta. Sin. These are the verses of the Quran and of the illustrious Book",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 377,
            "ruku": 327,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3161,
            "text": "They are glad news and guidance for the believers",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 377,
            "ruku": 327,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3162,
            "text": "who are steadfast in prayer, who pay the religious tax, and who have strong faith in the life hereafter.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 377,
            "ruku": 327,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3163,
            "text": "We have made the deeds of those who do not believe in the life to come, attractive to them and they wander about blindly.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 377,
            "ruku": 327,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3164,
            "text": "They will suffer the worst kind of torment and will be lost in the life to come.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 377,
            "ruku": 327,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3165,
            "text": "(Muhammad), you have certainly received the Quran from the All-wise and All-knowing One.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 377,
            "ruku": 327,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3166,
            "text": "Moses said to his family, 'I have seen some fire. I shall bring you some news about it or some fire so that you can warmyourselves'.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 377,
            "ruku": 327,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3167,
            "text": "When he approached the fire, he was told, 'Blessed is the one in the fire and those around it. All glory belongs to God, the Lord of the Universe.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 377,
            "ruku": 327,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3168,
            "text": "Moses, I am God, the Majestic and All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 377,
            "ruku": 327,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3169,
            "text": "Throw down your staff.' When Moses saw his staff on the ground moving like a living creature, he stepped back and did not come forward again. The Lord said,'Moses, do not be afraid. Messengers do not become afraid in My presence'.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 377,
            "ruku": 327,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3170,
            "text": "Only the unjust become afraid in My presence. Even to these people who replace their bad deeds by good ones, I am All-forgiving and All-merciful.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 377,
            "ruku": 327,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3171,
            "text": "Put your hand into your pocket. It will come out sheer white but unharmed. This is one of the nine miracles which shall be showing to the Pharaoh and his people; they are truly wicked men.'",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 377,
            "ruku": 327,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3172,
            "text": "When Our miracles were visibly shown to them, they said, 'It is plain magic'.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 377,
            "ruku": 327,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3173,
            "text": "They rejected the evidence because of their arrogance and injustice, although their souls knew it to be true. Think how terrible the end of the sinful ones was!",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 378,
            "ruku": 327,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3174,
            "text": "We gave knowledge to David and Soloman. They said, 'It is only God who deserves all praise. He has exalted us above many of His believing servants.'",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 378,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3175,
            "text": "Solomon became the heir to David. He said, 'People, we have been taught the language of the birds and have been granted a share of everything. This indeed is a manifest favor (from God)'.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 378,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3176,
            "text": "Soloman's army, consisting of human beings, jinn, and birds were gathered together in his presence in ranks.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 378,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3177,
            "text": "When they arrived in the valley of the ants, one ant said to the others, 'Enter your dwellings lest you be carelessly crushed by Soloman and his army.'",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 378,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3178,
            "text": "(Solomon) smiled at the ant's remarks and said, 'Lord, inspire me to thank you for Your favors to me and my parents and to act righteously so as to please you. Admit me, by your mercy into the company of Your righteous servants'.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 378,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3179,
            "text": "(Solomon) inspected the birds and said, 'How is it that I cannot see the hoopoe. Is he absent?",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 378,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3180,
            "text": "I shall certainly punish him severely or slaughter him unless he has a good reason for his absence.'",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 378,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3181,
            "text": "Not long after the hoopoe came forward and said, 'I have information which you do not have. I have come from the land of Sheba with a true report.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 378,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3182,
            "text": "I found a woman ruling the people there and she possessed something of (almost) everything and a great throne.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 379,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3183,
            "text": "I found her and her people prostrating before the sun instead of God. Satan has made their deeds attractive to them. He has kept them away from the right path and they have no guidance.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 379,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3184,
            "text": "(Satan has done this) so that they will not worship God who brings forth whatever is hidden in the heavens and the earth and knows whatever you conceal or reveal.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 379,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3185,
            "text": "God is the only Lord and master of the Great Throne.'",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 379,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 151,
            "sajda": {
              "id": 9,
              "recommended": true,
              "obligatory": false
            }
          },
          {
            "number": 3186,
            "text": "Solomon said, 'We shall see whether you are truthful or a liar.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 379,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3187,
            "text": "Take this letter of mine and deliver it to them, then return and see what their reply will be.'",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 379,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3188,
            "text": "(The Queen of Sheba) said to her officials, 'A gracious letter has been dropped before me.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 379,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3189,
            "text": "It reads, 'From Soloman. In the Name of God, the Beneficent and the Merciful.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 379,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3190,
            "text": "Do not consider yourselves superior to me but come to me as Muslims (in submission)'.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 379,
            "ruku": 328,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3191,
            "text": "She said, 'My officials, what are your views on this matter? I will not decide until I have your views.",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 379,
            "ruku": 329,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3192,
            "text": "They replied, 'We have great power and valor. You are the commander, so decide as you like'.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 379,
            "ruku": 329,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3193,
            "text": "She said, 'When Kings enter a town they destroy it and disrespect its honorable people. That is what they will do, too.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 379,
            "ruku": 329,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3194,
            "text": "I will send a gift and we shall see what response the Messengers will bring.'",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 379,
            "ruku": 329,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3195,
            "text": "When her Messengers came to Soloman, he said, 'Have you brought me wealth? What God has given to me is far better than what He has given to you, but you are happy with your gifts.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 380,
            "ruku": 329,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3196,
            "text": "Go back to your people and we shall soon come there with an army which they will not be able to face. We shall drive them from their town, humble, and disgraced.'",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 380,
            "ruku": 329,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3197,
            "text": "Solomon asked his people, 'Who among you can bring her throne before (she, the queen of Sheba) comes to me submissively?'",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 380,
            "ruku": 329,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3198,
            "text": "A monstrous jinn said, 'I can bring it before you even stand up. I am powerful and trustworthy'.",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 380,
            "ruku": 329,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3199,
            "text": "The one who had knowledge from the Book said, 'I can bring it to you before you even blink your eye.' When Solomon saw the throne placed before him, he said, 'This is a favor from my Lord by which He wants to test whether I am grateful or ungrateful. Whoever thanks God does so for his own good. Whoever is ungrateful to God should know that my Lord is Self-Sufficient and Benevolent.'",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 380,
            "ruku": 329,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3200,
            "text": "Then he said, 'Make a few changes to her throne and let us see whether she will recognize it or not.'",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 380,
            "ruku": 329,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3201,
            "text": "When she came she was asked, 'Is your throne like this?' She replied, 'It seems that this is it. We had received the knowledge before this and were submissive (to Solomon's power)'.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 380,
            "ruku": 329,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3202,
            "text": "Her idols prevented her from believing in God and she was an infidel.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 380,
            "ruku": 329,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3203,
            "text": "She was told to enter the palace. When she saw it, she thought that it was a pool and raised her clothe up to her legs. Solomon said, 'This is a palace constructed with glass.' She said, 'My Lord, indeed I have wronged myself and I submit myself with Solomon to the will of God, the Lord of the Universe.'",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 380,
            "ruku": 329,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3204,
            "text": "We sent to the tribe of Thamud their brother Salih so that they would worship God, but they became two quarrelling groups.",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 381,
            "ruku": 330,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3205,
            "text": "Salih said, 'My people, why do you commit sins so quickly before doing good? Would that you ask forgiveness from God so that perhaps He will have mercy upon you.'",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 381,
            "ruku": 330,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3206,
            "text": "They said, 'We have an ill omen about you and your followers.' Salih replied, God has made your ill fortune await you. You are a people on trial.'",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 381,
            "ruku": 330,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3207,
            "text": "There were nine tribes in the city spreading evil without any reform in the land.",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 381,
            "ruku": 330,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3208,
            "text": "They said, 'Let us swear by God to do away with him and his family during the night then tell his guardian that we did not see how he and his family had been destroyed, and we shall be telling the truth.'",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 381,
            "ruku": 330,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3209,
            "text": "They plotted and We planned without their knowledge. Consider the result of their plot.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 381,
            "ruku": 330,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3210,
            "text": "We destroyed them and their people altogether.",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 381,
            "ruku": 330,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3211,
            "text": "Those are their empty houses which We ruined because of their injustice. In this there is evidence (of the truth) for the people of knowledge.",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 381,
            "ruku": 330,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3212,
            "text": "We saved the faithful God-fearing believers.",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 381,
            "ruku": 330,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3213,
            "text": "Lot asked his people, 'Do you understandably commit indecency?",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 381,
            "ruku": 330,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3214,
            "text": "Do you have carnal relations with men rather than women? You are ignorant people'.",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 19,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 381,
            "ruku": 330,
            "hizbQuarter": 152,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3215,
            "text": "His people had no answer but to say, 'Expel Lot and his family from the town for they want to be pure.'",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 382,
            "ruku": 330,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3216,
            "text": "We saved (Lot) and his family except his wife who was destined to remain behind.",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 382,
            "ruku": 330,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3217,
            "text": "We sent to them a terrible rainstorm. How horrible was the rain for the people who had already received warning.",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 382,
            "ruku": 330,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3218,
            "text": "(Muhammad), say, 'It is only God who deserves all praise. Peace be upon His chosen servants. Which is better God or the idols?",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 382,
            "ruku": 331,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3219,
            "text": "'(Are the idols worthier or) the One who has created the heavens and the earth, who has sent water from the sky for you, who has established delightful gardens and you could not even plant one tree? Is there any Lord besides God? In fact, the unbelievers are the ones who deviate from the right path.",
            "numberInSurah": 60,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 382,
            "ruku": 331,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3220,
            "text": "'(Are the idols worthier or) the One who has made the earth a resting place, the rivers flow from its valleys, the mountains as anchors and a barrier between the two seas? Is there any lord besides God? In fact, most people do not know.",
            "numberInSurah": 61,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 382,
            "ruku": 331,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3221,
            "text": "'(Are the idols worthier or) the One who answers the prayers of the distressed ones, removes their hardship, and makes you the successors in the land? Is there any lord besides God? In fact, you take very little heed.",
            "numberInSurah": 62,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 382,
            "ruku": 331,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3222,
            "text": "'(Are the idols worthier or) the One who guides you in the darkness of the land and sea and sends the winds bearing the glad news of His mercy? Is there any lord besides God? God is too exalted to be considered equal to anything else.",
            "numberInSurah": 63,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 382,
            "ruku": 331,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3223,
            "text": "'(Are the idols worthier or) the One who began the creation and who will turn it back, who gives you sustenance from the heavens and the earth? Is there any lord besides God? Say, 'Bring your proof if what you say is true.'",
            "numberInSurah": 64,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 383,
            "ruku": 331,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3224,
            "text": "(Muhammad) say, 'No one in the heavens or the earth knows the unseen except God, and no one knows when they will be resurrected.",
            "numberInSurah": 65,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 383,
            "ruku": 331,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3225,
            "text": "Their knowledge of the next life is no more than doubts. In fact, they are blind about it.",
            "numberInSurah": 66,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 383,
            "ruku": 331,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3226,
            "text": "The unbelievers have said, 'Shall we and our fathers be brought out of the graves after we become dust?",
            "numberInSurah": 67,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 383,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3227,
            "text": "It was promised to us and to our fathers before us. It is only ancient legends.'",
            "numberInSurah": 68,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 383,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3228,
            "text": "Say, 'Travel through the land and see how terrible was the end of the criminal ones'.",
            "numberInSurah": 69,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 383,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3229,
            "text": "(Muhammad), do not be grieved (about their disbelief) nor distressed about their evil plans against you.",
            "numberInSurah": 70,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 383,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3230,
            "text": "They ask, 'When the Day of Judgment will come, if it is true at all?'",
            "numberInSurah": 71,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 383,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3231,
            "text": "Say, 'Perhaps some of the things which you wish to experience immediately are very close to you.'",
            "numberInSurah": 72,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 383,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3232,
            "text": "Your Lord has many favors for mankind but most of them are ungrateful.",
            "numberInSurah": 73,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 383,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3233,
            "text": "Your Lord certainly knows whatever their hearts conceal or reveal.",
            "numberInSurah": 74,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 383,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3234,
            "text": "All the secrets in heavens and earth are recorded in the illustrious Book.",
            "numberInSurah": 75,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 383,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3235,
            "text": "This Quran tells the Israelites most of the matters about which they had disputes among themselves.",
            "numberInSurah": 76,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 383,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3236,
            "text": "It is a guide and mercy for the believers.",
            "numberInSurah": 77,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 384,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3237,
            "text": "Your Lord will judge among them according to His own decree. He is Majestic and All-Knowing.",
            "numberInSurah": 78,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 384,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3238,
            "text": "Trust in God for you follow the manifest truth.",
            "numberInSurah": 79,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 384,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3239,
            "text": "You cannot make the dead listen and the deaf are unable to hear calls. Thus, they turn back on their heels.",
            "numberInSurah": 80,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 384,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3240,
            "text": "You cannot guide the straying blind ones. You can only make hear those who believe in Our revelations submissively.",
            "numberInSurah": 81,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 384,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 153,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3241,
            "text": "When the word about them comes true We shall make a creature appear to them on earth who will tell them that people had no faith in Our revelations.",
            "numberInSurah": 82,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 384,
            "ruku": 332,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3242,
            "text": "On the day when We resurrect from every nation a group from among those who had rejected Our revelations, they will be kept confined in ranks.",
            "numberInSurah": 83,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 384,
            "ruku": 333,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3243,
            "text": "When they will be brought into the presence of God, He will ask them, 'Did you reject My revelations without fully understanding them. What did you know about them if you had any knowledge at all?",
            "numberInSurah": 84,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 384,
            "ruku": 333,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3244,
            "text": "They will become subject to punishment because of their injustice. Thus, they will not speak.",
            "numberInSurah": 85,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 384,
            "ruku": 333,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3245,
            "text": "Have they not seen that We have created the night for them to rest and the day for them to see. In this there is evidence for the believing people.",
            "numberInSurah": 86,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 384,
            "ruku": 333,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3246,
            "text": "Everyone in the heavens and earth will be terrified on the day when the trumpet will be sounded except those whom God will save. Everyone will humbly come into the presence of God.",
            "numberInSurah": 87,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 384,
            "ruku": 333,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3247,
            "text": "You think the mountains are solid. In fact, they move like clouds. It is God's technique which has established everything perfectly. He is well Aware of what you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 88,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 384,
            "ruku": 333,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3248,
            "text": "Whoever does a good deed will receive a better reward than what he has done. He will be secure from the terror of the Day of Judgment.",
            "numberInSurah": 89,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 385,
            "ruku": 333,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3249,
            "text": "Those who commit evil will be thrown headlong into hell fire. (It will be said to them) can you expect any recompense other than what you deserve for your deeds?",
            "numberInSurah": 90,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 385,
            "ruku": 333,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3250,
            "text": "I am commanded to worship the Lord of this town which He has made sacred. To Him belong all things. I am commanded to be a Muslim",
            "numberInSurah": 91,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 385,
            "ruku": 333,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3251,
            "text": "and recite the Quran. Whoever seeks guidance will find it for his own soul. Say to whoever goes astray, 'I am only a warner'.",
            "numberInSurah": 92,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 385,
            "ruku": 333,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3252,
            "text": "Say, 'It is only He who deserves all praise. He will soon show you His signs and you will recognize them. Your Lord is not unaware of what you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 93,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 385,
            "ruku": 333,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 28,
        "name": "سُورَةُ القَصَصِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Qasas",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Stories",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 3253,
            "text": "Ta. Sin. Mim.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 385,
            "ruku": 334,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3254,
            "text": "These are the verses of the illustrious Book.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 385,
            "ruku": 334,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3255,
            "text": "We recite to you some of the story of Moses and the Pharaoh for a genuine purpose, and for the benefit of the believing people.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 385,
            "ruku": 334,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3256,
            "text": "The Pharaoh dominated the land and divided its inhabitants into different groups, suppressing one group by killing their sons and keeping their women alive. He was certainly an evil-doer.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 385,
            "ruku": 334,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3257,
            "text": "But We have decided to grant a favor to the suppressed ones by appointing them leaders and heirs of the land,",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 385,
            "ruku": 334,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3258,
            "text": "give them power in the land and make the Pharaoh, Haman (his Minister), and their armies to experience from their victims what they feared most.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 386,
            "ruku": 334,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3259,
            "text": "We inspired Moses' mother saying, 'Breast-feed your son. When you become afraid for his life, throw him into the sea. Do not be afraid or grieved for We shall return him to you and make him a Messenger.'",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 386,
            "ruku": 334,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3260,
            "text": "The people of the Pharaoh picked him up (without realizing) that he would become their enemy and a source of their sorrow. The Pharaoh, Haman, and their army were sinful people.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 386,
            "ruku": 334,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3261,
            "text": "The Pharaoh's wife said, 'He, (Moses), is the delight of our eyes. Do not kill him. Perhaps he will benefit us or we may adopt him.' They were unaware of the future.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 386,
            "ruku": 334,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3262,
            "text": "The heart of Moses' mother was relieved and confident. But she would almost have made the whole matter public had We not strengthened her heart with faith.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 386,
            "ruku": 334,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3263,
            "text": "She told Moses' sister to follow her brother. His sister watched him from one side and the people of the Pharaoh did not notice her presence.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 386,
            "ruku": 334,
            "hizbQuarter": 154,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3264,
            "text": "We had decreed that the infant must not be breast-fed by any nurse besides his mother. His sister said to the people of the Pharaoh, 'May I show you a family who can nurse him for you with kindness?'",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 386,
            "ruku": 334,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3265,
            "text": "Thus did We return Moses to his mother that We would delight her eyes, relieve her sorrows, and let her know that the promise of God was true, but many people do not know.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 386,
            "ruku": 334,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3266,
            "text": "When he become matured and grow to manhood, We granted him wisdom and knowledge. Thus do We reward the righteous ones.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 387,
            "ruku": 335,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3267,
            "text": "He entered the city without the knowledge of its inhabitants and found two men fighting each other. One was his follower and the other his enemy. His follower asked him for help. Moses struck his enemy to death, but later said, 'It was the work of satan; he is the sworn enemy of the human being and wants to mislead him'.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 387,
            "ruku": 335,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3268,
            "text": "(Moses) said, 'Lord, I have wronged myself. Forgive me!' The Lord forgave him; He is All-forgiving and All-merciful.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 387,
            "ruku": 335,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3269,
            "text": "He said, 'Lord, in appreciation for Your favor to me I shall never support the criminals'.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 387,
            "ruku": 335,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3270,
            "text": "He remained in the city but very afraid and cautious. Suddenly the person who asked him for help the previous day asked him for help again. Moses said, 'You are certainly a mischievous person'.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 387,
            "ruku": 335,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3271,
            "text": "When Moses was about to attack their enemy, he said, 'Moses, do you want to kill me as you slew a soul the other day? Do you want to become a tyrant in the land, not a reformer?'",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 387,
            "ruku": 335,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3272,
            "text": "A man came running from the farthest part of the city saying, 'Moses, people are planning to kill you. I sincerely advise you to leave the city.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 387,
            "ruku": 335,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3273,
            "text": "So he left the city afraid and cautious, saying, 'Lord, protect me against the unjust people'.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 387,
            "ruku": 335,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3274,
            "text": "When he started his journey to Midian he said, 'Perhaps my Lord will show me the right path.'",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 388,
            "ruku": 336,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3275,
            "text": "When he arrived at the well of Midian, he found some people watering (their sheep) and two women keeping the sheep away from the others. He asked the two women, 'What is the matter with you?' They replied, 'We cannot water our sheep until all the shepherds have driven away their flocks. Our father is an old man'.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 388,
            "ruku": 336,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3276,
            "text": "Moses watered their flocks and then sought shelter under a shadow praying, 'Lord, I need the means to preserve (the power) that You have granted me.'",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 388,
            "ruku": 336,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3277,
            "text": "One of the women, walking bashfully, came to Moses and said, 'My father calls you and wants to pay you for your watering our flocks.' When Moses came to the woman's father and told him his whole story, he said, 'Do not be afraid. Now you are secure from the unjust people.'",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 388,
            "ruku": 336,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3278,
            "text": "One of the women said to her father, 'Father, hire him; the best whom you may hire is a strong and trustworthy one.'",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 388,
            "ruku": 336,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3279,
            "text": "He (Shu'ayb) said to (Moses), 'I want to give one of my daughters to you in marriage on the condition that you will work for me for eight years, but you may continue for two more years only out of your own accord. I do not want it to become a burden for you. God willing, you will find me a righteous person'.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 388,
            "ruku": 336,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3280,
            "text": "(Moses) said, 'Let it be a binding contract between us and I shall be free to serve for any of the said terms. God will bear witness to our agreement.'",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 388,
            "ruku": 336,
            "hizbQuarter": 155,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3281,
            "text": "When Moses completed the term of the contract and departed from his employer with his family, he saw a fire (on his way) on one side of the Mount (Sinai). He asked his wife, 'Stay here. I can see some fire. Perhaps I will be able to bring some news of it or some fire for you to warm-up yourselves.'",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 389,
            "ruku": 337,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3282,
            "text": "He was called from a tree of the blessed spot of the bank of the right side of the valley when he appraoched it, 'Moses, I am God, the Lord of the Universe.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 389,
            "ruku": 337,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3283,
            "text": "Throw down your staff.' When Moses saw his staff moving on the ground like a living being he fled with no desire to step forward. He was told, 'Moses, step forward. Do not be afraid; you will be safe and secure.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 389,
            "ruku": 337,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3284,
            "text": "Place your hand in your pocket; it will come out sheer white but not sick. Be humble for fear of God and show these two miracles of your Lord to the Pharaoh and his officials; they are an evil-doing people.'",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 389,
            "ruku": 337,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3285,
            "text": "(Moses) said, 'Lord, I have killed a man from their people and I am afraid that they will kill me.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 389,
            "ruku": 337,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3286,
            "text": "My brother Aaron is more fluent then I am. Send him with me to assist me and express my truthfulness; I am afraid they will reject me'.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 389,
            "ruku": 337,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3287,
            "text": "The Lord said, 'We will support you by your brother and will grant you such prestige that no one will dare to approach anyone of you. By the help of Our miracles both you and your follower will certainly triumph.'",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 389,
            "ruku": 337,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3288,
            "text": "When Moses came to them with Our miracles, they said, 'These are only invented magic. We have never heard of such things from our fathers'.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 390,
            "ruku": 337,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3289,
            "text": "Moses said, 'My Lord knows best who has received guidance from Him and who will achieve a happy end. The unjust ones certainly will have no happiness.'",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 390,
            "ruku": 337,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3290,
            "text": "The Pharaoh said, 'My people, I know no one who could be your lord besides myself. Haman, construct for me a tower of baked bricks so that I may climb on it and see the God of Moses; I think he is a liar.'",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 390,
            "ruku": 337,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3291,
            "text": "The Pharaoh and his army were puffed-up with pride in the land for no true cause. They thought that they would never return to Us.",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 390,
            "ruku": 337,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3292,
            "text": "We sized him and his army and threw them into the sea. See how terrible was the end of the unjust people!",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 390,
            "ruku": 337,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3293,
            "text": "We made them the kinds of leaders who would invite people to the fire and who would receive no help on the Day of Judgment.",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 390,
            "ruku": 337,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3294,
            "text": "We made them to be mentioned with condemnation in this life and they will be disgraced on the Day of Judgment.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 390,
            "ruku": 337,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3295,
            "text": "After destroying the people of the ancient towns We gave the Book to Moses to be a source of knowledge, a guidance, and mercy for mankind so that perhaps they would take heed.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 390,
            "ruku": 338,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3296,
            "text": "(Muhammad), you were not present at the west bank to witness when We gave the commandments to Moses.",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 391,
            "ruku": 338,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3297,
            "text": "But We raised many generations after Moses and they lived for many years. You did not dwell with the people of Midian reciting Our revelations to them, but We had certainly sent Messengers to them.",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 391,
            "ruku": 338,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3298,
            "text": "You had not been present at the side of the Mount (Sinai) when We called Moses (from the tree), but through Our mercy we told you his story so that you might warn the people",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 391,
            "ruku": 338,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3299,
            "text": "to whom no warner had been sent that perhaps they might take heed, and that, on experiencing afflictions because of their own deeds, they may not say, 'Lord, would that You had sent to us a Messenger so that we could follow Your revelations and become believers'.",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 391,
            "ruku": 338,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3300,
            "text": "When the Truth from Us came to them they said, 'Would that he, (Muhammad), had received what was given to Moses (by his Lord).' Did not they reject what Moses had brought to them saying, 'These two, Moses and Aaron, are two magicians who support each other. We do not have any faith in them.'",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 391,
            "ruku": 338,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3301,
            "text": "(Muhammad), tell them, 'Bring a Book if you are able to, from God better in its guidance than the Torah and the Quran; I shall follow it'.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 391,
            "ruku": 338,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3302,
            "text": "If they cannot meet such a challenge, know that they are only following their (evil) desires. Who strays more than one who follows his desires without guidance from God? God does not guide the unjust people.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 391,
            "ruku": 338,
            "hizbQuarter": 156,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3303,
            "text": "We sent Our guidance to them so that perhaps they might take heed.",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 392,
            "ruku": 339,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3304,
            "text": "(Some of) the followers of the Bible believe in the Quran.",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 392,
            "ruku": 339,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3305,
            "text": "When it is recited to them, they say, 'We believe in it. It is the Truth from our Lord. We were Muslims before it was revealed'.",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 392,
            "ruku": 339,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3306,
            "text": "These will receive double reward for their forbearance, replacing evil by virtue, and for their spending for the cause of God.",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 392,
            "ruku": 339,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3307,
            "text": "When they hear impious words, they ignore them, saying, 'We shall be responsible for our deeds and you will be responsible for yours. Peace be with you. We do not want to become ignorant.'",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 392,
            "ruku": 339,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3308,
            "text": "(Muhammad), you cannot guide whomever you love, but God guides whomever He wants and knows best those who seek guidance.",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 392,
            "ruku": 339,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3309,
            "text": "They, (the pagans), say, 'If we were to follow your guidance we would be snatched away from our land. Have We not given them the secure, holy precinct wherein all types of fruits are brought to them as a sustenance from Us? However, many of them do not know it.",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 392,
            "ruku": 339,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3310,
            "text": "How many nations, who had enjoyed great prosperity, had We destroyed? Those are their homes which were not inhabited thereafter except for a short time. Only We were their heirs.",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 392,
            "ruku": 339,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3311,
            "text": "Your Lord did not destroy the people of the towns without first sending a Messenger to the mother town who would recite His revelations to them. We did not want to destroy the towns if the people therein were not unjust.",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 392,
            "ruku": 339,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3312,
            "text": "Whatever you (people) have been given are only the means for enjoyment and beauty of the worldly life, but the means of enjoyment (which you will receive from God) in the life to come will be better and everlasting. Will you then not take heed?",
            "numberInSurah": 60,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 393,
            "ruku": 339,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3313,
            "text": "Is the case of those to whom We have promised good things - which they will certainly receive in the life to come - equal to the case of those to whom We have granted the means of enjoyment in the worldly life and who will certainly be questioned about them in the life to come?",
            "numberInSurah": 61,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 393,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3314,
            "text": "On the day when He will ask (the latter group), 'Where are those whom you had considered equal to Me?'",
            "numberInSurah": 62,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 393,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3315,
            "text": "Those who have become subject to punishment will say, 'Lord, they seduced us.' Their idols will say, 'We seduced them but we renounce their worshipping us for it was not us whom they worshipped'.",
            "numberInSurah": 63,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 393,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3316,
            "text": "They will be told to call their idols. They will call them but will receive no answer. They will see the torment approaching and wish that they had sought guidance.",
            "numberInSurah": 64,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 393,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3317,
            "text": "On the day when God will call them and ask them, 'What answer did you give to (Our) messengers?'",
            "numberInSurah": 65,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 393,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3318,
            "text": "The door to all answers will be closed to them and they will not even be able to ask one another.",
            "numberInSurah": 66,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 393,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3319,
            "text": "However, those who have repented and have become righteously striving believers will perhaps have everlasting happiness.",
            "numberInSurah": 67,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 393,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3320,
            "text": "Your Lord creates and chooses (to grant mercy) to whomever He wants. (In matters of guidance) they (unbelievers) do not have the choice to choose whatever they want. God is too exalted to be considered equal to anything else.",
            "numberInSurah": 68,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 393,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3321,
            "text": "Your Lord knows all that their hearts hide or reveal.",
            "numberInSurah": 69,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 393,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3322,
            "text": "He is the only God and it is only He who deserves to be given thanks in this world and in the life to come. Judgment is in His hands and to Him you will all return.",
            "numberInSurah": 70,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 393,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3323,
            "text": "(Muhammad), ask them, 'Think, if God were to cause the night to continue until the Day of Judgment which Lord besides Him could bring you light? Will you then not listen to (His revelations)?'",
            "numberInSurah": 71,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 394,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3324,
            "text": "Say, 'Do you not think that if God were to cause the day to continue until the Day of Judgment, which Lord besides Him could bring you the night to rest. Do you not see (His signs)?'",
            "numberInSurah": 72,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 394,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3325,
            "text": "He has made the night and day for you to rest as a mercy to you and seek His favor and that perhaps you will give Him thanks.",
            "numberInSurah": 73,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 394,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3326,
            "text": "God will call the unbelievers on the Day of Judgment and ask them, 'Where are your idols in which you had faith?",
            "numberInSurah": 74,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 394,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3327,
            "text": "We shall call from every nation a witness and shall ask them to bring proof (in support of their belief). They will know that truth belongs to God and that whatever they had falsely invented has abandoned them.",
            "numberInSurah": 75,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 394,
            "ruku": 340,
            "hizbQuarter": 157,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3328,
            "text": "Korah was a man from the people of Moses. This man rebelled against them. We had given him so much treasure that the keys of the stores of his treasures could hardly even be carried by a group of strong people. His people told him, 'Do not be proud of your wealth; God does not love those who are proudly happy of their wealth.",
            "numberInSurah": 76,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 394,
            "ruku": 341,
            "hizbQuarter": 158,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3329,
            "text": "Seek the gains of the life to come through your wealth without ignoring your share of this life. Do favors to others just as God has done favors to you. Do not commit evil in the land for God does not love the evil-doers.'",
            "numberInSurah": 77,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 394,
            "ruku": 341,
            "hizbQuarter": 158,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3330,
            "text": "He said, 'I have received this wealth because of my knowledge.' Did he not know that God had destroyed many generations that lived before him who were stronger than him in power and people? (There will be no need) to ask the criminals what sins they have committed, (for the angels already know them)",
            "numberInSurah": 78,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 395,
            "ruku": 341,
            "hizbQuarter": 158,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3331,
            "text": "Korah would bedeck himself to show off his wealth. Those who wanted worldly gains would say, 'Would that we were given that which Korah has received. He has certainly received a great share.'",
            "numberInSurah": 79,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 395,
            "ruku": 341,
            "hizbQuarter": 158,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3332,
            "text": "The people who had received knowledge would tell them, 'Woe to you! The reward of God is far better for the righteously striving believers. No one can receive such reward except those who exercise patience.'",
            "numberInSurah": 80,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 395,
            "ruku": 341,
            "hizbQuarter": 158,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3333,
            "text": "We caused the earth to swallow up him and his home. No one besides God could help him nor could he himself achieve victory.",
            "numberInSurah": 81,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 395,
            "ruku": 341,
            "hizbQuarter": 158,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3334,
            "text": "The people who the other day had wished to be like him, began saying, 'Woe to us! God gives abundant wealth only to those of His servants whom He wants and He determines everyone's share. Had it not been for God's favor to us, He would have caused the earth to swallow us up. Woe to the unbelievers who will have no happiness.'",
            "numberInSurah": 82,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 395,
            "ruku": 341,
            "hizbQuarter": 158,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3335,
            "text": "There is the life hereafter which We have prepared for those who do not want to impose their superiority over the others in the land nor commit evil therein. The happy end certainly belongs to the pious ones.",
            "numberInSurah": 83,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 395,
            "ruku": 341,
            "hizbQuarter": 158,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3336,
            "text": "The reward for a good deed will be greater than the deed itself and the recompense for an evil deed will be equivalent to the deed.",
            "numberInSurah": 84,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 395,
            "ruku": 341,
            "hizbQuarter": 158,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3337,
            "text": "(Muhammad), God, Who has commanded you to follow the guidance of the Quran, will certainly return you victoriously to your place of birth. Say, 'My Lord knows best who has brought guidance and who is in plain error.'",
            "numberInSurah": 85,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 396,
            "ruku": 341,
            "hizbQuarter": 158,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3338,
            "text": "You had no hope of receiving the Book except by the mercy of your Lord. Do not be a supporter of the unbelievers.",
            "numberInSurah": 86,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 396,
            "ruku": 341,
            "hizbQuarter": 158,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3339,
            "text": "Let them not prevent you from following the revelations of God after they are revealed to you. Call (mankind) to your Lord and do not be a pagan.",
            "numberInSurah": 87,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 396,
            "ruku": 341,
            "hizbQuarter": 158,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3340,
            "text": "Do not worship anything besides God. He is the only God. Everything will be destroyed except God. To Him belongs Judgment and to Him you will all return.",
            "numberInSurah": 88,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 396,
            "ruku": 341,
            "hizbQuarter": 158,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 29,
        "name": "سُورَةُ العَنكَبُوتِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Ankaboot",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Spider",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 3341,
            "text": "Alif. Lam. Mim.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 396,
            "ruku": 342,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3342,
            "text": "Do people think they will not be tested because they say, 'We have faith?'",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 396,
            "ruku": 342,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3343,
            "text": "We had certainly tried those who lived before them to make sure who were truthful in their faith and who were liars.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 396,
            "ruku": 342,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3344,
            "text": "Do the evil-doers think they can escape Us? How terrible is their judgment?",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 396,
            "ruku": 342,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3345,
            "text": "Let those who have the desire to be in the presence of God on the Day of Judgment know that their day will certainly be coming. God is All-Hearing and All-Knowing.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 396,
            "ruku": 342,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3346,
            "text": "Whoever strives hard should know that it is for his own good. God is independent of the whole world.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 396,
            "ruku": 342,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3347,
            "text": "We shall expiate the sins of the righteously striving believers and shall reward them better than their deeds.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 397,
            "ruku": 342,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3348,
            "text": "We have advised the human being, 'Be kind to your parents. Do not obey them if they force you to consider equal to Me things which you do not know are such.' You will all return (to Me) and I shall show all that you have done.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 397,
            "ruku": 342,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3349,
            "text": "We shall admit the righteously striving believers into the company of the pious ones.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 397,
            "ruku": 342,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3350,
            "text": "Some people say, 'We have faith in God.' But when they face some hardship for His cause, they begin to consider the persecution that they have experienced from people as a torment from God. When your Lord grants you a victory, they say, 'We were with you.' Does God not know best what is in the hearts of every creature?",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 397,
            "ruku": 342,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3351,
            "text": "God certainly knows all about the believers and the hypocrites.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 397,
            "ruku": 342,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3352,
            "text": "The unbelievers say to the believers. 'Follow our way. We shall take the responsibility for your sins.' They cannot take responsibility for any of the sins. They are only liars.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 397,
            "ruku": 342,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3353,
            "text": "Besides the other burdens that they will have to carry, they will certainly be loaded with the burden of their own sins. They will be questioned on the Day of Judgment about what they had falsely invented.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 397,
            "ruku": 342,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3354,
            "text": "We sent Noah to his people and he lived with them for nine hundred and fifty years, then the flood engulfed them for their injustice.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 397,
            "ruku": 343,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3355,
            "text": "We saved Noah and the people in the Ark and made (their case) a miracle for the world.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 398,
            "ruku": 343,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3356,
            "text": "Abraham told his people, 'Worship God and have fear of Him. It is better for you if only you knew it.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 398,
            "ruku": 343,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3357,
            "text": "You worship idols besides God and you create falsehood. Whatever you worship besides Him cannot provide you with anything for your sustenance. Seek your sustenance from the bounties of God. Worship Him. Give Him thanks. To Him you will all return.'",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 398,
            "ruku": 343,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3358,
            "text": "If you, (pagans), call our (revelations) lies, certainly many generations living before you have also done the same thing. The duty of a Messenger is only to preach clearly.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 398,
            "ruku": 343,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3359,
            "text": "Have they not seen how God begins the creation and then turns it back? This is not difficult at all for God.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 398,
            "ruku": 343,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3360,
            "text": "(Muhammad), say to them, 'Travel through the land and see how He has begun the creation and how He will invent the next life. God has power over all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 398,
            "ruku": 343,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3361,
            "text": "He punishes or grants mercy to whomever He wants and to Him you will all return.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 398,
            "ruku": 343,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3362,
            "text": "You cannot challenge God in the heavens or in the earth. No one besides God is your guardian or helper.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 398,
            "ruku": 343,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3363,
            "text": "Those who have rejected God's revelations have no hope in receiving His mercy. They will face a painful torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 398,
            "ruku": 344,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3364,
            "text": "(Abraham's) people had no answer except suggesting, 'Kill him or burn him.' But God saved him from the fire. In this there is evidence (of truth) for the believing people.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 399,
            "ruku": 344,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3365,
            "text": "Abraham said, 'You believe in idols besides God only out of worldly love, but on the Day of Judgment you will reject and condemn each other. Your dwelling will be fire and no one will help you.'",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 399,
            "ruku": 344,
            "hizbQuarter": 159,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3366,
            "text": "Only Lot believed in (Abraham) and said, 'I seek refuge in my Lord, for He is Majestic and All-wise'.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 399,
            "ruku": 344,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3367,
            "text": "We granted Isaac and Jacob to Abraham and We bestowed upon his offspring, prophethood and the Book. We gave him his reward in this world and in the next life, he will be among the pious ones.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 399,
            "ruku": 344,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3368,
            "text": "Lot told his people, 'You are certainly committing the kind of indecency which no one in the world has committed before'.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 399,
            "ruku": 344,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3369,
            "text": "Do you engage in carnal relations with men, rob the travellers, and commit evil in your gatherings? His people had no answer but to say, 'Bring upon us the torment of God if you are truthful'.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 399,
            "ruku": 344,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3370,
            "text": "He prayed, 'Lord help me against the evil-doing people.'",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 399,
            "ruku": 344,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3371,
            "text": "When Our angelic Messengers brought glad news to Abraham, they told him, 'We are about to destroy the people of this town for their injustice'.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 400,
            "ruku": 345,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3372,
            "text": "Abraham said, 'Lot is there in that town!' They said, 'We know everyone there. We shall certainly save him and his family except his wife who will remain behind.'",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 400,
            "ruku": 345,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3373,
            "text": "When Our angelic Messengers came to Lot, he was grieved and depressed to see them. They told him, 'Do not be afraid or grieved. We will rescue you and your family except your wife who will remain behind.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 400,
            "ruku": 345,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3374,
            "text": "We will bring torment from the sky on this town because of the evil-deeds of its inhabitants'.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 400,
            "ruku": 345,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3375,
            "text": "We left manifest evidence (of the truth) there for the people of understanding.",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 400,
            "ruku": 345,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3376,
            "text": "We sent to the people of Midian their brother Shu`ayb. He told them, 'Worship God. Have hope in the life to come. Do not spread evil in the land'.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 400,
            "ruku": 345,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3377,
            "text": "They rejected him so We jolted them with a violent earthquake and they were left motionless in their houses.",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 400,
            "ruku": 345,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3378,
            "text": "How the people of Ad and Thamud were destroyed is evident to you from their homes. Satan made their deeds seem attractive to them and prevented them from the right path, even though they had visions.",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 400,
            "ruku": 345,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3379,
            "text": "Korah, the Pharaoh, and Haman were also destroyed. Moses had brought them illustrious miracles, but they were puffed-up with pride in the land and they could not defeat Us.",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 401,
            "ruku": 345,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3380,
            "text": "We punished all of these people because of their sin. Some of them were struck by a violent sand-storm, some by a blast of sound, others were swallowed up by the earth, and some were drowned (in the sea). God did not do injustice to them, but they had wronged themselves.",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 401,
            "ruku": 345,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3381,
            "text": "The belief of considering other things as one's guardians besides God is as feeble as a spider's web. The spider's web is the frailest of all dwellings, if only they knew it.",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 401,
            "ruku": 345,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3382,
            "text": "God knows whatever they worship besides Him; He is the Majestic and All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 401,
            "ruku": 345,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3383,
            "text": "These are parables which We tell to human being, but only the learned ones understand them.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 401,
            "ruku": 345,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3384,
            "text": "God has created the heavens and the earth for a genuine purpose. In this there is evidence (of the truth) for the believers.",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 401,
            "ruku": 345,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3385,
            "text": "(Muhammad), recite to them what has been revealed to you in the Book and be steadfast in prayer; prayer keeps one away from indecency and evil. It is the greatest act of worshipping God. God knows what you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 20,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 401,
            "ruku": 346,
            "hizbQuarter": 160,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3386,
            "text": "Do not argue with the People of the Book except only by the best manner, except the unjust among them. Tell them, 'We believe in what is revealed to us and to you. Our Lord and your Lord is one. We have submitted ourselves to His will'.",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 402,
            "ruku": 346,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3387,
            "text": "We have revealed the Book to you. Some of the People of the Book and some of the pagans also believe in it. No one rejects Our revelations except the infidels.",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 402,
            "ruku": 346,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3388,
            "text": "You were not able to read or write before the Quran was revealed to you; otherwise, the followers of falsehood would have tried to confuse the matter.",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 402,
            "ruku": 346,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3389,
            "text": "In fact, the Quran consists of illustrious verses that exist in the hearts of those who have knowledge. No one rejects Our revelations except the unjust ones.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 402,
            "ruku": 346,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3390,
            "text": "They say, 'Why a miracle is not sent to him from his Lord.' Say, 'Miracles are in the hands of God. I am simply a warner.'",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 402,
            "ruku": 346,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3391,
            "text": "Is it not enough for them that We have revealed the Book to you to be recited to them. It is a mercy and a reminder for the believers.",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 402,
            "ruku": 346,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3392,
            "text": "Say, 'God is sufficient as a witness between me and you. He knows all that is in the heavens and the earth.' Those who have faith in falsehood and disbelieve in God are certainly lost.",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 402,
            "ruku": 347,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3393,
            "text": "They demand you to bring upon them torment immediately. Had not the time been fixed, the torment would certainly have approached them. It would have come to them suddenly and they would not have even realized how it came.",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 403,
            "ruku": 347,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3394,
            "text": "They demand you to bring upon them the torment immediately. Hell will certainly engulf the unbelievers.",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 403,
            "ruku": 347,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3395,
            "text": "They will be told on the Day of Judgment, when the torment will surround them from all sides, 'Suffer the consequences of your deeds.'",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 403,
            "ruku": 347,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3396,
            "text": "My believing servants, My land is vast. Worship Me alone.",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 403,
            "ruku": 347,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3397,
            "text": "Every soul will experience the agony of death and to Me you will all return.",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 403,
            "ruku": 347,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3398,
            "text": "We shall give mansions in Paradise wherein streams flow to the righteously striving believers and therein they will live forever. How blessed is the reward of the hard working people",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 403,
            "ruku": 347,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3399,
            "text": "who have exercised patience and who have had trust in their Lord.",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 403,
            "ruku": 347,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3400,
            "text": "There are many living creatures which do not carry their sustenance, but God provides them and you with sustenance. He is All-hearing and All-knowing.",
            "numberInSurah": 60,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 403,
            "ruku": 347,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3401,
            "text": "If you ask them, 'Who has created the heavens and the earth and has subdued the sun and moon?' They will say, 'God has done it.' So why are they wandering about!?",
            "numberInSurah": 61,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 403,
            "ruku": 347,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3402,
            "text": "God increases the sustenance of whichever of His servants He wants and He determines their share. God has the knowledge of all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 62,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 403,
            "ruku": 347,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3403,
            "text": "If you ask them, 'Who has sent down water from the sky to revive the dead earth?' They will say, 'God has done it.' Say, 'It is only God who deserves all praise, but many of them do not understand.'",
            "numberInSurah": 63,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 403,
            "ruku": 347,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3404,
            "text": "The worldly life is not more than a childish game. It is the life hereafter which will be the real life, if only they knew it.",
            "numberInSurah": 64,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 404,
            "ruku": 348,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3405,
            "text": "When they sail in a boat, they sincerely pray to God with pure faith. But when We bring them safely to land, they start considering things equal to God.",
            "numberInSurah": 65,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 404,
            "ruku": 348,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3406,
            "text": "Let them be ungrateful to what We have granted them. Let them enjoy themselves, but they will soon know (the consequences of their deeds).",
            "numberInSurah": 66,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 404,
            "ruku": 348,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3407,
            "text": "Have the (pagans) not seen that We have made the holy precinct a safe place while all the people around are suffering terror. Do they believe in falsehood and disbelieve in God's bounties?",
            "numberInSurah": 67,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 404,
            "ruku": 348,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3408,
            "text": "Who is more unjust than one who invents falsehood against God or rejects the Truth after it has come to him? Is not hell the dwelling for the disbelievers.",
            "numberInSurah": 68,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 404,
            "ruku": 348,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3409,
            "text": "We shall certainly guide those who strive for Our cause to Our path. God is certainly with the righteous ones.",
            "numberInSurah": 69,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 404,
            "ruku": 348,
            "hizbQuarter": 161,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 30,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الرُّومِ",
        "englishName": "Ar-Room",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Romans",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 3410,
            "text": "Alif. Lam. Mim.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 404,
            "ruku": 349,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3411,
            "text": "The Romans have been defeated in a nearby land and after this defeat,",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 404,
            "ruku": 349,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3412,
            "text": "(within a few years) they will be victorious.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 404,
            "ruku": 349,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3413,
            "text": "All matters of the past and future are in the hands of God. The believers will enjoy the help of God on that Day.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 404,
            "ruku": 349,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3414,
            "text": "He helps whomever He wants. He is Majestic and All-merciful.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 404,
            "ruku": 349,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3415,
            "text": "This is the promise of God. God does not ignore His promise, but many people do not know.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 405,
            "ruku": 349,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3416,
            "text": "They only know the superficial realities of the worldly life and they are unaware of the life to come.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 405,
            "ruku": 349,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3417,
            "text": "Have they not thought that God has not created the heavens and the earth and all that is between them but for a genuine purpose to exist for an appointed term? Many people do not believe in their meeting with their Lord.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 405,
            "ruku": 349,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3418,
            "text": "Have they not travelled through the land to see how terrible was the end of the people who lived before them. The people who lived before them were stronger than them in might, in tilling, and in developing the earth. Our Messengers came to them with clear miracles. God did not do an injustice to them but they wronged themselves.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 405,
            "ruku": 349,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3419,
            "text": "The end of the evil-doers was terrible, for they had rejected the revelations of God and mocked them.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 405,
            "ruku": 349,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3420,
            "text": "God begins the creation then causes it to turn back and to Him you will all return.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 405,
            "ruku": 350,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3421,
            "text": "On the day when the Hour of Doom comes, the criminals will despair.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 405,
            "ruku": 350,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3422,
            "text": "None of the idols will intercede for them and they will reject their idols.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 405,
            "ruku": 350,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3423,
            "text": "When that day comes, (people) will be separated from one another.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 405,
            "ruku": 350,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3424,
            "text": "The righteously striving believers will happily live in paradise.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 405,
            "ruku": 350,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3425,
            "text": "However, the disbelievers, who called Our revelations and the Day of Judgment lies, will be brought into torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 406,
            "ruku": 350,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3426,
            "text": "Glory belongs to God all the time, in the evening and in the morning.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 406,
            "ruku": 350,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3427,
            "text": "To Him belongs all the thanks giving which takes place in the heavens and the earth, in the evenings and the noontime.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 406,
            "ruku": 350,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3428,
            "text": "He brings forth the living from the dead, takes out the dead from the living, and revives the earth from its death. Thus, you will all be brought back to life again.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 406,
            "ruku": 350,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3429,
            "text": "Some evidence of His existence are His creating you from clay and from that you became human beings scattered all around;",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 406,
            "ruku": 351,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3430,
            "text": "His creating spouses for you out of yourselves so that you might take comfort in them and His creating love and mercy among you. In this there is evidence (of the truth) for the people who (carefully) think.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 406,
            "ruku": 351,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3431,
            "text": "Other evidence of His existence are the creation of the heavens and the earth and the differences of languages and colors. In this there is evidence (of the truth) for the worlds (mankind).",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 406,
            "ruku": 351,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3432,
            "text": "Your sleeping during the night and in the day your seeking His favors are evidence (of the truth) for the people who have hearing.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 406,
            "ruku": 351,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3433,
            "text": "Also, of the evidence of His existence are His showing you lightening which gives you fear and hope and His sending water down from the sky which revives the earth after its death. In this there is evidence (of the truth) for the people of understanding.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 406,
            "ruku": 351,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3434,
            "text": "Some other evidence of His existence is that both the heavens and the earth stand firm at His command. When He will call you from the earth, you will start to come out.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 407,
            "ruku": 351,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3435,
            "text": "Everyone in the heavens and the earth belongs to Him and is subservient to Him.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 407,
            "ruku": 351,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3436,
            "text": "It is He who begins the creation, then, turns it back. For Him this is very easy. All the exalted attributes in the heavens and the earth belong to Him. He is the Majestic and All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 407,
            "ruku": 351,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3437,
            "text": "God has told you this parable about yourselves: Could your slaves share your wealth equally with you and could you fear them as you fear yourselves? Thus, do We clarify the evidence (of the truth) for the people of understanding.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 407,
            "ruku": 352,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3438,
            "text": "In fact, the unjust have followed their desires without knowledge. Who will guide those whom God has caused to go astray? No one will be their helper.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 407,
            "ruku": 352,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3439,
            "text": "(Muhammad), be devoted to the upright religion. It is harmonious with the nature which God has designed for people. The design of God cannot be altered. Thus is the upright religion, but many people do not know.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 407,
            "ruku": 352,
            "hizbQuarter": 162,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3440,
            "text": "Turn in repentance to Him. Have fear of Him. Be steadfast in your prayer. Do not be like the pagans",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 407,
            "ruku": 352,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3441,
            "text": "who have divided themselves into various religious sects, each one happy with their own belief.",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 407,
            "ruku": 352,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3442,
            "text": "When people face hardship, they begin praying to their Lord and turn in repentance to Him. When they receive mercy from Him, a group of them begin to consider things equal to God,",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 408,
            "ruku": 352,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3443,
            "text": "because of their ingratitude for what We have given them. Let them enjoy themselves, but they will soon know (the consequences of their deeds).",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 408,
            "ruku": 352,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3444,
            "text": "Have We sent them any authority to speak in support of their idols?",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 408,
            "ruku": 352,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3445,
            "text": "When people receive mercy, they are happy with it. However, when hardship befalls them because of their own deeds, they despair.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 408,
            "ruku": 352,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3446,
            "text": "Have they not seen how God increases the livelihood of whomever He wants and determines his share. In this there is evidence (of the truth) for the believing people.",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 408,
            "ruku": 352,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3447,
            "text": "Give the relatives, the destitute, and the needy travellers their share (of charity). It is better for those who want to please God and they will have everlasting happiness.",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 408,
            "ruku": 352,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3448,
            "text": "God will not allow to increase whatever illegal interest you try to receive in order to increase your wealth at the expense of people's property. Whatever amount of zakat you give to please God will be doubled (for you).",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 408,
            "ruku": 352,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3449,
            "text": "It is God who has created you and given you sustenance. He will make you die and will bring you back to life. Can any of your idols do such things? God is too Exalted to be considered equal to anything else.",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 408,
            "ruku": 352,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3450,
            "text": "Evil has spread over the land and the sea because of human deeds and through these God will cause some people to suffer so that perhaps they will return to Him.",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 408,
            "ruku": 353,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3451,
            "text": "(Muhammad), tell them, 'Travel through the land to see how terrible was the end of those who lived before. Many of them were pagans.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 409,
            "ruku": 353,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3452,
            "text": "Be devoted to the upright religion before the coming of the inevitable day when no one can escape from God and people will either be sent to Paradise or hell.'",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 409,
            "ruku": 353,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3453,
            "text": "Those who disbelieve do so against their own souls. Those who do good pave the way for their own benefit.",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 409,
            "ruku": 353,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3454,
            "text": "God will reward the righteously striving believers through His favor. He does not love the unbelievers.",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 409,
            "ruku": 353,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3455,
            "text": "Some evidence of His existence is His sending the glad-news-bearing winds so that He would let you to receive His mercy, cause the ships to sail by His command, and let you seek His favor so that perhaps you would give Him thanks.",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 409,
            "ruku": 353,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3456,
            "text": "(Muhammad), We had sent before you Our Messengers to their people. The Messengers showed them clear miracles and We took revenge on the criminals. It was necessary for Us to help the believers.",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 409,
            "ruku": 353,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3457,
            "text": "It is God who sends the winds to raise the clouds. He spreads them in the sky as He wants, then He intensifies them, and then you can see the rain coming down from the cloud. When He sends it down upon whichever of His servants He wants, they rejoice",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 409,
            "ruku": 353,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3458,
            "text": "at the rainfall, though before that they had been in despair.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 409,
            "ruku": 353,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3459,
            "text": "Look at the traces of the mercy of God, how He has revived the dead earth. God revives the dead; He has power over all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 409,
            "ruku": 353,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3460,
            "text": "Even if We had sent the wind and caused (the plants) to turn yellow and to fade away, they would still have remained in disbelief.",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 410,
            "ruku": 353,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3461,
            "text": "You cannot make the dead listen, nor the deaf hear. Thus, they, (the disbelievers), turn away on their heels.",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 410,
            "ruku": 353,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3462,
            "text": "You cannot guide the straying blind. You can make no one listen except those who believe in Our revelations and are Muslims.",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 410,
            "ruku": 353,
            "hizbQuarter": 163,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3463,
            "text": "It is God who has created you weak, then, given you strength after your weakness and caused you to become weak and old after being strong. He creates whatever He wants. He is All-knowing and All-powerful.",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 410,
            "ruku": 354,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3464,
            "text": "On the day when the Hour of Doom comes, the criminals will swear that they have remained (in their graves) for no more than an hour. They had been inventing lies in this way.",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 410,
            "ruku": 354,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3465,
            "text": "Those who have received knowledge and have faith will say, 'By the decree of God, you have remained for the exact period which was mentioned in the Book of God about the Day of Resurrection. This is the Day of Resurrection, but you did not know.'",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 410,
            "ruku": 354,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3466,
            "text": "The excuses of the unjust on this day will be of no avail to them and they will not be able to please God.",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 410,
            "ruku": 354,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3467,
            "text": "We have told people various parables in this Quran. Even if you had shown them a miracle, the unbelievers would have said, 'You are only the followers of falsehood'.",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 410,
            "ruku": 354,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3468,
            "text": "Thus does God seal the hearts of those who do not know.",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 410,
            "ruku": 354,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3469,
            "text": "Be patient. The promise of God is certainly true. Let not the faithless make you despair of the promise of God.",
            "numberInSurah": 60,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 410,
            "ruku": 354,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 31,
        "name": "سُورَةُ لُقۡمَانَ",
        "englishName": "Luqman",
        "englishNameTranslation": "Luqman",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 3470,
            "text": "Alif. Lam. Mim.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 411,
            "ruku": 355,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3471,
            "text": "These are the verses of the Book of wisdom.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 411,
            "ruku": 355,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3472,
            "text": "A guidance and mercy for the righteous",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 411,
            "ruku": 355,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3473,
            "text": "people who are steadfast in prayer, pay the religious tax, and have firm belief in the life to come.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 411,
            "ruku": 355,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3474,
            "text": "They follow the guidance of their Lord and they will have everlasting happiness.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 411,
            "ruku": 355,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3475,
            "text": "(In an attempt to show that God's revelations are only ancient legends) some people pay for meaningless tales to draw others attention away from the Quran without knowledge and treat as a matter of fun. They will suffer a humiliating torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 411,
            "ruku": 355,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3476,
            "text": "When Our revelations are recited to them, they turn back on their heels out of pride as if they did not hear them or their ears had been sealed off. Warn them of the painful torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 411,
            "ruku": 355,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3477,
            "text": "The righteously striving believers will enter Paradise",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 411,
            "ruku": 355,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3478,
            "text": "wherein they will live forever. It is the true promise of God. He is Majestic and All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 411,
            "ruku": 355,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3479,
            "text": "He has created the heavens without pillar as you can see, fixed the mountains on earth so that it may not shake you away, and settled therein all types of living creatures. We have sent down water from the sky and made all kinds of plants grow in gracious pairs.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 411,
            "ruku": 355,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3480,
            "text": "This is the creation of God. Show me what those whom you consider equal to God have created. In fact, the unjust ones are in plain error.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 411,
            "ruku": 355,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3481,
            "text": "We gave wisdom to Luqman so that he would give thanks to God. Those who give thanks to God do so for their own good. Those who are ungrateful should know that God is Self-sufficient and Praiseworthy.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 412,
            "ruku": 356,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3482,
            "text": "Luqman advised his son telling him, 'My son, do not consider anything equal to God, for it is the greatest injustice.'",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 412,
            "ruku": 356,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3483,
            "text": "(Concerning his parents), We advised the man, whose mother bears him with great pain and breast-feeds him for two years, to give thanks to Me first and then to them, to Me all things proceed.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 412,
            "ruku": 356,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3484,
            "text": "If they try to force you to consider things equal to Me, which you cannot justify, equal to Me, do not obey them. Maintain lawful relations with them in this world and follow the path of those who turn in repentance to Me. To Me you will all return and I shall tell you all that you have done.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 412,
            "ruku": 356,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3485,
            "text": "'My son, God keeps the records of all the good and evil deeds, even if they are as small as a grain of mustard seed, hidden in a rock or in the heavens or the earth. God is subtle and All-aware.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 412,
            "ruku": 356,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3486,
            "text": "My son, be steadfast in prayer. Make others do good. Prevent them from doing evil. Be patient in hardship. Patience comes from faith and determination.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 412,
            "ruku": 356,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3487,
            "text": "Do not scornfully turn your face away from people. Do not walk around puffed-up with pride; God does not love arrogant and boastful people.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 412,
            "ruku": 356,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3488,
            "text": "Be moderate in your walking and your talking. The most unpleasant sound is the braying of donkeys.'",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 412,
            "ruku": 356,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3489,
            "text": "Have you not seen that God has made all that is in the heavens and the earth, subservient to you (human beings), and has extended and perfected for you His apparent and unseen bounties? Some people argue about God without knowledge, guidance, or an enlightening book.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 413,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3490,
            "text": "When they are told to follow what God has revealed to them, they say, 'We shall only follow our father's way of life.' Will they follow it even if it is Satan who is calling them to the burning torment?",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 413,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 164,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3491,
            "text": "Whoever submits himself to the will of God in righteousness has certainly achieved a strong-hold. The end of all things is in the hands of God.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 413,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3492,
            "text": "(Muhammad), do not let the disbelievers grieve you. To Us they will all return and We shall tell them all about what they have done. God knows best what is in everyone's hearts.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 413,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3493,
            "text": "We shall allow them to enjoy themselves for a short while, then force them into severe torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 413,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3494,
            "text": "If you ask them, 'Who has created the heavens and the earth,' they will certainly say, 'God has created them.' Say, 'It is only God who deserves all praise, but most of them do not know'.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 413,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3495,
            "text": "To God belongs all that is in the heavens and the earth. He is Self-sufficient and Praiseworthy.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 413,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3496,
            "text": "If all the trees in the earth were pens and the ocean, with seven more oceans, were ink still these could not suffice to record all the Words of God. God is Majestic and All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 413,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3497,
            "text": "For God your creation and your resurrection are only like the creation and resurrection of one soul. God is All-hearing and All-seeing.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 413,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3498,
            "text": "Have you not seen that God causes the night to enter into the day and the day into the night. He has made the sun and moon subservient (to Himself). Each moves (in an orbit) for an appointed time. God is certainly All-aware of what you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 414,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3499,
            "text": "This is because God is the supreme Truth and whatever they worship besides Him is falsehood. God is the Most High and the Most Great.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 414,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3500,
            "text": "Have you not seen that the ships sail in the ocean through the bounty of God so that He may show you the evidence (of His existence). There is evidence (of the truth) in this for every forbearing and grateful one.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 414,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3501,
            "text": "When the waves cover them like shadows, they pray to God with sincerity in their religion, but when We bring them safely to land, only some of them follow the right path. No one rejects Our revelations except the treacherous ungrateful ones.",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 414,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3502,
            "text": "Mankind, have fear of your Lord and the day when a father will be of no avail to his son, nor will a son carry any part of the burden of his father. The promise of God is true. Do not let the worldly life deceive you nor let your pride deceive you about God.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 414,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3503,
            "text": "Only God has the knowledge of the coming of the Hour of Doom. He sends down the rain and knows what is in the wombs. No soul is aware of what it will achieve tomorrow and no soul knows in which land it will die. God is All-knowing and All-aware.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 414,
            "ruku": 357,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 32,
        "name": "سُورَةُ السَّجۡدَةِ",
        "englishName": "As-Sajda",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Prostration",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 3504,
            "text": "Alif. Lam. Mim.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 415,
            "ruku": 358,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3505,
            "text": "There is no doubt that this Book is revealed by the Lord of the Universe.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 415,
            "ruku": 358,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3506,
            "text": "Do they say that he, (Muhammad), has invented it? No, it is the truth from your Lord so that you will warn the people who have not received a warning before you. Perhaps they will seek guidance.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 415,
            "ruku": 358,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3507,
            "text": "God is the one who created the heavens and the earth and all that is between them in six days, then He established His dominion over the Throne. No one besides Him is your guardian or intercessor. Will you then not take heed?",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 415,
            "ruku": 358,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3508,
            "text": "He sends the regulation of the affair from the heavens to the earth, then on the day which is equal to one thousand years of yours, it will ascend to Him.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 415,
            "ruku": 358,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3509,
            "text": "He knows the unseen and the seen. He is Majestic and All-merciful.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 415,
            "ruku": 358,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3510,
            "text": "It is He Who created everything in the best manner and began the creation of the human being from clay.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 415,
            "ruku": 358,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3511,
            "text": "He made His offspring come into existence from an extract of insignificant fluid,",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 415,
            "ruku": 358,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3512,
            "text": "then He gave it proper shape and blew His spirit in it. He made ears, eyes and hearts for you, but you give Him very little thanks.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 415,
            "ruku": 358,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3513,
            "text": "They have said, 'How can we be brought to life again after we have been lost in the earth?' In fact, they have no faith in the Day of Judgment",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 415,
            "ruku": 358,
            "hizbQuarter": 165,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3514,
            "text": "(Muhammad), say, 'The angel of death, who is appointed over everyone of you, will cause you to die and to your Lord you will all return.'",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 415,
            "ruku": 358,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3515,
            "text": "Would that you could see (on the Day of Judgment) that criminals, with their heads hanging down before their Lord, saying, 'Our Lord, we have seen and heard. Send us back to act righteously. Now we have strong faith'.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 416,
            "ruku": 359,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3516,
            "text": "Had We wanted, We could have given guidance to every soul, but My decree, that hell will be filled-up with jinn and people, has already been executed.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 416,
            "ruku": 359,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3517,
            "text": "They will be told, 'Suffer on this Day of Judgment. For your having ignored it, We have ignored you. Suffer everlasting torment for your evil deeds.'",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 416,
            "ruku": 359,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3518,
            "text": "The only people who believe in Our revelations are those who, when reminded about them, bow down in prostration and glorify their Lord with His praise without pride.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 416,
            "ruku": 359,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": {
              "id": 10,
              "recommended": false,
              "obligatory": true
            }
          },
          {
            "number": 3519,
            "text": "Their sides give-up rest in beds in order to pray before their Lord in fear and hope. They spend for the cause of God out of what we have given them.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 416,
            "ruku": 359,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3520,
            "text": "No soul knows what delight awaits them as the reward for their deeds.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 416,
            "ruku": 359,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3521,
            "text": "Is a believer equal to an evil-doer? They are not equal at all.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 416,
            "ruku": 359,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3522,
            "text": "The righteously striving believers will have Paradise for their dwelling as the reward of their good deeds.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 416,
            "ruku": 359,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3523,
            "text": "However, the dwelling of the sinful ones will be hell fire. Each time they try to come out, they will be turned back with this remark, 'Suffer the torment of the fire which you had called a lie'.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 416,
            "ruku": 359,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3524,
            "text": "We shall certainly make them suffer worldly torment before suffering the great torment so that perhaps they may return to Us.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 417,
            "ruku": 359,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3525,
            "text": "Who are more unjust than those who are reminded of the revelation of their Lord, but have ignored them? We will take revenge on the criminal.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 417,
            "ruku": 359,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3526,
            "text": "We gave the Book to Moses - do not have any doubt about the Day of Judgment - and made it a guide for the children of Israel.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 417,
            "ruku": 360,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3527,
            "text": "We appointed some of the Israelites as leaders for their exercising patience to guide the others to Our commands. They had firm belief in Our revelations.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 417,
            "ruku": 360,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3528,
            "text": "Your Lord will issue His decree about their (believers and disbeliever's) differences on the Day of Judgment.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 417,
            "ruku": 360,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3529,
            "text": "Was it not a lesson for them, (the unbelievers), that We destroyed the many generations living before them among whose ruined dwellings they are now walking. In this there is many evidence (of the truth). Will they not then listen?",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 417,
            "ruku": 360,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3530,
            "text": "Have they not seen that We drive the water to the barren land and cause crops to grow which they and their cattle consume? Why, then, they will not see?",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 417,
            "ruku": 360,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3531,
            "text": "They say, 'If what you say is true, when will the final triumph come?'",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 417,
            "ruku": 360,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3532,
            "text": "Say, 'On the day of the final triumph, the faith of the disbelievers will be of no avail to them, nor will they be given any respite'.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 417,
            "ruku": 360,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3533,
            "text": "Turn away from them and wait. They are, also, waiting.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 417,
            "ruku": 360,
            "hizbQuarter": 166,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 33,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الأَحۡزَابِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Ahzaab",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Clans",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 3534,
            "text": "Prophet, have fear of God and do not yield to the infidels and hypocrites. God is All-knowing and All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 418,
            "ruku": 361,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3535,
            "text": "Follow what has been revealed to you from your Lord. God is All-aware of what you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 418,
            "ruku": 361,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3536,
            "text": "Trust in God and be sure that He is a Sufficient Guardian.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 418,
            "ruku": 361,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3537,
            "text": "God has not created two hearts inside any one human being. God does not consider your wives whom you renounce by zihar as your mothers nor those whom you adopt as your sons. These are only words of your mouth. God tells the Truth and shows the right path.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 418,
            "ruku": 361,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3538,
            "text": "Call them sons of their own fathers. It is more just in the eyes of God. If you do not know their fathers, they are your brothers and friends in religion. You will not be responsible for your mistakes, but you will be responsible for what you do intentionally. God is All-forgiving and All-merciful.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 418,
            "ruku": 361,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3539,
            "text": "The Prophet has more authority over the believers than themselves. His wives are their mothers. The relatives are closer to each other, according to the Book of God, than the believers and the emigrants. However, you may show kindness to your guardians. This also is written in the Book.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 418,
            "ruku": 361,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3540,
            "text": "We had a solemn covenant with you (Muhammad), and the Prophets: Noah, Abraham, Moses, and Jesus, the son of Mary.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 419,
            "ruku": 361,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3541,
            "text": "This was a firm agreement. God will ask the truthful ones about their truthfulness and prepare a painful torment for the disbelievers.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 419,
            "ruku": 361,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3542,
            "text": "Believers, recall God's favor to you when the army attacked you. We sent a wind and the armies, which you did not see, to support you. God sees all that you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 419,
            "ruku": 362,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3543,
            "text": "Eyes became dull and hearts almost reached the throat when they attacked you from above and below and you started to think of God with suspicion.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 419,
            "ruku": 362,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3544,
            "text": "There the believers were tested and tremendously shaken.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 419,
            "ruku": 362,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3545,
            "text": "It was there that the hypocrites and those whose hearts were sick, said, 'The promise of God and His Messenger has proved to be nothing but deceit'.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 419,
            "ruku": 362,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3546,
            "text": "It was there that a group of them said, 'People of Yathrib, turn back for there is no place for you to stay.' Another group, asking for the Prophet's permission, said, 'Our homes are defenseless.' In fact, they were not defenseless. They only wanted to run away.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 419,
            "ruku": 362,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3547,
            "text": "Had the army of the enemies invaded their homes and asked them to give-up their religion, they would have yielded to them without delay.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 419,
            "ruku": 362,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3548,
            "text": "They had certainly promised God that they would not turn away. To promise God is certainly a (great) responsibility.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 419,
            "ruku": 362,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3549,
            "text": "(Muhammad), tell them, 'Running away will never be of any benefit to you even if you run away from death or being killed. Still you would not be able to enjoy yourselves except for a short while.'",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 420,
            "ruku": 362,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3550,
            "text": "Say, 'Who can prevent God from punishing you or granting you mercy? They will not find anyone besides God as their guardian or helper.'",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 420,
            "ruku": 362,
            "hizbQuarter": 167,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3551,
            "text": "God certainly knows those among you who create obstacles (on the way that leads to God) and those who say to their brothers, 'Come quickly to us' and very rarely take part in the fighting.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 420,
            "ruku": 362,
            "hizbQuarter": 168,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3552,
            "text": "They are niggardly in spending for you. When fear comes, you can see them looking at you, their eyes rolling about like to faint because of the agony of death. When their fear subsides, they start to bite you with their sharp tongues. They are miserly in spending for a virtuous cause and have no faith. God has turned their deeds devoid of all virtue. This was not at all difficult for God.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 420,
            "ruku": 362,
            "hizbQuarter": 168,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3553,
            "text": "They think that the confederate tribes have not yet gone. If the confederate tribes were to attack them, they would have wished to be left alone among the bedouin Arabs where they would only follow the news about you. Even if they were with you, only a few of them would take part in the fight.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 420,
            "ruku": 362,
            "hizbQuarter": 168,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3554,
            "text": "The Messenger of God is certainly a good example for those of you who have hope in God and in the Day of Judgment and who remember God very often.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 420,
            "ruku": 363,
            "hizbQuarter": 168,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3555,
            "text": "On seeing the confederate tribes, the believers said, 'This is what God and His Messenger had promised us. The promise of God and His Messenger is true.' This only strengthens their faith and their desire of submission to the will of God.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 420,
            "ruku": 363,
            "hizbQuarter": 168,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3556,
            "text": "Among the believers there are people who are true in their promise to God. Some of them have already passed away and some of them are waiting. They never yield to any change.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 421,
            "ruku": 363,
            "hizbQuarter": 168,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3557,
            "text": "God will certainly reward the truthful ones for their truthfulness and punish or pardon the hypocrites as He wishes. God is All-forgiving and All-merciful.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 421,
            "ruku": 363,
            "hizbQuarter": 168,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3558,
            "text": "God repelled the unbelievers in their rage. They could not achieve anything good. God rendered sufficient support to the believers in fighting. God is All-powerful and Majestic.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 421,
            "ruku": 363,
            "hizbQuarter": 168,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3559,
            "text": "God brought down those among the People of the Book who had supported the confederate tribes from their castles and struck their hearts with terror. You did away with some of them and captured the others.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 421,
            "ruku": 363,
            "hizbQuarter": 168,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3560,
            "text": "God made you inherit their land, houses, property, and a land on which you had never walked. God has power over all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 421,
            "ruku": 363,
            "hizbQuarter": 168,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3561,
            "text": "Prophet, tell your wives, 'If you want the worldly life and its beauty, I shall allow you to enjoy it and set you free in an honorable manner,",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 421,
            "ruku": 364,
            "hizbQuarter": 168,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3562,
            "text": "but if you want the pleasure of God, His Messenger, and the life hereafter, know that God has prepared a great reward for the righteous ones among you.'",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 421,
            "ruku": 364,
            "hizbQuarter": 168,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3563,
            "text": "Wives of the Prophet, if anyone among you commits indecency, her torment will be double. This is not at all difficult for God.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 21,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 421,
            "ruku": 364,
            "hizbQuarter": 168,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3564,
            "text": "To whoever of you obeys God and His Messenger and acts righteously, We will give double reward and a honorable sustenance.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 422,
            "ruku": 364,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3565,
            "text": "Wives of the Prophet, you are not like other women. If you have fear of God, do not be tender in your speech lest people whose hearts are sick may lust after you.",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 422,
            "ruku": 364,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3566,
            "text": "Do not display yourselves after the manner of the (pre-Islamic) age of darkness. Be steadfast in the prayer, pay the religious tax, and obey God and His Messenger. People of the house, God wants to remove all kinds of uncleanliness from you and to purify you thoroughly.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 422,
            "ruku": 364,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3567,
            "text": "Wives of the Prophet, remember the revelations of God and Words of wisdom that are recited in your homes. God is Most Kind and All-aware.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 422,
            "ruku": 364,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3568,
            "text": "God has promised forgiveness and great rewards to the Muslim men and the Muslim women, the believing men and the believing women, the obedient men and the obedient women, the truthful men and the truthful women, the forbearing men and the forbearing women, the humble men and the humble women, the alms-giving men and the alms-giving women, the fasting men and the fasting women, the chaste men and the chaste women, and the men and women who remember God very often.",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 422,
            "ruku": 365,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3569,
            "text": "The believing men and women must not feel free to do something in their affairs other than that which has been already decided for them by God and His Messenger. One who disobeys God and His Messenger is in plain error.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 423,
            "ruku": 365,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3570,
            "text": "Say to the person to whom you and God have granted favor, 'Keep your wife and have fear of God. You hide within yourself what God wants to make public. You are afraid of people while it is God whom one should fear.' When Zayd set her free, We gave her in marriage to you so that the believers would not face difficulties about the wives of their adopted sons when they are divorced. God's decree has already been issued.",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 423,
            "ruku": 365,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3571,
            "text": "The Prophet cannot be blamed for carrying out the commands of God. It was the tradition of God with those who lived before. The command of God has already been decreed and ordained.",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 423,
            "ruku": 365,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3572,
            "text": "Those who preach the message of God and are humble before Him should not be afraid of anyone besides God. God is Sufficient in keeping the account.",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 423,
            "ruku": 365,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3573,
            "text": "Muhammad is not the father of any of your males. He is the Messenger of God and the last Prophet. God has the knowledge of all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 423,
            "ruku": 365,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3574,
            "text": "Believers, remember God very often",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 423,
            "ruku": 366,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3575,
            "text": "and glorify Him both in the mornings and in the evenings.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 423,
            "ruku": 366,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3576,
            "text": "It is He who forgives you and His angels pray for you so that He will take you out of darkness into light. God is All-merciful to the believers.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 423,
            "ruku": 366,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3577,
            "text": "On the day when they will be brought into the presence of their Lord, their greeting to each other will be, 'Peace be with you.' God has prepared an honorable reward for them.",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 424,
            "ruku": 366,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3578,
            "text": "Prophet, We have sent you as a witness, a bearer of glad news, a warner,",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 424,
            "ruku": 366,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3579,
            "text": "a preacher for God by His permission and as a shining torch.",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 424,
            "ruku": 366,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3580,
            "text": "Give glad news to the believers of their receiving great favor from God.",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 424,
            "ruku": 366,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3581,
            "text": "Do not yield to the disbelievers or the hypocrites. Ignore their annoying you. Trust in God. God is your all Sufficient Protector.",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 424,
            "ruku": 366,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3582,
            "text": "Believers, if you marry believing women and then divorce them before the consummation of the marriage, they do not have to observe the waiting period. Give them their provisions and set them free in an honorable manner.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 424,
            "ruku": 366,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3583,
            "text": "Prophet, We have made lawful for you your wives whom you have given their dowry, slave girls whom God has given to you as gifts, the daughters of your uncles and aunts, both paternal and maternal, who have migrated with you. The believing woman, who has offered herself to the Prophet and whom the Prophet may want to marry, will be specially for him, not for other believers. We knew what to make obligatory for them concerning their wives and slave girls so that you would face no hardship (because we have given distinction to you over the believers). God is All-forgiving and All-merciful.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 424,
            "ruku": 366,
            "hizbQuarter": 169,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3584,
            "text": "You may refuse whichever (of the woman who offer themselves to you) as you want and accept whichever of them you wish. There is no blame on you if you marry (one whom you had refused previously). This would be more delightful for them. They should not be grieved but should be happy with whatever you have given to every one of them. God knows what is in your hearts. God is All-knowing and All-forbearing.",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 425,
            "ruku": 366,
            "hizbQuarter": 170,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3585,
            "text": "Besides these, other women are not lawful for you to marry nor is it lawful for you to exchange your wives for the wives of others (except for the slave girls), even though they may seem attractive to you. God is watchful over all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 425,
            "ruku": 366,
            "hizbQuarter": 170,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3586,
            "text": "Believers, do not enter the houses of the Prophet for a meal without permission. if you are invited, you may enter, but be punctual (so that you will not be waiting while the meal is being prepared). When you have finished eating, leave his home. Do not sit around chatting among yourselves. This will annoy the Prophet but he will feel embarrassed to tell you. God does not feel embarrassed to tell you the truth. When you want to ask something from the wives of the Prophet, ask them from behind the curtain. This would be more proper for you and for them. You are not supposed to trouble the Prophet or to ever marry his wives after his death, for this would be a grave offense in the sight of God.",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 425,
            "ruku": 367,
            "hizbQuarter": 170,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3587,
            "text": "Whether you reveal something or hid it, God has the knowledge of all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 425,
            "ruku": 367,
            "hizbQuarter": 170,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3588,
            "text": "It will not be an offense for the wives of the Prophet (not to observe the modest dress) in the presence of their fathers, sons, brothers, sons of their brothers and sisters, their own women, and their slave-girls. They should have fear of God. God witness all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 426,
            "ruku": 367,
            "hizbQuarter": 170,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3589,
            "text": "God showers His blessings upon the Prophet and the angels seek forgiveness for him. Believers, pray for the Prophet and greet him with, 'Peace be with you.'",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 426,
            "ruku": 367,
            "hizbQuarter": 170,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3590,
            "text": "Those who annoy God and His Messenger will be condemned by God in this life and in the life to come. He has prepared for them a humiliating torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 426,
            "ruku": 367,
            "hizbQuarter": 170,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3591,
            "text": "Those who annoy the believing men and women without reason will bear the sin for a false accusation, a manifest offense.",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 426,
            "ruku": 367,
            "hizbQuarter": 170,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3592,
            "text": "Prophet, tell your wives, daughters, and the wives of the believers to cover their bosoms and breasts. This will make them distinguishable from others and protect them from being annoyed. God is All-forgiving and All-merciful.",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 426,
            "ruku": 368,
            "hizbQuarter": 170,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3593,
            "text": "If the hypocrites, those whose hearts are sick and those who encourage the spread of evil in the city, will not desist, We shall arouse you against them and they will only be allowed to be your neighbors for a short while.",
            "numberInSurah": 60,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 426,
            "ruku": 368,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3594,
            "text": "They will be condemned wherever they are and will be sized and done away with for good.",
            "numberInSurah": 61,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 426,
            "ruku": 368,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3595,
            "text": "This was the tradition of God with those who lived before. There will never be any change in the tradition of God.",
            "numberInSurah": 62,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 426,
            "ruku": 368,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3596,
            "text": "(Muhammad), people ask you about the Day of Judgment. Say, 'Only God has knowledge about it. Perhaps the Hour of Doom will soon come to pass.'",
            "numberInSurah": 63,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 427,
            "ruku": 368,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3597,
            "text": "God has condemned the unbelievers and prepared for them a burning torment",
            "numberInSurah": 64,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 427,
            "ruku": 368,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3598,
            "text": "wherein they will live forever without being able to find any guardian or helper.",
            "numberInSurah": 65,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 427,
            "ruku": 368,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3599,
            "text": "On the day when their faces will be turned from side to side on the fire, they will say, 'Would that we had obeyed God and the Messenger!'",
            "numberInSurah": 66,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 427,
            "ruku": 368,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3600,
            "text": "They will say, 'Lord, we obeyed our chiefs and elders and they caused us to go astray.",
            "numberInSurah": 67,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 427,
            "ruku": 368,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3601,
            "text": "Lord, make them to suffer double torment and subject them to the greatest condemnation.'",
            "numberInSurah": 68,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 427,
            "ruku": 368,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3602,
            "text": "Believers, do not be like those who annoyed Moses. God proved him to be innocent of what they had said about him. Moses was a honorable person in the sight of God.",
            "numberInSurah": 69,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 427,
            "ruku": 369,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3603,
            "text": "Believers, have fear of God and speak righteous words.",
            "numberInSurah": 70,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 427,
            "ruku": 369,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3604,
            "text": "God will reform your deeds and forgive your sins. One who obeys God and His Messenger will certainly achieve a great success.",
            "numberInSurah": 71,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 427,
            "ruku": 369,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3605,
            "text": "We offered Our Trust (Our deputation) to the heavens, to the earth, and to the mountains, but they could not bear this burden and were afraid to accept it. Mankind was able to accept this offer but he was unjust to himself and ignorant of the significance of this Trust.",
            "numberInSurah": 72,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 427,
            "ruku": 369,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3606,
            "text": "(As a result of this) God will punish the hypocrites and the pagans, but He will accept the repentance of the believers. God is All-forgiving and All-merciful.",
            "numberInSurah": 73,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 427,
            "ruku": 369,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 34,
        "name": "سُورَةُ سَبَإٍ",
        "englishName": "Saba",
        "englishNameTranslation": "Sheba",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 3607,
            "text": "It is only God who deserves all praise. To Him belongs all that is in the heavens and the earth and it is only He who deserves to be praised in the life to come. He is All-wise and All-aware.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 428,
            "ruku": 370,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3608,
            "text": "He knows all that enters the earth, all that comes out of it, all that descends from the sky and all that ascends to it. He is All-merciful and All-forgiving.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 428,
            "ruku": 370,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3609,
            "text": "The disbelievers have said, 'There will be no Hour of Doom.' Say, 'By my Lord, it certainly will come. My Lord knows the unseen. Not even an atom's weight in the heavens or the earth remains hidden from Him. Nothing exists greater or smaller than this without its record in the illustrious Book.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 428,
            "ruku": 370,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3610,
            "text": "God will certainly reward the righteously striving believers. These are the ones who will receive forgiveness and honorable sustenance.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 428,
            "ruku": 370,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3611,
            "text": "However, those who try to challenge Our revelations will face the most painful torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 428,
            "ruku": 370,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3612,
            "text": "Those who have been given knowledge will see that whatever has been revealed to you from your Lord is the truth and that it guides to the straight path of the Majestic and Praiseworthy One.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 428,
            "ruku": 370,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3613,
            "text": "The unbelievers have said, 'Should we tell you about a man who says that you will be brought back to life again after your having been completely disintegrated?",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 428,
            "ruku": 370,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3614,
            "text": "Has he invented this falsehood against God or is he possessed by jinn?' However, those who do not have any faith in the life to come will suffer torment for their serious error.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 429,
            "ruku": 370,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3615,
            "text": "Have they not seen the heavens and the earth in front and behind them. Had We wanted, We could have caused the earth to swallow them up or made a part of the sky fall upon them. In this there is evidence (of the truth) for every repenting person.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 429,
            "ruku": 370,
            "hizbQuarter": 171,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3616,
            "text": "We granted David a favor by commanding the mountains and birds to sing Our praise along with him and softened iron for him",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 429,
            "ruku": 371,
            "hizbQuarter": 172,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3617,
            "text": "so that he could make coats of mail and properly measure their rings. We told him and his people to act righteously. We are Well-Aware of what you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 429,
            "ruku": 371,
            "hizbQuarter": 172,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3618,
            "text": "(We made subservient to) Solomon the wind that travelled a month's journey in the morning and a month's journey in the evening. We made a stream of brass flow for him and some of the jinn worked for him by his Lord's command. We would make whichever of them (jinn) who turned away from Our command to suffer a burning torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 429,
            "ruku": 371,
            "hizbQuarter": 172,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3619,
            "text": "They would make for him anything that he wanted like fortresses, statues, large basins like reservoirs, and huge immovable cooking pots. It was said, 'Family of David, worship and act gratefully. Only few of my servants are grateful.'",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 429,
            "ruku": 371,
            "hizbQuarter": 172,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3620,
            "text": "When We decreed that Solomon should die, no one knew of his death except for a creeping creature of the earth who ate-up his staff. When he fell down, the jinn realized that if they had known about the unseen, they would not have remained in such a humiliating torment for so long.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 429,
            "ruku": 371,
            "hizbQuarter": 172,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3621,
            "text": "There was evidence (of the truth) for the people of Sheba in their homeland. (We gave them) two gardens, one on the left and one on the right and (told them), 'Consume the sustenance which your Lord has given to you and give Him thanks. You have a blessed land and an All-forgiving Lord'.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 430,
            "ruku": 371,
            "hizbQuarter": 172,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3622,
            "text": "They ignored (the evidence) and We sent to them a flood, arising from a broken dam. Nothing was left in their gardens but bitter fruits, some tamarisk and a few lotus trees.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 430,
            "ruku": 371,
            "hizbQuarter": 172,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3623,
            "text": "This was how We recompensed them for their ungratefulness and thus do We recompense the ungrateful ones.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 430,
            "ruku": 371,
            "hizbQuarter": 172,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3624,
            "text": "We established between them and the town that We had blessed, other towns nearby, and thus made it easier to travel. We told them, 'Travel there safely day and night'.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 430,
            "ruku": 371,
            "hizbQuarter": 172,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3625,
            "text": "They said, 'Lord, make the distances of our journeys longer.' They did injustice to themselves and We turned their existence into ancient tales by making them disintegrate totally. In this there is evidence (of the truth) for every forbearing and grateful person.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 430,
            "ruku": 371,
            "hizbQuarter": 172,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3626,
            "text": "Iblis (satan) made his judgment about them to come true. They all followed them except a believing group among them.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 430,
            "ruku": 371,
            "hizbQuarter": 172,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3627,
            "text": "He did not have any authority over them except to the extent that would allow Us to know who had faith in the life to come and who had doubts about it. Your Lord is a Guard over all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 430,
            "ruku": 371,
            "hizbQuarter": 172,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3628,
            "text": "Say, (Muhammad), 'Ask help from those whom you worship besides God. They do not possess an atom's weight in the heavens and the earth, have no share therein, nor will any of their idols be able to support them.'",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 430,
            "ruku": 372,
            "hizbQuarter": 172,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3629,
            "text": "No intercession with Him will be of any benefit except that of those whom He has granted permission. The angels cannot intercede. They are always submissive to their Lord. Fear vanishes from their heart when (they receive a message from their Lord). They ask each other, 'What did your Lord say?' Others answer, 'He spoke the Truth. He is the Most High and the Most Great.'",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 431,
            "ruku": 372,
            "hizbQuarter": 172,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3630,
            "text": "Say, 'Who provides you with sustenance from the heavens and the earth?' Say, 'It is God. Only one group among us has the true guidance. The others must certainly be in plain error'.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 431,
            "ruku": 372,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3631,
            "text": "Say, 'You will not be questioned about our sins nor shall we about your deeds'.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 431,
            "ruku": 372,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3632,
            "text": "Say, 'Our Lord will gather us all together and issue the true Judgment about our differences. He is the Best Judge and All-knowing.'",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 431,
            "ruku": 372,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3633,
            "text": "Say, 'Show me those whom you have related to God as His partner. He is too Exalted to have any partners. He is the Majestic and All-wise God.'",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 431,
            "ruku": 372,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3634,
            "text": "We have sent you as a bearer of glad news and a warner to the whole of mankind, but most people do not know.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 431,
            "ruku": 372,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3635,
            "text": "They say, 'When will the Day of Judgment be if what you say is true?'",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 431,
            "ruku": 372,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3636,
            "text": "Say, 'That day has already been decreed for you and you cannot change the time of its coming even by a single hour.'",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 431,
            "ruku": 372,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3637,
            "text": "The unbelievers have said, 'We shall never believe in this Quran nor in the Bible.' Would that you could see the unjust having been halted in the presence of their Lord, exchanging words among themselves. The oppressed among them will say to their oppressors, 'Had it not been for you, we would certainly have been believers.'",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 431,
            "ruku": 373,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3638,
            "text": "The suppressing ones will say to the oppressed ones, 'Did we prevent you from having guidance after it had come to you? In fact, you yourselves were criminals.'",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 432,
            "ruku": 373,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3639,
            "text": "The oppressed ones will say to them, 'It was you who planned night and day, ordering us to disbelieve God, and consider other things equal to Him.' They will hide their regret on seeing their torment. We shall chain the necks of the disbelievers. Can they be recompensed with other than what they deserved for their deeds?",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 432,
            "ruku": 373,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3640,
            "text": "Every time We sent a warner to a town, the rich ones therein said (to Our Messenger), 'We have no faith in what you have brought (to us).",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 432,
            "ruku": 373,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3641,
            "text": "We are the ones who have more wealth and children and we shall suffer no punishment'.",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 432,
            "ruku": 373,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3642,
            "text": "Say, 'My Lord increases and determines the sustenance of whomever He wants, but most people do not know.'",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 432,
            "ruku": 373,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3643,
            "text": "Your property and children cannot bring you closer to Us. Only those who believe and act righteously will have double reward for their deeds and will live in secure mansions.",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 432,
            "ruku": 374,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3644,
            "text": "Those who try to challenge Our revelations will be driven into torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 432,
            "ruku": 374,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3645,
            "text": "Say, 'It is my Lord who determines and increases the sustenance of whomever He wants. He will replace whatever you spend for His cause and He is the best Sustainer.'",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 432,
            "ruku": 374,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3646,
            "text": "On the day when God will rise them all together and ask the angels, 'Had these people been worshipping you?'",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 433,
            "ruku": 374,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3647,
            "text": "They will reply, 'All glory belongs to you. You are our guardian, not they. They had been worshipping the jinn and most of them had strong faith'.",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 433,
            "ruku": 374,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3648,
            "text": "None of them can help or harm each other on this day. We shall tell the unjust ones, 'Suffer the torment of the fire which you had called a lie.'",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 433,
            "ruku": 374,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3649,
            "text": "When Our illustrious revelations are recited to them, they say, 'This man only wants to prevent you from worshipping what your father's had worshipped.' They say 'This, (the Quran), is a mere invented lie.' The unbelievers have said about the truth when it came to them, 'This only is plain magic.'",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 433,
            "ruku": 374,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3650,
            "text": "We did not send to them, (the pagans), any books to study nor a Messenger to warn them, and those who lived before them had rejected the Truth.",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 433,
            "ruku": 374,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3651,
            "text": "These people have not one tenth of power or wealth that we had given to those who lived before them. They called Our Messengers liars. Thus, how terrible was My vengeance.",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 433,
            "ruku": 374,
            "hizbQuarter": 173,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3652,
            "text": "Say, 'I advise you to believe only in One God and worship Him individually or two people together.' Think carefully; your companion is not possessed by jinn. He is only warning you of the coming severe torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 433,
            "ruku": 375,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3653,
            "text": "Say, 'Whatever reward I ask you (for my preaching) will be for your own good. No one can reward me except God. He is the Witness over all things.'",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 433,
            "ruku": 375,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3654,
            "text": "Say, 'My Lord speaks the Truth. He has the knowledge of the unseen'.",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 433,
            "ruku": 375,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3655,
            "text": "Say, 'The truth has come. Falsehood has vanished and it will not come back again'.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 434,
            "ruku": 375,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3656,
            "text": "Say, 'If I go astray it will only be against my own soul, but if I receive guidance, it will be through my Lord's revelations.' He is All-hearing and Omnipresent.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 434,
            "ruku": 375,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3657,
            "text": "Would that you could see how the unbelievers will be terrified by death from which they cannot escape. They will be seized from a nearby place",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 434,
            "ruku": 375,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3658,
            "text": "and then they will say, 'We have faith in the Quran.' How can they have any faith when they are far away from this world.",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 434,
            "ruku": 375,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3659,
            "text": "They had rejected it in their worldly life and expressed disbelief at the unseen (Day of Judgment), considering it less than a remote possibility.",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 434,
            "ruku": 375,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3660,
            "text": "A gulf will exist between them and their desires on the Day of Judgment like the similar people who lived before. They, too, had lived in doubt and uncertainty (about the life hereafter).",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 434,
            "ruku": 375,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 35,
        "name": "سُورَةُ فَاطِرٍ",
        "englishName": "Faatir",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Originator",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 3661,
            "text": "All praise belongs to God, the creator of the heavens and the earth who has made the angels Messengers of two or three or four wings. He increases the creation as He wills. God has power over all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 434,
            "ruku": 376,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3662,
            "text": "No one can withhold whatever mercy God grants to the human being, nor can one release whatever He withholds. He is Majestic and All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 434,
            "ruku": 376,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3663,
            "text": "People, remember the bounty of God that He has granted to you. Is their any creator besides God who could provide you with sustenance from the heavens and the earth? He is the only God. Where then can you turn away?",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 434,
            "ruku": 376,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3664,
            "text": "If they reject you, other Messengers had certainly been rejected before you. All decisions are in the hands of God.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 435,
            "ruku": 376,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3665,
            "text": "People, the promise of God is true. Let not the worldly life deceive you. Let not the devil deceive you about God",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 435,
            "ruku": 376,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3666,
            "text": "Satan is your enemy. Thus, consider him as your enemy. His party only calls you to make you the dwellers of the burning fire.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 435,
            "ruku": 376,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3667,
            "text": "The unbelievers will suffer a severe torment, but the righteously striving believers will receive forgiveness and a great reward.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 435,
            "ruku": 376,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3668,
            "text": "Can one whose evil deeds seem attractive and virtuous to him (be compared to a truly righteous person)? God guides or causes to go astray whomever He wants. (Muhammad), do not be grieved because of their disbelief. God knows well whatever they do.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 435,
            "ruku": 377,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3669,
            "text": "It is God who sends the winds to raise the clouds. We then drive them unto barren areas and revive the dead earth. (The Resurrection) will also be executed in the same way.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 435,
            "ruku": 377,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3670,
            "text": "Whoever seeks honor should know that all honor belongs to God. Good words (worship) will be presented before Him and He will accept good deeds. Those who make evil plans will suffer intense torment. Their evil plans are doomed to destruction.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 435,
            "ruku": 377,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3671,
            "text": "God created you from clay which He then turned into a living germ and made you into pairs. No female conceives or delivers without His knowledge. No one grows older nor can anything be reduced from one's life without having its record in the Book. This is not at all difficult for God.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 435,
            "ruku": 377,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3672,
            "text": "The two oceans, one sweet and the other salty, are not alike. From each you can eat fresh meat and obtain ornaments to use. You see ships ploughing their way through them so that you may seek His favor and give Him thanks.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 436,
            "ruku": 377,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3673,
            "text": "He causes the night to enter into the day and the day to enter into the night. He has made subservient to Himself the sun and moon, each moving in an orbit for an appointed time. Such is God, your Lord, to whom belongs the kingdom. Those whom you worship besides Him do not posses even a single straw.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 436,
            "ruku": 377,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3674,
            "text": "They will not listen to your prayers if you pray to them. Even if they would listen, they would not be able to answer you. On the Day of Judgment they will reject your worship of them. Not even an expert reporter can tell you the truth in the way that God can do.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 436,
            "ruku": 377,
            "hizbQuarter": 174,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3675,
            "text": "People, you are always in need of God and God is Self-sufficient and Praiseworthy.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 436,
            "ruku": 378,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3676,
            "text": "He could replace you by a new creation if He decided to.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 436,
            "ruku": 378,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3677,
            "text": "This would not cost God dear at all.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 436,
            "ruku": 378,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3678,
            "text": "No one will bear the burden of another. Even if an overburdened soul should ask another to bear a part of his burden, no one, not even a relative, will do so. (Muhammad), you can only warn those who have fear of their Lord without seeing Him and who are steadfast in prayer. Whoever purifies himself, does so for his own good. To God do all things return.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 436,
            "ruku": 378,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3679,
            "text": "The blind and the seeing are not alike",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 437,
            "ruku": 378,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3680,
            "text": "nor are darkness and light",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 437,
            "ruku": 378,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3681,
            "text": "nor shade and heat",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 437,
            "ruku": 378,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3682,
            "text": "nor are the living and the dead. God makes to listen whomever He wants. (Muhammad), you cannot make people in the graves to listen.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 437,
            "ruku": 378,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3683,
            "text": "You are simply a warner.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 437,
            "ruku": 378,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3684,
            "text": "We have sent you in all truth as a bearer of glad news and a warner. No nation who lived before was left without a warner.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 437,
            "ruku": 378,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3685,
            "text": "If they reject you, (know that) others who lived before them had also rejected their Messengers, Messengers who had brought them miracles, scriptures, and the enlightening Book",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 437,
            "ruku": 378,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3686,
            "text": "so I seized the unbelievers and how terrible was their torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 437,
            "ruku": 378,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3687,
            "text": "Have you not seen that God has sent water down from the sky, has produced fruits of various colors, and has made streaks of various colors in the mountains, white, red, and intense black.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 437,
            "ruku": 379,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3688,
            "text": "He has also created people, beasts, and cattle of various colors. Only God's knowledgeable servants fear Him. God is Majestic and All-pardoning.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 437,
            "ruku": 379,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3689,
            "text": "Those who recite the Book of God, who are steadfast in prayer and, who spend out of what We have given them for the cause of God, both in public and in private, have hope in an indestructible bargain",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 437,
            "ruku": 379,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3690,
            "text": "and in receiving their reward from God and in further favors. He is All-forgiving and All-appreciating.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 437,
            "ruku": 379,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3691,
            "text": "Whatever We have revealed to you from the Book is all truth. It confirms what was revealed before. God sees His servants and is All-aware of them.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 438,
            "ruku": 379,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3692,
            "text": "We gave the Book as an inheritance to Our chosen servants, among whom some are unjust against their souls, some are moderate, and some are exceedingly virtuous by the permission of God. This is indeed a great favor.",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 438,
            "ruku": 379,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3693,
            "text": "They will enter the gardens of Eden wherein they will be decked with bracelets of gold, pearls, and silk garments.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 438,
            "ruku": 379,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3694,
            "text": "They will say, 'It is only God who deserves all praise. He has removed all of our suffering. Our Lord is certainly All-forgiving and All-appreciating.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 438,
            "ruku": 379,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3695,
            "text": "It is He who has granted us, through His favor, an everlasting dwelling wherein we shall experience no hardship nor any fatigue.'",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 438,
            "ruku": 379,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3696,
            "text": "The unbelievers will dwell in hell. It will not be decreed for them to die nor will their torment be relieved. Thus do We recompense the ungrateful ones.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 438,
            "ruku": 379,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3697,
            "text": "Therein they will cry-out, 'Lord, take us out of here. We shall act righteously and behave different to what we did before.' They will be told, 'Did We not allow you to live long enough for you to seek guidance? Did We not send a warner to you? Suffer (the torment). There is no one to help the unjust.'",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 438,
            "ruku": 379,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3698,
            "text": "God has knowledge of whatever is unseen in the heavens and the earth. He knows best what the hearts contain.",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 438,
            "ruku": 380,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3699,
            "text": "It is He who has made you each other's successors on earth. Whoever disbelieves, does so against his own self. The disbelief of the unbelievers will only increase the anger of their Lord and will only cause them greater loss.",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 439,
            "ruku": 380,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3700,
            "text": "(Muhammad), ask them, 'Think about the idols which you worship besides God. Show me what part of the earth they have created. Do they have any share in the heavens? Has God sent them a Book to confirm their authority? In fact, whatever the unjust promise each other is nothing but deceit.'",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 439,
            "ruku": 380,
            "hizbQuarter": 175,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3701,
            "text": "God prevents the heavens and the earth from falling apart. If they do fall apart, then, no one besides Him can restore them. He is All-forbearing and All-forgiving.",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 439,
            "ruku": 380,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3702,
            "text": "They solemnly swear that if a warner were to come to them, they would certainly have been better guided than any other nation. But when a warner came to them, it only increased their hatred",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 439,
            "ruku": 380,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3703,
            "text": "because of their pride in the land and their evil plots. Evil plots only affect the plotters. Do they expect anything other than (God's) tradition (torment) with those who lived before. You will never find any change in the tradition of God nor will you find any alteration in it.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 439,
            "ruku": 380,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3704,
            "text": "Have they not travelled (sufficiently) through the land to see how terrible was the end of the mightier people who lived before them. Nothing in the heavens or the earth can challenge God. God is All-knowing and All-powerful.",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 439,
            "ruku": 380,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3705,
            "text": "Were God to punish people for their deeds immediately, not one creature would have survived on earth. However, He has given them a respite for an appointed time and when their term comes to an end, let it be known that God watches over His servants.",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 440,
            "ruku": 380,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 36,
        "name": "سُورَةُ يسٓ",
        "englishName": "Yaseen",
        "englishNameTranslation": "Yaseen",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 3706,
            "text": "I swear by Ya Sin",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 440,
            "ruku": 381,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3707,
            "text": "and the Quran, the Book of wisdom,",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 440,
            "ruku": 381,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3708,
            "text": "that you (Muhammad) are a Messenger",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 440,
            "ruku": 381,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3709,
            "text": "and that you follow the right path.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 440,
            "ruku": 381,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3710,
            "text": "This is a revelation sent down from the Majestic and All-merciful",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 440,
            "ruku": 381,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3711,
            "text": "so that you may warn a people who are unaware because their fathers were not warned.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 440,
            "ruku": 381,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3712,
            "text": "(I swear) that most of them are doomed to be punished. They have no faith.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 440,
            "ruku": 381,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3713,
            "text": "We have enchained their necks up to their chins. Thus, they cannot bend their heads (to find their way).",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 440,
            "ruku": 381,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3714,
            "text": "We have set-up a barrier in front of and behind them and have made them blind. Thus, they cannot see.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 440,
            "ruku": 381,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3715,
            "text": "Whether you warn them or not, they will not believe.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 440,
            "ruku": 381,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3716,
            "text": "You should only warn those who follow the Quran and have fear of the Beneficent God without seeing Him. Give them the glad news of their receiving forgiveness and an honorable reward (from God).",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 440,
            "ruku": 381,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3717,
            "text": "It is We who bring the dead to life and records the deeds of human beings and their consequences (of continual effects). We keep everything recorded in an illustrious Book.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 440,
            "ruku": 381,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3718,
            "text": "Tell them the story of the people of the town to whom Messengers came.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3719,
            "text": "We sent them two Messengers whom they rejected. We supported them by sending a third one who told the people, 'We are the Messengers (of God) who have been sent to you'.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3720,
            "text": "The people said, 'You are mere mortals like us and the Beneficent God has sent nothing. You are only liars.'",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3721,
            "text": "They said, 'Our Lord knows that We are Messengers",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3722,
            "text": "who have been sent to you. Our only duty is to preach clearly to you'.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3723,
            "text": "The people said, 'We have ill omens about you. If you will not desist, we shall stone you and make you suffer a painful torment'.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3724,
            "text": "The Messengers said, 'This ill omen lies within yourselves. Will you then take heed? In fact, you are a transgressing people.'",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3725,
            "text": "A man came running from the farthest part of the city saying, 'My people, follow the Messengers.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3726,
            "text": "Follow those who do not ask you for any reward and who are rightly guided.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3727,
            "text": "'Why should I not worship God who has created me? To him you will all return.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3728,
            "text": "Should I worship other gods besides Him? If the Beneficent God was to afflict me with hardship, the intercession of the idols can be of no benefit to me nor could it rescue me from hardship.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3729,
            "text": "(Had I worshipped things besides God, I would have been in manifest error).",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3730,
            "text": "Messengers, listen to me. I believe in your Lord.'",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3731,
            "text": "(Having been murdered by the disbelievers) he was told to enter paradise",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3732,
            "text": "(wherein he said), 'Would that people knew how my Lord has granted me forgiveness and honor'.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 22,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 441,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 176,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3733,
            "text": "We did not send an army against his people from the heaven after his death nor did We need to send one.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 442,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3734,
            "text": "It was only a single blast which made them extinct.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 442,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3735,
            "text": "Woe to human beings! Whenever a Messenger came to them, they mocked him.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 442,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3736,
            "text": "Have they not seen how many generations, living before them, had We destroyed and they cannot ever come back to them?",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 442,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3737,
            "text": "They will all be brought into Our presence together.",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 442,
            "ruku": 382,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3738,
            "text": "Evidence (of the truth) for them is how We revived the dead earth",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 442,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3739,
            "text": "and produced therein grains from which they eat and established therein gardens of palms trees and vineyards and have made streams flow therein",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 442,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3740,
            "text": "so that they may consume the fruits and whatever their hands prepare. Will they not then be grateful?",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 442,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3741,
            "text": "All glory belongs to the One Who has created pairs out of what grow from the earth, out of their soul and out of that which they do not know.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 442,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3742,
            "text": "Of the signs for them is how We separated the day from the night and thus they remained in darkness;",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 442,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3743,
            "text": "how the sun moves in its orbit and this is the decree of the Majestic and All-knowing God;",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 442,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3744,
            "text": "how We ordained the moon to pass through certain phases until it seems eventually to be like a bent twig;",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 442,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3745,
            "text": "how the sun is not supposed to catch-up with the moon, nor is the night to precede the day. All of them are to float in a certain orbit;",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 442,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3746,
            "text": "how We carried them and their offspring inside the laden Ark",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 443,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3747,
            "text": "and created for them similar things to ride.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 443,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3748,
            "text": "Had We wanted, We could have drowned them and nothing would have been able to help or rescue them",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 443,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3749,
            "text": "except Our mercy which could enable them to enjoy themselves for an appointed time.",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 443,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3750,
            "text": "Whenever they are told to guard themselves against sin and the forth coming torment so that perhaps they could receive mercy",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 443,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3751,
            "text": "and whenever a revelation out of their Lord's revelations comes to them, they ignore it.",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 443,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3752,
            "text": "When they are told to spend for the cause of God out of what He has provided for them for their sustenance, the disbelievers say to the believers, 'Should we feed those whom God has decided to feed? You are in plain error.'",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 443,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3753,
            "text": "The unbelievers say, 'When will the Day of Judgment come if what you say is at all true?'",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 443,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3754,
            "text": "They will not have to wait long. When the Day of Judgment comes, it will only take a single blast of sound to strike them while they are quarrelling with one another.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 443,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3755,
            "text": "Then they will not be able to make a will or return to their families.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 443,
            "ruku": 383,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3756,
            "text": "When the trumpet is sounded, they will be driven out of their grave into the presence of their Lord.",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 443,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3757,
            "text": "They will say, 'Woe to us! Who has raised us up from our graves? This is what the Beneficent God has promised. The Messengers have also spoke the truth'.",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 443,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3758,
            "text": "Only after a single blast of sound, they will all be brought into Our presence.",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 443,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3759,
            "text": "No soul will be in the least bit wronged on that Day and no one will receive any recompense other than what he deserves for his deeds.",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 443,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3760,
            "text": "The dwellers of Paradise on that day will enjoy themselves.",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3761,
            "text": "They and their spouses will recline on couches in the shade therein.",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3762,
            "text": "They will have fruits and whatever they desire.",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3763,
            "text": "'Peace be with you,' will be a greeting for them from the Merciful Lord.",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3764,
            "text": "(The Lord will command), 'Criminals, stand away from the others on this day.'",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 177,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3765,
            "text": "Children of Adam, did We not command you not to worship satan. He was your sworn enemy.",
            "numberInSurah": 60,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3766,
            "text": "Did We not command you to worship Me and tell you that this is the straight path?'",
            "numberInSurah": 61,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3767,
            "text": "Satan misled a great multitude of you. Did you not have any understanding?",
            "numberInSurah": 62,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3768,
            "text": "This is hell with which you were threatened.",
            "numberInSurah": 63,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3769,
            "text": "Suffer therein on this day for your disbelief.",
            "numberInSurah": 64,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3770,
            "text": "We shall seal your mouths on that Day, let your hands speak to us and your feet testify to what you had achieved.",
            "numberInSurah": 65,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3771,
            "text": "We could have blinded them had We wanted. Then they would have raced along to cross the Bridge but how could they have seen (their way)?",
            "numberInSurah": 66,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3772,
            "text": "We could have turned them into other creatures on the spot had We wanted and they would not have been able to precede or turn back.",
            "numberInSurah": 67,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 384,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3773,
            "text": "The physical growth of those whom We grant a long life will be reversed. Will you then not understand?",
            "numberInSurah": 68,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3774,
            "text": "We did not teach him (Muhammad) poetry, nor was he supposed to be a poet. It is only the word (of God) and the illustrious Quran",
            "numberInSurah": 69,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3775,
            "text": "by which he may warn those who are living and may let the words of God come true against the unbelievers.",
            "numberInSurah": 70,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 444,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3776,
            "text": "Have they not seen what We have created from the labor of Our own hands? We have given them cattle.",
            "numberInSurah": 71,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 445,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3777,
            "text": "We have made the cattle subservient to them so they ride and consume them.",
            "numberInSurah": 72,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 445,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3778,
            "text": "From cattle they get milk and other benefits. Will they not then give thanks?",
            "numberInSurah": 73,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 445,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3779,
            "text": "They chose idols besides God in the hope of receiving help from them, but they will not be able to help them.",
            "numberInSurah": 74,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 445,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3780,
            "text": "Instead, the disbelievers will be brought into the presence of God as the soldiers of the idols.",
            "numberInSurah": 75,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 445,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3781,
            "text": "Muhammad, let not their words annoy you. We certainly know whatever they conceal or reveal.",
            "numberInSurah": 76,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 445,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3782,
            "text": "Has the human being not considered that We have created him from a drop of fluid. He is openly quarrelsome.",
            "numberInSurah": 77,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 445,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3783,
            "text": "He questions Our Resurrection of him, but has forgotten his own creation. He has said, 'Who will give life to the bones which have become ashes?'",
            "numberInSurah": 78,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 445,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3784,
            "text": "(Muhammad), tell him, 'He who gave them life in the first place will bring them back to life again. He has the best knowledge of all creatures.",
            "numberInSurah": 79,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 445,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3785,
            "text": "He has created fire for you out of the green tree from which you can kindle other fires.",
            "numberInSurah": 80,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 445,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3786,
            "text": "Is the One who has created the heavens and the earth not able to create another creature like the human being? He certainly has the power to do so. He is the Supreme Creator and is All-knowing.",
            "numberInSurah": 81,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 445,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3787,
            "text": "Whenever He decides to create something He has only to say, 'Exist,' and it comes into existence.",
            "numberInSurah": 82,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 445,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3788,
            "text": "All glory belongs to the One in whose hands is the control of all things. To Him you will all return.",
            "numberInSurah": 83,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 5,
            "page": 445,
            "ruku": 385,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 37,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الصَّافَّاتِ",
        "englishName": "As-Saaffaat",
        "englishNameTranslation": "Those drawn up in Ranks",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 3789,
            "text": "I swear by (the angels) who stand in ranks,",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3790,
            "text": "by those who drive away the devil (to protect Our revelation),",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3791,
            "text": "and those who recite Our revelations,",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3792,
            "text": "that your Lord is the only Lord.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3793,
            "text": "He is the Lord of the heavens and the earth and all that is between them, the Lord of the Eastern regions.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3794,
            "text": "We have decked the lower heavens with stars",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3795,
            "text": "to protect them from the rebellious satan.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3796,
            "text": "The devils cannot hear those high above. They would be struck from all sides",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3797,
            "text": "and driven away to suffer the necessary torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3798,
            "text": "Some of them who stealthily steal words from the heavens are pursued by a glistening flame.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3799,
            "text": "(Muhammad), ask them, 'Have they (people) been created stronger than what We have created?' We have created them from moist clay.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3800,
            "text": "(Muhammad), you will be surprised that they still mock (God's revelations).",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3801,
            "text": "They pay no attention when they are reminded",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3802,
            "text": "and when they see a miracle, they mock",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3803,
            "text": "it and say, 'It is only plain magic'.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3804,
            "text": "They say, 'Shall we be brought to life again after we die and turn into dust and bones?",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3805,
            "text": "Will our forefathers also be brought to life again?'",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3806,
            "text": "Say, 'You will certainly be brought back to life in disgrace'.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3807,
            "text": "The Day of Judgment will come within a single roar and they will remain gazing at it.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3808,
            "text": "They will say, 'Woe to us!' (They will be told), 'This is the day of receiving recompense'.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3809,
            "text": "This is the Day of Judgment in which you disbelieved.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 386,
            "hizbQuarter": 178,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3810,
            "text": "(God will command the angels), 'Gather together the unjust, their spouses, and what they had worshipped",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3811,
            "text": "besides God, and show them the way of hell.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3812,
            "text": "Stop them. They must be questioned.'",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 446,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3813,
            "text": "They will be asked, 'Why do you not help each other?'",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3814,
            "text": "In fact, on that day they will be submissive.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3815,
            "text": "They will turn to each other saying,",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3816,
            "text": "'It was you who tried to mislead us from righteousness'.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3817,
            "text": "Others will respond, 'It was you who did not want to have any faith.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3818,
            "text": "We had no authority over you, in fact, you were a rebellious people.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3819,
            "text": "Thus, the words of Our Lord about us have come true and now we are suffering the torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3820,
            "text": "We mislead you and we ourselves had also gone astray.'",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3821,
            "text": "On that day they will all share the torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3822,
            "text": "This is how We deal with the criminals.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3823,
            "text": "They were the ones, who on being told, 'God is only One,' become puffed-up with pride",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3824,
            "text": "and said, 'Should we give up our idols for the sake of an insane poet'.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3825,
            "text": "In fact, he had brought them the truth and had acknowledged the Messengers (who were sent before him).",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3826,
            "text": "(They will be told), 'You will certainly suffer the painful torment",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3827,
            "text": "and will be recompensed only for what you deserve.",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3828,
            "text": "But the sincere servants of God",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3829,
            "text": "will have their determined sustenance",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3830,
            "text": "and fruits while they are honored.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3831,
            "text": "(They will live) in the bountiful gardens,",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3832,
            "text": "on couches facing each other.",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3833,
            "text": "They will be served with a cup full of crystal clear wine,",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3834,
            "text": "delicious to those who drink it",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3835,
            "text": "but not harmful or intoxicating.",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3836,
            "text": "They will have with them loving wives with big black and white eyes",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3837,
            "text": "who are as chaste as sheltered eggs.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3838,
            "text": "They will turn to each other and ask questions.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3839,
            "text": "One of them will say, 'I had a companion who asked me,",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 447,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3840,
            "text": "'Do you believe in the Day of Judgment?",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3841,
            "text": "Shall we be recompensed for our deeds after we die and become bones and dust?",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3842,
            "text": "Do you want to see him?' '",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3843,
            "text": "He will look down and see him in hell.",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3844,
            "text": "He will say to his friend in hell, 'By God, you almost destroyed me.",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3845,
            "text": "Had I not the guidance of my Lord, I would certainly have been brought into torment'.",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3846,
            "text": "He will ask his companion, 'Did you not say that there would only be one death",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3847,
            "text": "and that we would not be punished?'",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3848,
            "text": "This is certainly the greatest triumph",
            "numberInSurah": 60,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3849,
            "text": "for which one must strive hard.",
            "numberInSurah": 61,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3850,
            "text": "Is this not a better reward than the tree of Zaqqum",
            "numberInSurah": 62,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3851,
            "text": "which We have made as a torment for the unjust?",
            "numberInSurah": 63,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3852,
            "text": "(Zaqqum) is a tree which grows from the deepest part of hell,",
            "numberInSurah": 64,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3853,
            "text": "and its fruits are like the heads of devils.",
            "numberInSurah": 65,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3854,
            "text": "The dwellers of hell will eat that fruit and fill-up their bellies.",
            "numberInSurah": 66,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3855,
            "text": "Then they will have on top of it a mixture of boiling water.",
            "numberInSurah": 67,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3856,
            "text": "They can only return to hell.",
            "numberInSurah": 68,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3857,
            "text": "They found their father going astray",
            "numberInSurah": 69,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3858,
            "text": "and rushed to follow them.",
            "numberInSurah": 70,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3859,
            "text": "Most of the ancient people had also gone astray.",
            "numberInSurah": 71,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3860,
            "text": "We had certainly sent warners to them.",
            "numberInSurah": 72,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3861,
            "text": "See how terrible was the end of those who were warned.",
            "numberInSurah": 73,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3862,
            "text": "Only Our sincere servants were saved.",
            "numberInSurah": 74,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 387,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3863,
            "text": "Noah called for help. How blessed was the answer which he received.",
            "numberInSurah": 75,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3864,
            "text": "We rescued him and his people from the greatest affliction",
            "numberInSurah": 76,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 448,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3865,
            "text": "and We made his offspring the only survivors.",
            "numberInSurah": 77,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3866,
            "text": "We perpetuated his praise in later generations.",
            "numberInSurah": 78,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3867,
            "text": "Peace be with Noah among all men in the worlds.",
            "numberInSurah": 79,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3868,
            "text": "Thus do We reward the righteous ones.",
            "numberInSurah": 80,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3869,
            "text": "He was one of Our believing servants.",
            "numberInSurah": 81,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3870,
            "text": "We drowned all the others (besides Noah and his people).",
            "numberInSurah": 82,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 179,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3871,
            "text": "Abraham was one of his followers.",
            "numberInSurah": 83,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3872,
            "text": "He turned to his Lord with a sound heart",
            "numberInSurah": 84,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3873,
            "text": "and asked his father and his people, 'What is that you worship?",
            "numberInSurah": 85,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3874,
            "text": "Do you want to worship false idols as your lords besides God?",
            "numberInSurah": 86,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3875,
            "text": "What do you think about the Lord of the Universe?'",
            "numberInSurah": 87,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3876,
            "text": "The people invited him to attend their feast). Then he looked at the stars",
            "numberInSurah": 88,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3877,
            "text": "and said, 'I am sick!'",
            "numberInSurah": 89,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3878,
            "text": "All the people turned away from him",
            "numberInSurah": 90,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3879,
            "text": "and he turned to their idols and asked them, 'Do you eat?",
            "numberInSurah": 91,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3880,
            "text": "Why do you not speak?'",
            "numberInSurah": 92,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3881,
            "text": "He struck them with his right hand.",
            "numberInSurah": 93,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3882,
            "text": "Thereupon the people came running to him.",
            "numberInSurah": 94,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3883,
            "text": "He said, 'How can you worship what you yourselves have carved",
            "numberInSurah": 95,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3884,
            "text": "even though God created both you and that which you have made?'",
            "numberInSurah": 96,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3885,
            "text": "They said, 'Let us build a fire and throw him into the flames'.",
            "numberInSurah": 97,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3886,
            "text": "They plotted against him, but We brought humiliation upon them.",
            "numberInSurah": 98,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3887,
            "text": "(Abraham) said, 'I will go to my Lord who will guide me'.",
            "numberInSurah": 99,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3888,
            "text": "Abraham prayed, 'Lord, grant me a righteous son'.",
            "numberInSurah": 100,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3889,
            "text": "We gave him the glad news of the birth of a forbearing son.",
            "numberInSurah": 101,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3890,
            "text": "When his son was old enough to work with him, he said, 'My son, I have had a dream that I must sacrifice you. What do you think of this?' He replied, 'Father, fulfill whatever you are commanded to do and you will find me patient, by the will of God'.",
            "numberInSurah": 102,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 449,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3891,
            "text": "When they both agreed and Abraham had lain down his son on the side of his face (for slaughtering),",
            "numberInSurah": 103,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3892,
            "text": "We called to him, 'Abraham,",
            "numberInSurah": 104,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3893,
            "text": "you have fulfilled what you were commanded to do in your dream.' Thus do We reward the righteous ones.",
            "numberInSurah": 105,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3894,
            "text": "It was certainly an open trial.",
            "numberInSurah": 106,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3895,
            "text": "We ransomed his son with a great sacrifice",
            "numberInSurah": 107,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3896,
            "text": "and perpetuated his praise in later generations.",
            "numberInSurah": 108,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3897,
            "text": "Peace be with Abraham.",
            "numberInSurah": 109,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3898,
            "text": "Thus, do We reward the righteous ones.",
            "numberInSurah": 110,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3899,
            "text": "He was one of Our believing servants.",
            "numberInSurah": 111,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3900,
            "text": "We gave him the glad news of the birth of Isaac, one of the righteous Prophets.",
            "numberInSurah": 112,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3901,
            "text": "We had blessed him and Isaac. Some of their offspring were righteous and others were openly unjust to themselves.",
            "numberInSurah": 113,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 388,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3902,
            "text": "We certainly bestowed Our favor upon Moses and Aaron",
            "numberInSurah": 114,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3903,
            "text": "and saved them and their people from great distress.",
            "numberInSurah": 115,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3904,
            "text": "We helped them and they were victorious.",
            "numberInSurah": 116,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3905,
            "text": "We gave them the enlightening Book,",
            "numberInSurah": 117,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3906,
            "text": "guided them to the right path,",
            "numberInSurah": 118,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3907,
            "text": "and perpetuated their praise in later generations.",
            "numberInSurah": 119,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3908,
            "text": "Peace be with Moses and Aaron.",
            "numberInSurah": 120,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3909,
            "text": "Thus do We reward the righteous ones.",
            "numberInSurah": 121,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3910,
            "text": "They were two of Our believing servants.",
            "numberInSurah": 122,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3911,
            "text": "Elias was certainly a Messenger.",
            "numberInSurah": 123,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3912,
            "text": "He told his people, 'Why do you not have fear of God?",
            "numberInSurah": 124,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3913,
            "text": "Do you worship Ba`al and abandon the Best Creator.",
            "numberInSurah": 125,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3914,
            "text": "who is your Lord and the Lord of your forefathers?'",
            "numberInSurah": 126,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 450,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3915,
            "text": "They called him a liar. Thus, all of them will suffer torment",
            "numberInSurah": 127,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3916,
            "text": "except the sincere servants of God.",
            "numberInSurah": 128,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3917,
            "text": "We perpetuated his praise in the later generations.",
            "numberInSurah": 129,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3918,
            "text": "Peace be with the followers of Elias.",
            "numberInSurah": 130,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3919,
            "text": "In this way do We reward the righteous ones.",
            "numberInSurah": 131,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3920,
            "text": "He was one of Our believing servants.",
            "numberInSurah": 132,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3921,
            "text": "Lot was certainly a Messenger.",
            "numberInSurah": 133,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3922,
            "text": "We rescued him and his whole family,",
            "numberInSurah": 134,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3923,
            "text": "except for an old woman who remained behind.",
            "numberInSurah": 135,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3924,
            "text": "Then We totally destroyed the others.",
            "numberInSurah": 136,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3925,
            "text": "You pass by (their ruined town) in the morning and at night.",
            "numberInSurah": 137,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3926,
            "text": "Will you then not understand?",
            "numberInSurah": 138,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 389,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3927,
            "text": "Jonah was certainly a Messenger.",
            "numberInSurah": 139,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3928,
            "text": "He abandoned his people",
            "numberInSurah": 140,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3929,
            "text": "and sailed away in a laden ship, wherein people cast lots. Because he lost, he was thrown into the water.",
            "numberInSurah": 141,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3930,
            "text": "The fish swallowed him up and he deserved (all this).",
            "numberInSurah": 142,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3931,
            "text": "Had he not glorified God,",
            "numberInSurah": 143,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3932,
            "text": "he would certainly have remained inside the fish until the Day of Resurrection.",
            "numberInSurah": 144,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 180,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3933,
            "text": "We cast him out of the fish unto dry land and he was sick.",
            "numberInSurah": 145,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3934,
            "text": "We made a plant of gourd grow up for him.",
            "numberInSurah": 146,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3935,
            "text": "We sent him to a hundred thousand or more people.",
            "numberInSurah": 147,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3936,
            "text": "They believed in him so We granted them enjoyment for an appointed time.",
            "numberInSurah": 148,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3937,
            "text": "(Muhammad), ask them, 'Do daughters belong to your Lord and sons to them?",
            "numberInSurah": 149,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3938,
            "text": "Have We created the angels as females before their very eyes?",
            "numberInSurah": 150,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3939,
            "text": "It is only because of their false invention that they say,",
            "numberInSurah": 151,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3940,
            "text": "'God has begotten a son.' They are certainly liars.",
            "numberInSurah": 152,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3941,
            "text": "Has He chosen daughters in preference to sons?",
            "numberInSurah": 153,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 451,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3942,
            "text": "Woe to you! How terrible is your Judgment.",
            "numberInSurah": 154,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3943,
            "text": "Do you not understand?",
            "numberInSurah": 155,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3944,
            "text": "Do you have clear authority?",
            "numberInSurah": 156,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3945,
            "text": "Bring your book if what you say is true.",
            "numberInSurah": 157,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3946,
            "text": "They have said that there is a relationship between Him and the jinn. The jinn certainly know that they will all be brought to suffer torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 158,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3947,
            "text": "God is too glorious to be described as they describe Him",
            "numberInSurah": 159,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3948,
            "text": "except the servants of God, sincere and devoted.",
            "numberInSurah": 160,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3949,
            "text": "You and whatever you worship",
            "numberInSurah": 161,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3950,
            "text": "cannot mislead anyone",
            "numberInSurah": 162,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3951,
            "text": "except those who are doomed to enter hell.",
            "numberInSurah": 163,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3952,
            "text": "The angels say, 'Each of us has an appointed place.",
            "numberInSurah": 164,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3953,
            "text": "We stand in ranks (for prayer)",
            "numberInSurah": 165,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3954,
            "text": "and we glorify God'.",
            "numberInSurah": 166,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3955,
            "text": "Even though they (unbelievers) say,",
            "numberInSurah": 167,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3956,
            "text": "'Had we received guidance from the people living before us,",
            "numberInSurah": 168,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3957,
            "text": "we would have certainly been sincere servants of God'.",
            "numberInSurah": 169,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3958,
            "text": "They have rejected the Quran. They will soon know the consequences (of their disbelief).",
            "numberInSurah": 170,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3959,
            "text": "We decreed that Our Messenger servants",
            "numberInSurah": 171,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3960,
            "text": "will certainly be victorious",
            "numberInSurah": 172,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3961,
            "text": "and that Our army will be triumphant.",
            "numberInSurah": 173,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3962,
            "text": "(Muhammad), stay away from them for a while",
            "numberInSurah": 174,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3963,
            "text": "and watch them. They, too, will watch.",
            "numberInSurah": 175,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3964,
            "text": "Do they want to suffer Our torment immediately?",
            "numberInSurah": 176,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3965,
            "text": "When it descends into their courtyard, it will be terrible for those who have already been warned.",
            "numberInSurah": 177,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3966,
            "text": "Stay away from them for a while",
            "numberInSurah": 178,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3967,
            "text": "and watch. They, too, will watch.",
            "numberInSurah": 179,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3968,
            "text": "Your Lord, the Lord of Honor, is too exalted to be considered as they describe Him.",
            "numberInSurah": 180,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3969,
            "text": "Peace be with the Messengers (of God).",
            "numberInSurah": 181,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3970,
            "text": "It is only God, the Lord of the Universe, who deserves all praise.",
            "numberInSurah": 182,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 452,
            "ruku": 390,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 38,
        "name": "سُورَةُ صٓ",
        "englishName": "Saad",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The letter Saad",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 3971,
            "text": "Sad. I swear by the Quran, which is full of reminders of God, (that you are a Messenger).",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 391,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3972,
            "text": "In fact, the unbelievers are the ones who are boastful and quarrelsome.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 391,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3973,
            "text": "How many ancient generations did We destroy? (On facing Our torment) they cried out for help, but it was too late for them to escape.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 391,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3974,
            "text": "It seems strange to the pagans that a man from their own people should come to them as a Prophet. The unbelievers have said, 'He is only a lying magician'.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 391,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3975,
            "text": "They say, 'Has he condemned all other gods but One? This is certainly strange'.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 391,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3976,
            "text": "A group of the pagans walked out of a meeting with the Prophet and told the others, 'Let us walk away. Be steadfast in the worship of your gods. This man wants to dominate you.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 391,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3977,
            "text": "We have heard nothing like this in the latest religion. This is only his own false invention.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 391,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3978,
            "text": "Can it be that he alone has received the Quran?' In fact, they have doubts about My Quran and this is because they have not yet faced (My) torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 391,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3979,
            "text": "Do they possess the treasures of the mercy of your, (Muhammad's), Lord, the Majestic and Munificent God?",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 391,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3980,
            "text": "Do they own the heavens and the earth and all that is between them? Let them try on their own to block (the ways of heavens so that Our revelations cannot come to you).",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 391,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3981,
            "text": "They are only a small band among the defeated confederate tribes.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 391,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3982,
            "text": "The people of Noah, Ad and the dominating Pharaoh had rejected Our revelations.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 391,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3983,
            "text": "So also did the people of Thamud, Lot, and the dwellers of the Forest.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 391,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3984,
            "text": "Each of them who rejected the Messenger become subject to Our punishment.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 391,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3985,
            "text": "They had only to wait for the single inevitable blast.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 392,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3986,
            "text": "They scornfully said, 'Lord, show us the record of our deeds before the day when everyone must present the account of their deeds.'.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 453,
            "ruku": 392,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3987,
            "text": "(Muhammad), bear patiently what they say and recall Our servant, David, who had strong hands and who was most repentant.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 454,
            "ruku": 392,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3988,
            "text": "We made the mountains join him in glorifying Us in the evening and in the morning.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 454,
            "ruku": 392,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3989,
            "text": "We made the birds assemble around him in flocks.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 454,
            "ruku": 392,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3990,
            "text": "We strengthened his kingdom, giving him wisdom and the power of sound Judgment.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 454,
            "ruku": 392,
            "hizbQuarter": 181,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3991,
            "text": "Have you heard the news of the disputing parties who climbed the walls of the prayer room",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 454,
            "ruku": 392,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3992,
            "text": "and entered where David was (praying). He was frightened, so they said, 'Do not be afraid. We are only two disputing parties of which one of us has transgressed against the other. Judge between us with truth and justice and guide us to the right path'.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 454,
            "ruku": 392,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3993,
            "text": "One of them said, 'This is my brother who has ninety-nine ewes when I have only one. He has demanded me to place that one in his custody; he had the stronger argument'.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 454,
            "ruku": 392,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3994,
            "text": "David said, 'He has certainly been unjust in demanding your ewe from you. Most partners transgress against each other except for the righteously striving believers who are very few.' David realized that it was a test from Us so he asked forgiveness from his Lord and knelt down before him in repentance.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 454,
            "ruku": 392,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": {
              "id": 11,
              "recommended": true,
              "obligatory": false
            }
          },
          {
            "number": 3995,
            "text": "We forgave him for this. In Our eyes he certainly has a good position and the best share (of the world to come).",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 454,
            "ruku": 392,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3996,
            "text": "We told him. 'David, We have appointed you as Our deputy on earth so judge among the people with truth. Do not follow (worldly) desires lest you go astray from the way of God. Those who go astray from the way of God will suffer severe torment for forgetting the Day of Reckoning.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 454,
            "ruku": 392,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3997,
            "text": "We have not created the heavens and the earth and all that is between them without purpose, even though this is the belief of the disbelievers. Woe to the disbelievers; they will suffer the torment of fire",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 393,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3998,
            "text": "Do We consider the righteously striving believers equal to the evil-doers in the land? Are the pious ones equal to those who openly commit sin?",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 393,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 3999,
            "text": "It is a blessed Book which We have revealed for you so that you will reflect upon its verses and so the people of understanding will take heed.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 393,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4000,
            "text": "We granted Solomon to David, a blessed servant of Ours and certainly the most repentant person.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 393,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4001,
            "text": "When the noble galloping horses were displayed to him one evening,",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 393,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4002,
            "text": "he said, 'My love of horses for the cause of God has made me continue watching them until sunset, thus making me miss my prayer'.",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 393,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4003,
            "text": "He said, 'Bring them back to me.' Then he started to rub their legs and necks.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 393,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4004,
            "text": "We tested Solomon by (causing death to his son) and leaving his body on Solomon's chair. Then he turned to Us in repentance,",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 393,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4005,
            "text": "saying, 'Lord, forgive me and grant me a kingdom that no one after me can have the like. You are All-munificent'.",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 393,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4006,
            "text": "We made the wind subservient to him, to blow gently wherever he desired at his command",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 393,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4007,
            "text": "and all the devils who built and dived for him.",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 393,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4008,
            "text": "The rest of the devils were bound in chains.",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 393,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4009,
            "text": "We told him, 'This is Our gift to you so give them away free or keep them as you like'.",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 393,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4010,
            "text": "In Our eyes he certainly has a high position and the best place to return.",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 393,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4011,
            "text": "(Muhammad), recall Our servant Job. When he prayed to his Lord saying, 'Satan has afflicted me with hardship and torment,'",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4012,
            "text": "(We answered his prayer, healed his sickness, and told him), 'Run on your feet. This is cool water (for you) to wash and drink'.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 455,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4013,
            "text": "We gave him back his family and doubled their number as a blessing from Us and as a reminder to the people of understanding.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4014,
            "text": "We told him, 'Take a handful of straw. Strike your wife with it to fulfill your oath.' We found him to be patient. What an excellent servant he was. He was certainly most repenting.",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4015,
            "text": "(Muhammad), recall Our servants Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, all of whom possessed virtuous hands and clear visions.",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4016,
            "text": "We gave them this pure distinction because of their continual remembrance of the Day of Judgment.",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4017,
            "text": "In Our eyes they were of the chosen, virtuous people.",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4018,
            "text": "Recall Ismael, Elisha, and Dhulkifl (Ezekiel) who were all virtuous people.",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4019,
            "text": "Such is their noble story. The pious ones will certainly have the best place to return.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4020,
            "text": "They will enter gardens of Eden with their gates open for them.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4021,
            "text": "They will be resting therein and will be able to ask for many kinds of fruit and drink.",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 182,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4022,
            "text": "They will have bashful wives of equal age with them.",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4023,
            "text": "This is what they had been promised for the Day of Judgment.",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4024,
            "text": "Our provision (for you) will never be exhausted.",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4025,
            "text": "However, the rebellious ones will have the worst place to return.",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4026,
            "text": "They will suffer in hell. What a terrible dwelling!",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4027,
            "text": "(They will be told), 'This is your recompense.",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4028,
            "text": "Taste the scalding water, pus, and other putrid things'.",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4029,
            "text": "Their leaders will be told, 'This band will also be thrown headlong with you into hell.' Their leaders will exclaim, 'May condemnation fall upon them! Let them suffer the torment of fire'.",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4030,
            "text": "Their followers will say, 'In fact, it is you who deserve condemnation. It was you who led us to hell, a terrible dwelling'.",
            "numberInSurah": 60,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4031,
            "text": "They will continue saying, 'Lord, double the torment of fire for those who led us into this.",
            "numberInSurah": 61,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 456,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4032,
            "text": "But why is it that we cannot see men whom we had considered as wicked",
            "numberInSurah": 62,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4033,
            "text": "and whom we mocked? Have they been rescued or can our eyes not find them?'",
            "numberInSurah": 63,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4034,
            "text": "Such disputes will certainly take place among the dwellers of hell fire.",
            "numberInSurah": 64,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 394,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4035,
            "text": "(Muhammad) say, 'I am only a warner. The only Lord is God, the Almighty.",
            "numberInSurah": 65,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4036,
            "text": "He is the Lord of the heavens, the earth, and all that is between them, the Majestic and All-forgiving'.",
            "numberInSurah": 66,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4037,
            "text": "Say, 'It (facts about the supremacy of God) is the greatest message,",
            "numberInSurah": 67,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4038,
            "text": "but you have turned away from it.",
            "numberInSurah": 68,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4039,
            "text": "I have no knowledge of the dispute among the angels (concerning their attitude towards Adam).",
            "numberInSurah": 69,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4040,
            "text": "I have only received revelation to give you plain warning.",
            "numberInSurah": 70,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4041,
            "text": "When your Lord told the angels, 'I will create a mortal out of clay,",
            "numberInSurah": 71,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4042,
            "text": "and when I give it proper shape and blow My spirit into it, bow down in prostration to him,'",
            "numberInSurah": 72,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4043,
            "text": "all the angel then prostrated themselves",
            "numberInSurah": 73,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4044,
            "text": "except Iblis who puffed himself up with pride and became a disbeliever.",
            "numberInSurah": 74,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4045,
            "text": "The Lord said, 'Iblis, what prevented you from prostrating before what I have created with My own hands? Was it because of your pride or are you truly exalted?'",
            "numberInSurah": 75,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4046,
            "text": "He said, 'I am better than him. You have created me from fire and him out of clay'.",
            "numberInSurah": 76,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4047,
            "text": "The Lord said, 'Get out of here. You deserve to be stoned!",
            "numberInSurah": 77,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4048,
            "text": "My condemnation will be with you until the Day of Judgment!'",
            "numberInSurah": 78,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4049,
            "text": "He said, 'Lord, grant me respite until the Day of Resurrection'.",
            "numberInSurah": 79,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4050,
            "text": "The Lord said, 'You will only be given a respite",
            "numberInSurah": 80,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4051,
            "text": "for an appointed time'.",
            "numberInSurah": 81,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4052,
            "text": "He said, 'By Your Glory, I shall seduce all of them (children of Adam).",
            "numberInSurah": 82,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4053,
            "text": "except Your sincere servants among them'.",
            "numberInSurah": 83,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 457,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4054,
            "text": "The Lord said, 'I swear by the Truth - and I speak the Truth -",
            "numberInSurah": 84,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 458,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4055,
            "text": "that I shall certainly fill hell with you and your followers all together'.",
            "numberInSurah": 85,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 458,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4056,
            "text": "(Muhammad), say, 'I do not ask any reward for my preaching to you for I am not a pretender.",
            "numberInSurah": 86,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 458,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4057,
            "text": "It, (the Quran), is nothing but a reminder to you from the Lord of the Universe.",
            "numberInSurah": 87,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 458,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4058,
            "text": "You will certainly know its truthfulness after a certain time.",
            "numberInSurah": 88,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 458,
            "ruku": 395,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 39,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الزُّمَرِ",
        "englishName": "Az-Zumar",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Groups",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4059,
            "text": "This Book is a revelation from God, the Majestic and All-Wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 458,
            "ruku": 396,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4060,
            "text": "We have revealed the Book to you in all truth. Worship God and be devoted to His religion.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 458,
            "ruku": 396,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4061,
            "text": "The religion of God is certainly pure. Concerning those whom they consider as their guardians besides God, they say, 'We only worship them so that they may make our positions nearer to God.' God will certainly issue His decree about their differences. God does not guide the liars and the disbelievers.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 458,
            "ruku": 396,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4062,
            "text": "Had God wanted to have a son, He would have chosen one from His creatures according to His will. God is too Exalted to have a son. He is One and Almighty.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 458,
            "ruku": 396,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4063,
            "text": "He has created the heavens and the earth for a genuine purpose. He covers the night with the day and the day with the night and has subdued the sun and the moon, each of which floats for an appointed time. God is certainly Majestic and All-Forgiving.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 458,
            "ruku": 396,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4064,
            "text": "He has created you from a single soul. Out of this He created your spouse. He sent you eight pairs of cattle. He creates you for a second time in the wombs of your mothers behind three curtains of darkness. He is your Lord to whom belongs the Kingdom. He is the only Lord. Where then will you turn away?",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 459,
            "ruku": 396,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4065,
            "text": "If you disbelieve, know that God is certainly independent of you. He does not want disbelief for His servants. If you give thanks, He will accept it from you. No one will be responsible for the sins of others. To your Lord you will all return and He will tell you about what you have done. He knows best what the hearts contain.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 459,
            "ruku": 396,
            "hizbQuarter": 183,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4066,
            "text": "When the human being is afflicted with hardship, he starts to pray to his Lord and turns to Him in repentance. When God grants him a favor, he forgets the hardship about which he had prayed to God and starts to consider equal to God things that lead him astray from His path. (Muhammad), tell him, 'You can only enjoy in your disbelief for a short time. You will certainly be a dweller of hell fire'.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 459,
            "ruku": 396,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4067,
            "text": "Can this one be considered equal to one who worships God during the night, prostrating and standing, who has fear of the Day of Judgment, and who has hope in the mercy of his Lord? Say, 'Are those who know equal to those who do not know? Only the people of reason take heed'.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 459,
            "ruku": 396,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4068,
            "text": "Say to My believing servants, 'Have fear of your Lord. Those who act righteously in this life will receive good reward. The land of God is vast. God will recompense the deeds of those who have exercised patience, without keeping an account'.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 459,
            "ruku": 397,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4069,
            "text": "Say, 'I am commanded to worship God and be devoted to His religion",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 460,
            "ruku": 397,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4070,
            "text": "and I am commanded to be the first Muslim'.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 460,
            "ruku": 397,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4071,
            "text": "Say, 'I am afraid that for disobeying my Lord I shall suffer the torment of the great day'.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 460,
            "ruku": 397,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4072,
            "text": "Say, 'I worship God alone and devote myself to His religion.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 460,
            "ruku": 397,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4073,
            "text": "Worship besides Him whatever you want. The greatest losers are those whose souls and family members will be lost on the Day of Judgment for this is certainly a great loss'.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 460,
            "ruku": 397,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4074,
            "text": "Above and below them their will be shadows of fire. This is how God frightens His servants. My servants have fear of Me.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 460,
            "ruku": 397,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4075,
            "text": "Those who have avoided worshipping idols and have turned in repentance to God will receive the glad news.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 460,
            "ruku": 397,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4076,
            "text": "(Muhammad), give the glad news to those of Our servants who listen to the words and only follow the best ones. Tell them that they are those whom God has guided. They are the people of understanding.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 460,
            "ruku": 397,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4077,
            "text": "How can you rescue the one who is destined to suffer the torment?",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 460,
            "ruku": 397,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4078,
            "text": "Those who have fear of their Lord will have lofty mansions built upon mansions beneath which streams flow. It is the promise of God. God does not disregard His promise.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 460,
            "ruku": 397,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4079,
            "text": "Have you not seen that God has sent down water from the sky and made it flow as springs out of the earth? He makes crops of different colors grow with this water and flourish, which then turn yellow and wither away. In this there is a reminder for the people of understanding.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 460,
            "ruku": 397,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4080,
            "text": "One whose chest (heart and mind) is left open for Islam (submission to His will) shall receive light from God. Woe to those whose hearts have become like stone against the remembrance of God. They are clearly in error.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 461,
            "ruku": 398,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4081,
            "text": "God has revealed the best reading material in the form of a Book with similar passages which refer to each other and make the skins of those who fear their Lord shiver. Then their skins and hearts incline to the remembrance of God. This is the guidance of God. He guides whomever He wants. No one can guide those whom God has caused to go astray.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 461,
            "ruku": 398,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4082,
            "text": "Is there anyone who is afraid of the torment of the Day of Judgment when the unjust will be told, 'Suffer the result of your deeds?'",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 461,
            "ruku": 398,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4083,
            "text": "Those who lived before them had also rejected Our revelations. Thus, the torment struck them and they did not even realize where it came from.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 461,
            "ruku": 398,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4084,
            "text": "God made them suffer humiliation in this life. Would that they knew that the torment for them in the next life will be even greater.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 461,
            "ruku": 398,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4085,
            "text": "We have given all kinds of examples for the human being in this Quran so that perhaps he may take heed.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 461,
            "ruku": 398,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4086,
            "text": "This Quran is a flawless reading text in the Arabic language. Perhaps they will have fear of God.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 461,
            "ruku": 398,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4087,
            "text": "God tells a parable in which there is a company of quarrelsome people and only one of them is well disciplined. Can they be considered as equal? It is only God who deserves all praise. In fact, most of them do not know.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 461,
            "ruku": 398,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4088,
            "text": "(Muhammad), you will die and all of them will also die.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 461,
            "ruku": 398,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4089,
            "text": "Then, on the Day of Judgment, all of you will present your disputes before your Lord.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 23,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 461,
            "ruku": 398,
            "hizbQuarter": 184,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4090,
            "text": "Who is more unjust then one who invents falsehood against God and rejects the truth after it has come to them. Is not hell a dwelling for the disbelievers?",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 462,
            "ruku": 399,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4091,
            "text": "Those who have brought the truth and have acknowledged it are those who have fear of God.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 462,
            "ruku": 399,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4092,
            "text": "They will receive whatever they want from their Lord. Thus is the reward of the righteous ones.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 462,
            "ruku": 399,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4093,
            "text": "God will certainly expiate their bad deeds and reward them much more for what they have done.",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 462,
            "ruku": 399,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4094,
            "text": "Is God not sufficient (support) for His servants? They frighten you with what they worship besides God. Who can guide one whom God has caused to go astray?",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 462,
            "ruku": 399,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4095,
            "text": "Who can mislead one whom God has guided? Is God not Majestic and Revengeful?",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 462,
            "ruku": 399,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4096,
            "text": "If you ask them, 'Who has created the heavens and the earth?' They will certainly say, 'God has created them.' Ask them, 'Do you think that you can rescue me from the punishment of God with which He may afflict me? Can you prevent His mercy if He wants to grant it to me?' Say, 'God is Sufficient (support) for me. In Him alone one must trust'.",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 462,
            "ruku": 399,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4097,
            "text": "Say, 'My people, act as you wish. I shall do as I like and you will soon know",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 462,
            "ruku": 399,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4098,
            "text": "who will face the humiliating torment and suffer everlasting retribution'.",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 462,
            "ruku": 399,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4099,
            "text": "(Muhammad), We have revealed the Book to you for mankind in all truth. Whoever seeks guidance does so for his own good. Whosoever goes astray goes against his own soul. You are not their representative.",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 463,
            "ruku": 399,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4100,
            "text": "God will receive their souls when they die. Their souls do not die when they are sleeping. During people's sleep He withholds those souls which He has decreed to die and releases the others for an appointed time. In this there is evidence (of the Truth) for the thoughtful people.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 463,
            "ruku": 400,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4101,
            "text": "Have they chosen intercessors besides God? Say, 'Would you choose them as your intercessors even though they do not possess anything and have no understanding?'",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 463,
            "ruku": 400,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4102,
            "text": "Say, 'Intercession belongs to God. To Him belongs the heavens and the earth and to Him you will all return.'",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 463,
            "ruku": 400,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4103,
            "text": "When one God is mentioned, the hearts of those who do not believe in the Day of Judgment begin to shrink, but when the idols are mentioned, they rejoice.",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 463,
            "ruku": 400,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4104,
            "text": "Say, 'Lord, the Creator of the heavens and the earth, knower of the seen and unseen, it is You who will issue Your decree about the differences of Your servants.'",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 463,
            "ruku": 400,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4105,
            "text": "Had the unjust possessed double the amount of the wealth of the whole earth, they would certainly have liked to offer it on the Day of Resurrection as redemption from the torment of Our scourge when God would make public what they had never expected.",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 463,
            "ruku": 400,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4106,
            "text": "Their bad deeds will become public and they will be surrounded by the torment which they had mocked during their worldly life.",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 464,
            "ruku": 400,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4107,
            "text": "When the human being is afflicted with hardship, he cries out to us for help. When We grant him a favor, he says, 'I knew that I deserved it.' In fact, it is only a test for him, but most people do not know this.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 464,
            "ruku": 400,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4108,
            "text": "People who lived before them had also said, 'Our wealth has been earned by our own merits.' What they had earned was of no benefit to them",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 464,
            "ruku": 400,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4109,
            "text": "They were afflicted by the terrible result of whatever they gained. Besides this affliction, the unjust among them will also suffer the consequence of their deeds. They will not be able to challenge God.",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 464,
            "ruku": 400,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4110,
            "text": "Did they not know that God determines and increases the sustenance of whomever He wants. In this there is evidence (of the truth) for the believing people.",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 464,
            "ruku": 400,
            "hizbQuarter": 185,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4111,
            "text": "(Muhammad), tell my servants who have committed injustice to themselves, 'Do not despair of the mercy of God. God certainly forgives all sins. He is All-forgiving and All-merciful.'",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 464,
            "ruku": 401,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4112,
            "text": "Turn in repentance to your Lord and submit to His will before you are afflicted with the torment after which you can receive no help.",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 464,
            "ruku": 401,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4113,
            "text": "Follow the best of what is revealed to you from your Lord before the torment suddenly approaches you and you will not realize how it came about.",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 464,
            "ruku": 401,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4114,
            "text": "Turn to God in repentance before a soul says, 'Woe to me because of my failure to fulfill my duties to God. Woe to me for mocking God's guidance!'",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 464,
            "ruku": 401,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4115,
            "text": "Or before the soul says, 'Had God guided me, I could have been a pious man'.",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 465,
            "ruku": 401,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4116,
            "text": "Or, on seeing the torment, it would say, 'Would I have the opportunity, this time I would certainly become a pious person'.",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 465,
            "ruku": 401,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4117,
            "text": "God will reply to the soul, 'My revelations had certainly come to you but you rejected them. You were puffed-up with pride and you became an unbeliever'.",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 465,
            "ruku": 401,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4118,
            "text": "On the Day of Judgment you will see the faces of those who had invented falsehood against God blackened. Is not hell the dwelling of the arrogant ones?",
            "numberInSurah": 60,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 465,
            "ruku": 401,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4119,
            "text": "God will save the pious ones because of their virtuous deeds. No hardship will touch them nor will they be grieved.",
            "numberInSurah": 61,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 465,
            "ruku": 401,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4120,
            "text": "God is the Creator and Guardian of all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 62,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 465,
            "ruku": 401,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4121,
            "text": "In His hands are the keys of the treasuries of the heavens and the earth. Those who reject God's revelations will be lost.",
            "numberInSurah": 63,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 465,
            "ruku": 401,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4122,
            "text": "(Muhammad), say, 'Ignorant ones, do you command me to worship things other than God",
            "numberInSurah": 64,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 465,
            "ruku": 402,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4123,
            "text": "even though God has said, 'It has been revealed to you and to those who lived before you that if you consider other things equal to God, your deeds will be made devoid of all virtue and you will certainly be lost?'",
            "numberInSurah": 65,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 465,
            "ruku": 402,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4124,
            "text": "(Muhammad), You must worship God alone and give Him thanks.",
            "numberInSurah": 66,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 465,
            "ruku": 402,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4125,
            "text": "They have not paid due respect to God. The whole earth will be gripped in His hands on the Day of Judgment and the heavens will be just like a scroll in His right hand. God is too Glorious and High to be considered equal to their idols.",
            "numberInSurah": 67,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 465,
            "ruku": 402,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4126,
            "text": "Everyone in the heavens and the earth will faint in terror except for those whom God will save when the trumpet is sounded. They will all stand up and wait when the trumpet sounds for the second time.",
            "numberInSurah": 68,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 466,
            "ruku": 402,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4127,
            "text": "The earth will become bright from the light of your Lord. The Book of Records will be presented and the Prophets and witness will be summoned. All will be judged with justice and no wrong will be done to anyone.",
            "numberInSurah": 69,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 466,
            "ruku": 402,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4128,
            "text": "Every soul will be recompensed for its deeds. God knows best whatever they have done.",
            "numberInSurah": 70,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 466,
            "ruku": 402,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4129,
            "text": "The disbelievers will be driven to hell in hordes. Its gates will be opened when they are brought nearby and the keepers will ask them, 'Did Messengers from your own people not come to you to recite your Lord's revelations and to warn you about this day?' They will reply, 'Yes, the Messengers did come to us, but the unbelievers were doomed to face the torment'.",
            "numberInSurah": 71,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 466,
            "ruku": 403,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4130,
            "text": "They will be told, 'Enter the gates of hell to live therein forever. What a terrible dwelling for the arrogant ones!'",
            "numberInSurah": 72,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 466,
            "ruku": 403,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4131,
            "text": "The pious ones will be led to Paradise in large groups. Its gates will be opened to them when they are brought nearby and its keepers will say, 'Welcome! Peace be with you. Enter the gates of Paradise to live therein forever'.",
            "numberInSurah": 73,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 466,
            "ruku": 403,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4132,
            "text": "They will say, 'It is only God who deserves all praise. He has made His promise come true and has given the earth as an inheritance to us. Now we live in the gardens as we wished. Blessed is the reward of those who labor.",
            "numberInSurah": 74,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 466,
            "ruku": 403,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4133,
            "text": "(Muhammad), on that day you will see the angels circling around the Throne, glorifying and praising their Lord. Judgment with justice will be decreed between the people of Paradise and hell and it will be said, 'It is only God, Lord of the Universe who deserves all praise.'",
            "numberInSurah": 75,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 467,
            "ruku": 403,
            "hizbQuarter": 186,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 40,
        "name": "سُورَةُ غَافِرٍ",
        "englishName": "Ghafir",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Forgiver",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4134,
            "text": "Ha. Mim.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 467,
            "ruku": 404,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4135,
            "text": "This Book is a revelation from God, the Majestic and All-knowing",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 467,
            "ruku": 404,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4136,
            "text": "who forgives sins, who accepts repentance, whose punishment is severe, and whose bounty is universal. He is the only Lord and to Him all things proceed.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 467,
            "ruku": 404,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4137,
            "text": "No one disputes the revelations of the Lord except the disbelievers. Let not their activities in the land deceive you.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 467,
            "ruku": 404,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4138,
            "text": "The people of Noah who lived before and the Confederate tribes who lived after them rejected Our revelations. Every nation schemed against its Messengers to seize them and disputed against them to defeat the truth. But torment struck them and how terrible was their retribution!",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 467,
            "ruku": 404,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4139,
            "text": "The word of your Lord that the disbelievers will be the dwellers of hell fire has already been decreed.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 467,
            "ruku": 404,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4140,
            "text": "The bearers of the Throne glorify their Lord with His praise. They believe in Him and ask Him to forgive the believers. They say, 'Our Lord, Your mercy and knowledge encompass all things. Forgive those who turn to You in repentance and follow Your path. Lord, save them from the torment of hell.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 467,
            "ruku": 404,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4141,
            "text": "Lord, admit them and their fathers, spouses, and offspring who have reformed themselves to the gardens of Eden which You have promised them. You are Majestic and All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 468,
            "ruku": 404,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4142,
            "text": "Lord, keep them away from evil deeds. Whomever You have saved from evil on the Day of Judgment has certainly been granted Your mercy and this is the greatest triumph.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 468,
            "ruku": 404,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4143,
            "text": "The disbelievers will be told, 'God's hatred towards you is much greater than your hatred of your own selves. You were called to the faith but you disbelieved'.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 468,
            "ruku": 405,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4144,
            "text": "They say, 'Lord, You have caused us to die twice and You have brought us back to life twice. We have confessed our sins, so is there any way out of this (hell)?'",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 468,
            "ruku": 405,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4145,
            "text": "They will be answered, 'Your suffering is only because you disbelieved when One God was mentioned. When other things were considered equal to Him, you believed in them. Judgment belongs to God, the Most High, the Most Great.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 468,
            "ruku": 405,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4146,
            "text": "It is He who has shown you the evidence of His existence and has sent you sustenance from the sky, yet only those who turn to God in repentance take heed.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 468,
            "ruku": 405,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4147,
            "text": "Worship God and be devoted to His religion even though the disbelievers dislike this.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 468,
            "ruku": 405,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4148,
            "text": "God is the promoter of His servants and the owner of the Throne. He sends His spirit by His command to whichever of His servants He wants to warn them of the Day of Judgment.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 468,
            "ruku": 405,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4149,
            "text": "Nothing will remain hidden from God concerning them on the day when they appear before God (from their graves) (It will be asked), 'To whom does the kingdom belong on this Day?' (It will be answered), 'The kingdom belongs to the Almighty One God'.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 468,
            "ruku": 405,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4150,
            "text": "Every soul will be recompensed for its deeds on this Day. There will be no injustice. Certainly God's reckoning is swift.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 469,
            "ruku": 405,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4151,
            "text": "(Muhammad), warn them of the approaching day when because of hardship and frustration their hearts will almost reach up to their throats. The unjust will have no friends nor any intercessor who will be heard.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 469,
            "ruku": 405,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4152,
            "text": "God knows the disloyalty of the eyes and what the hearts conceal.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 469,
            "ruku": 405,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4153,
            "text": "God judges with Truth but those whom they worship besides God can have no Judgment. God is certainly All-hearing and All-aware.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 469,
            "ruku": 405,
            "hizbQuarter": 187,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4154,
            "text": "Have they not travelled through the land to see the terrible end of those who lived before them. They had been mightier than them in power and in leaving their traces on earth. God punished them for their sins. They had no one to save them from God's torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 469,
            "ruku": 406,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4155,
            "text": "Messengers had come to them with illustrious miracles but they disbelieved and thus God struck them with His torment. He is Mighty and Severe in His retribution.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 469,
            "ruku": 406,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4156,
            "text": "We sent Moses with Our miracles and clear authority.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 469,
            "ruku": 406,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4157,
            "text": "to the Pharaoh, Haman, and Korah, who said, 'He is only a lying magician.'.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 469,
            "ruku": 406,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4158,
            "text": "When We sent him to them for a genuine purpose, they said, 'Kill the sons of those who have believed in him but keep their women alive.' The plots of the unbelievers can only result in failure.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 469,
            "ruku": 406,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4159,
            "text": "The Pharaoh said, 'Let me kill Moses and let him call for help from his Lord. I am afraid that he will change your religion or spread evil through the land.'.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 470,
            "ruku": 406,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4160,
            "text": "Moses said, 'I seek protection from your and my Lord against every arrogant person who has no faith in the Day of Judgment.'",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 470,
            "ruku": 406,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4161,
            "text": "A believing person from the people of the Pharaoh who concealed his faith said, 'Would you kill a man just because he says God is my Lord? He has brought you illustrious miracles from your Lord. If he speaks lies, it will only harm him, but if he speaks the Truth, some of his warnings may affect you. God does not guide a transgressing liar.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 470,
            "ruku": 407,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4162,
            "text": "My people, today you have the kingdom and the power on earth but who will help us against the wrath of God if it will befall us?' The Pharaoh said, 'I show you only what I think is proper and guide you only to the right direction'.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 470,
            "ruku": 407,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4163,
            "text": "The believing man said, 'I am afraid that you will face a (terrible) day like that of the groups:",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 470,
            "ruku": 407,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4164,
            "text": "people of Noah, Ad, Thamud, and those after them. God did not want injustice for His servants.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 470,
            "ruku": 407,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4165,
            "text": "My people, I am afraid for you on (the Day of Judgment), when people will cry for help.",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 470,
            "ruku": 407,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4166,
            "text": "On that day you will run away, but no one will be able to protect you from (God's Judgment). No one can guide one whom God has caused to go astray.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 470,
            "ruku": 407,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4167,
            "text": "Joseph came to you before with illustrious evidence but you still have doubts about what he brought. When he passed away, you said, 'God will never send any Messenger after him.' Thus does God causes to go astray the skeptical transgressing people,",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 471,
            "ruku": 407,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4168,
            "text": "those who dispute the revelations of God without having received clear authority. This act greatly angers God and the believers. Thus does God seal the hearts of every arrogant oppressor.'",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 471,
            "ruku": 407,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4169,
            "text": "Pharaoh said, 'Haman, build a tower of baked bricks for me so that I shall have access.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 471,
            "ruku": 407,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4170,
            "text": "to the heavens and be able to climb up to the Lord of Moses. I think that Moses is lying.' Thus, Pharaoh's evil deeds seemed attractive to him and prevented him from the right path. The Pharaoh's plots only led him to his own destructor.",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 471,
            "ruku": 407,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4171,
            "text": "The believing man said, 'My people, follow me and I shall show you the right guidance.",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 471,
            "ruku": 408,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4172,
            "text": "My people, this worldly life is only the means (to an end), but the life hereafter will be the everlasting abode.",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 471,
            "ruku": 408,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4173,
            "text": "Whoever commits evil deeds will be recompensed to the same degree. The righteously striving believer, male or female, will enter Paradise wherein they will receive their sustenance without any account being kept.",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 471,
            "ruku": 408,
            "hizbQuarter": 188,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4174,
            "text": "My people, 'How strange is it that I invite you to salvation when you invite me to the fire.",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 472,
            "ruku": 408,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4175,
            "text": "You call me to disbelieve in God and to believe other things equal to Him about which I have no knowledge. I call you to the Majestic and All-forgiving One.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 472,
            "ruku": 408,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4176,
            "text": "The idols to which you invite me certainly have no claim to be deities in this world or in the life to come. Our return is to God and the transgressors will be the dwellers of hell fire.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 472,
            "ruku": 408,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4177,
            "text": "You will soon recall what I have told you. I entrust God with my affairs. God is Well Aware of His servants.'",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 472,
            "ruku": 408,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4178,
            "text": "God protected him against their evil plans and the people of the Pharaoh were struck by the most horrible torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 472,
            "ruku": 408,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4179,
            "text": "They will be exposed to the fire in the mornings and the evenings and on the Day of Judgment, they will be told, 'People of the Pharaoh, suffer the most severe torment.'",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 472,
            "ruku": 408,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4180,
            "text": "During a dispute in the fire, the suppressed ones will say to those who had dominated them, 'We were your followers. Can you now relieve us of our suffering in the fire?'",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 472,
            "ruku": 408,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4181,
            "text": "The ones who had dominated them will say, 'All of us are now in hell. God has already issued His Judgment of His servants (and no one can change this).'",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 472,
            "ruku": 408,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4182,
            "text": "The dwellers of hell fire will ask its keepers, 'Pray to your Lord to relieve us from the torment at least for one day'.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 472,
            "ruku": 408,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4183,
            "text": "The keepers will ask them, 'Did your Messengers not come to you with illustrious evidence (of the Truth)? They will reply, 'Yes, they did.' The keepers will then say, 'You may pray but the prayer of the disbelievers will not be answered'.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 473,
            "ruku": 408,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4184,
            "text": "We shall help Our Messengers and the believers, in this life and on the day when witness will come forward.",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 473,
            "ruku": 409,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4185,
            "text": "The excuses of the unjust will be of no benefit to them on that day. They will be condemned to live in a most terrible abode.",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 473,
            "ruku": 409,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4186,
            "text": "To Moses We had given guidance and to the children of Israel We had given the Book",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 473,
            "ruku": 409,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4187,
            "text": "as their inheritance and as a guide and a reminder to the people of understanding.",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 473,
            "ruku": 409,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4188,
            "text": "(Muhammad), exercise patience. The promise of God is true. Seek forgiveness for your sins and glorify your Lord with His praise in the evenings and in the early mornings.",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 473,
            "ruku": 409,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4189,
            "text": "Those who dispute the revelations of God without having received any authority do so because of their arrogance, but their arrogance cannot bring them any success. Seek protection from God for He is All-hearing and All-aware.",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 473,
            "ruku": 409,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4190,
            "text": "The creation of the heavens and the earth is certainly greater than the creation of mankind, but most people do not know.",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 473,
            "ruku": 409,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4191,
            "text": "Just as the blind and the seeing are not equal, so are the righteously striving believers and the sinners are not equal. How little to this you pay attention.",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 473,
            "ruku": 409,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4192,
            "text": "The Hour of Doom will inevitably come, but most people do not have faith.",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 474,
            "ruku": 409,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4193,
            "text": "Your Lord has said, 'Pray to Me for I shall answer you prayers. Those who are too proud to worship Me will soon go to hell in disgrace'.",
            "numberInSurah": 60,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 474,
            "ruku": 409,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4194,
            "text": "It is God Who has made the night for you to rest and the day for you to see. God is Benevolent to the human being, but most people do not give Him due thanks.",
            "numberInSurah": 61,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 474,
            "ruku": 410,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4195,
            "text": "It is God, your Lord, Who has created all things. He is the only Lord. Why then do you turn away from His worship to the worshipping of idols?",
            "numberInSurah": 62,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 474,
            "ruku": 410,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4196,
            "text": "Thus are indeed those who have rejected the revelations of God.",
            "numberInSurah": 63,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 474,
            "ruku": 410,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4197,
            "text": "It is God who has created the earth as a place for you to live and the sky as a dome above you. He has shaped you in the best form and has provided you with pure sustenance. This is God, your Lord. Blessed is God, the Lord of the Universe.",
            "numberInSurah": 64,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 474,
            "ruku": 410,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4198,
            "text": "He is the Everlasting and the only Lord. So worship Him and be devoted to His religion. It is only God, the Lord of the Universe who deserves all praise.",
            "numberInSurah": 65,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 474,
            "ruku": 410,
            "hizbQuarter": 189,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4199,
            "text": "(Muhammad), say, 'I have been forbidden to worship whatever you worship besides God after receiving clear evidence from my Lord. I have been commanded to submit myself to the will of the Lord of the Universe'.",
            "numberInSurah": 66,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 474,
            "ruku": 410,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4200,
            "text": "It is He Who created you from clay, turning it into a living germ, then into a clot of blood, and then brings you forth as a child. He then made you grow into manhood and become old. He causes some of you to live for the appointed time and some of you to die before so that perhaps you may have understanding.",
            "numberInSurah": 67,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 475,
            "ruku": 410,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4201,
            "text": "It is He Who gives life and causes things to die. When He decides to do something, He only says, 'Exist,' and it comes into existence.",
            "numberInSurah": 68,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 475,
            "ruku": 410,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4202,
            "text": "Have you not seen how those who dispute the revelations of God, turn away from Truth to falsehood?",
            "numberInSurah": 69,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 475,
            "ruku": 411,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4203,
            "text": "Those who rejected the Book and the message which was given to Our Messenger will soon know (the consequences of their evil deeds).",
            "numberInSurah": 70,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 475,
            "ruku": 411,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4204,
            "text": "when fetters will be placed around their necks and chains will drag them",
            "numberInSurah": 71,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 475,
            "ruku": 411,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4205,
            "text": "into boiling water and then they will be burned in the fire.",
            "numberInSurah": 72,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 475,
            "ruku": 411,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4206,
            "text": "Then they will be asked, 'Where are the idols which you worshipped besides God?'",
            "numberInSurah": 73,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 475,
            "ruku": 411,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4207,
            "text": "They will reply, 'They have abandoned us. In fact, we had worshipped nothing' Thus does God cause the disbelievers to go astray.",
            "numberInSurah": 74,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 475,
            "ruku": 411,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4208,
            "text": "They will be told, 'This (torment) is the result of your unreasonable happiness on the earth and of your propagation of falsehood.",
            "numberInSurah": 75,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 475,
            "ruku": 411,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4209,
            "text": "Enter the gates of hell to live therein forever. How terrible is the dwelling of the arrogant ones.",
            "numberInSurah": 76,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 475,
            "ruku": 411,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4210,
            "text": "(Muhammad), exercise patience. The promise of God is true. Whether We let you witness the suffering with which they were threatened or because of your death (you do not see them suffering,), We shall still punish them when they return to Us (on the Day of Judgment).",
            "numberInSurah": 77,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 475,
            "ruku": 411,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4211,
            "text": "We have told you the stories of some of Our Messengers whom We had sent before you and We have not told you the stories of some others. A Messenger is not supposed to show a miracle without the permission of God. When God's decree of punishment comes to pass, He will judge truthfully and the supporters of the falsehood will perish when God's decree of punishemnt comes to pass.",
            "numberInSurah": 78,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 476,
            "ruku": 411,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4212,
            "text": "It is God Who has created cattle for you to ride and to consume as food.",
            "numberInSurah": 79,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 476,
            "ruku": 412,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4213,
            "text": "You may also obtain other benefits from them. You may ride them to seek whatever you need or be carried by them as ships carry you by sea.",
            "numberInSurah": 80,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 476,
            "ruku": 412,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4214,
            "text": "God shows you the evidence (of His existence). How can you then deny such evidence?",
            "numberInSurah": 81,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 476,
            "ruku": 412,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4215,
            "text": "Have they not travelled through the land to see the terrible end of those who lived before them? They were far mightier in both number and power and in what they had established. Their (worldly) gains were of no benefit to them.",
            "numberInSurah": 82,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 476,
            "ruku": 412,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4216,
            "text": "They were far too content with their own knowledge (to pay attention to the Messengers) when Our Messengers came to them with illustrious evidence. They were encompassed by the torment for mocking Our guidance.",
            "numberInSurah": 83,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 476,
            "ruku": 412,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4217,
            "text": "They said, 'We believe in One God and disbelieve in whatever we had considered equal to Him,' when they experienced Our wrath.",
            "numberInSurah": 84,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 476,
            "ruku": 412,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4218,
            "text": "Their faith proved to be of no benefit to them when they became subject to Our torment. Such was God's prevailing tradition among His servants in the past. Thus were the unbelievers destroyed.",
            "numberInSurah": 85,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 476,
            "ruku": 412,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 41,
        "name": "سُورَةُ فُصِّلَتۡ",
        "englishName": "Fussilat",
        "englishNameTranslation": "Explained in detail",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4219,
            "text": "Ha. Mim.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 477,
            "ruku": 413,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4220,
            "text": "This is the revelations from the Beneficent, Merciful God.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 477,
            "ruku": 413,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4221,
            "text": "The verses of this Book have been fully expounded. It is a reading in the Arabic language for the people of knowledge.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 477,
            "ruku": 413,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4222,
            "text": "It contains glad news and warnings (for the people), but most of them have ignored it and do not listen.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 477,
            "ruku": 413,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4223,
            "text": "They say, 'Our hearts are covered against and our ears are deaf to whatever you (Muhammad) invite us to. There is a barrier between us and you. So act as you please and we shall act as we please'.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 477,
            "ruku": 413,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4224,
            "text": "(Muhammad), say, 'I am a mere mortal like you. I have received a revelation that your Lord is the only One. So be up-right and obedient to Him and seek forgiveness from Him.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 477,
            "ruku": 413,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4225,
            "text": "Woe to the pagans, who do not pay zakat and have no faith in the life to come.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 477,
            "ruku": 413,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4226,
            "text": "The righteously striving believers will have a never-ending reward'.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 477,
            "ruku": 413,
            "hizbQuarter": 190,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4227,
            "text": "Say, 'Do you really disbelieve in the One Who created the earth in two days? Do you consider things equal to Him? He is the Lord of the Universe.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 477,
            "ruku": 414,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4228,
            "text": "In four days He placed the mountains on it, blessed it, and equally measured out sustenance for those who seek sustenance.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 477,
            "ruku": 414,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4229,
            "text": "He established His dominance over the sky, which (for that time) was like smoke. Then He told the heavens and the earth, 'Take your shape either willingly or by force' They said, 'We willingly obey'.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 477,
            "ruku": 414,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4230,
            "text": "He formed the seven heavens in two days and revealed to each one its task. He decked the sky above the earth with torches and protected it from (intruders).. Such is the design of the Majestic and All-knowing God'.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 478,
            "ruku": 414,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4231,
            "text": "If they ignore (your message), tell them, 'I have warned you against a destructive blast of sound like that which struck the people of `Ad and Thamud.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 478,
            "ruku": 414,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4232,
            "text": "When Messengers from all sides came to them saying, 'Do not worship anything besides God, ' they said, 'Had our Lord wanted, He would have sent us angelic Messengers. We do not believe in your message'.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 478,
            "ruku": 414,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4233,
            "text": "The people of Ad unjustly sought dominance on earth saying, 'Who is more powerful than us?' Did they not consider that God created them and that He is more powerful than they were?' They rejected Our revelations.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 478,
            "ruku": 414,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4234,
            "text": "We sent upon them a violent wind during a few ill-fated days to make them suffer a disgraceful torment in this life. Their torment in the life to come will be even more disgraceful and they will not receive any help.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 478,
            "ruku": 414,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4235,
            "text": "We sent guidance to the people of Thamud but they preferred blindness to guidance so a humiliating blast of torment struck them for their evil deeds.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 478,
            "ruku": 414,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4236,
            "text": "We only rescued the believers who had fear of God.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 478,
            "ruku": 414,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4237,
            "text": "They will be spurred on",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 478,
            "ruku": 415,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4238,
            "text": "until (on the brink of it) their eyes, ears and skin will testify to their deeds on the Day when the enemies of God are driven to the fire.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 478,
            "ruku": 415,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4239,
            "text": "They will ask their own skin, 'Why did you testify against us?' They will reply, 'God, who has made everything speak, made us also speak. It was He Who created you in the first place and to Him you have returned.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 479,
            "ruku": 415,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4240,
            "text": "You did not (think) to hide your deeds from your ears, eyes and skin and you felt that God would not know all that you had been doing.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 479,
            "ruku": 415,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4241,
            "text": "This was how you considered your Lord, but He knows you better than you know yourselves. Thus, you are now lost'.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 479,
            "ruku": 415,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4242,
            "text": "Even if they were to exercise patience, their dwelling would still be hell fire. Even if they were to seek favors, they would receive none.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 479,
            "ruku": 415,
            "hizbQuarter": 191,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4243,
            "text": "We assigned for them companions who would make their past and present (deeds) seem attractive to them. Thus, they became subject to what the jinn and human beings before were destined to suffer. They were certainly lost.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 479,
            "ruku": 415,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4244,
            "text": "The disbelievers say, 'Do not listen to this Quran but make a lot of unnecessary noise while it is being read so that perhaps you will defeat it'.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 479,
            "ruku": 416,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4245,
            "text": "We shall certainly make the unbelievers suffer severe torment and will punish them far worse than what they deserve for their deeds.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 479,
            "ruku": 416,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4246,
            "text": "The recompense of the enemies of God for their rejection of Our revelations will be fire as their eternal dwelling.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 479,
            "ruku": 416,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4247,
            "text": "The disbelievers will say, 'Lord, show us the human beings and jinn who caused us to go astray. We shall put them under our feet to lower them'.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 479,
            "ruku": 416,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4248,
            "text": "To those who have said, 'God is our Lord, ' and who have remained steadfast to their belief, the angels will descend saying, 'Do not be afraid or grieved. Receive the glad news of the Paradise which was promised to you.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 480,
            "ruku": 416,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4249,
            "text": "We are your guardians in this world and in the life to come, where you will have whatever you call for,",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 480,
            "ruku": 416,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4250,
            "text": "a hospitable welcome from the All-forgiving and All-merciful God'.",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 480,
            "ruku": 416,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4251,
            "text": "Who speaks better than one who invites human beings to God, acts righteously and says, 'I am a Muslim'.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 480,
            "ruku": 417,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4252,
            "text": "Virtue and evil are not equal. If you replace evil habits by virtuous ones, you will certainly find that your enemies will become your intimate friends.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 480,
            "ruku": 417,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4253,
            "text": "Only those who exercise patience and who have been granted a great share of God's favor can find such an opportunity.",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 480,
            "ruku": 417,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4254,
            "text": "(Muhammad), seek God's protection if satan's temptation grieves you, for God is All-hearing and All-knowing.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 480,
            "ruku": 417,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4255,
            "text": "(Some evidence of His existence) are the night, day, sun, and moon. Do not prostrate before the sun and the moon, but prostrate before God Who has created them if you want to worship Him alone.",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 480,
            "ruku": 417,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4256,
            "text": "However, if people are too proud to prostrate before God, let them know that God's other creatures glorify Him both day and night without fatigue.",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 480,
            "ruku": 417,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": {
              "id": 12,
              "recommended": false,
              "obligatory": true
            }
          },
          {
            "number": 4257,
            "text": "Further evidence is that (at times) you find the earth to be barren. When it is watered it moves and swells (to let the plants grow). The One who brings it back to life will also bring the dead back to life. He has power over all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 481,
            "ruku": 417,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4258,
            "text": "Those who deviate from Our revelations are not hidden from Us. Is the one who will be thrown into hell fire better than the one who will be brought safely into the presence of God on the Day of Judgment? Act as you wish; God is Well-Aware of whatever you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 481,
            "ruku": 417,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4259,
            "text": "The disbelievers (do not know) that the Quran which was sent to them is certainly a glorious Book.",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 481,
            "ruku": 417,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4260,
            "text": "Falsehood can not reach it from any direction. It is the revelation from the All-wise, Praiseworthy One.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 481,
            "ruku": 417,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4261,
            "text": "Nothing has been said to you which was not said to the Messengers who lived before you. Your Lord is certainly All-forgiving, but stern in His retribution.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 481,
            "ruku": 417,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4262,
            "text": "Had We sent down this Quran in a non-Arabic language, they would have said, 'Why have its verses not been well expounded?' Could a non-Arabic Book be revealed to an Arabic speaking person? (Muhammad), say, 'It is a guide and a cure for the believers. As for those who do not believe, they are deaf and blind. It is as though they had been called from a distant place'.",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 481,
            "ruku": 417,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4263,
            "text": "We had given the Book to Moses about which people greatly disagreed. Had the word of your Lord not been decreed, He would have certainly settled their differences (there and then). They were greatly suspicious and doubtful about the Book of Moses.",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 481,
            "ruku": 418,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4264,
            "text": "Whoever acts righteously does so for his own good and whoever commits evil does so against his soul. Your Lord is not unjust to His servants.",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 24,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 481,
            "ruku": 418,
            "hizbQuarter": 192,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4265,
            "text": "It is He who has the knowledge of the Hour of Doom and the fruits that will come out of their covering. He knows what the females conceive and deliver. On the day when the unbelievers will be asked, 'Where are the idols which you considered equal to God?,' they will reply, 'We declare that none of us have seen them'.",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 482,
            "ruku": 418,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4266,
            "text": "Whatever they had worshipped before will disappear and they will then know that there is no way for them to escape.",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 482,
            "ruku": 418,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4267,
            "text": "The human being never tires of asking for good, but if he is afflicted by hardship, he despairs and gives up all hope.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 482,
            "ruku": 418,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4268,
            "text": "When We grant him mercy after his suffering, he (boldly) says, 'This is what I deserved. I do not think that there will ever be a Day of Judgment. Even if I will be returned to my Lord, I shall still deserve to receive better rewards from Him.' We shall certainly tell the unbelievers about their deeds and cause them to suffer a severe punishment.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 482,
            "ruku": 418,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4269,
            "text": "When We grant the human being a favor, he ignores it and turns away but when he is afflicted by hardship, he starts lengthy prayers.",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 482,
            "ruku": 418,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4270,
            "text": "Say, 'Think, if the (Quran) is from God and you have rejected it, then who has gone farther astray than the one who has wandered far from the truth?",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 482,
            "ruku": 418,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4271,
            "text": "We shall (continue to) show them Our evidence in the world and within their souls until it becomes clear that the Quran is the truth. Is it not sufficient for you that your Lord witness all things?",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 482,
            "ruku": 418,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4272,
            "text": "They are certainly doubtful about their meeting with their Lord. God indeed encompasses all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 482,
            "ruku": 418,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 42,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الشُّورَىٰ",
        "englishName": "Ash-Shura",
        "englishNameTranslation": "Consultation",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4273,
            "text": "Ha. Mim.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 483,
            "ruku": 419,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4274,
            "text": "Ayn. Sin. Qaf.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 483,
            "ruku": 419,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4275,
            "text": "(Muhammad), this is how God, the Majestic and All-wise, sends revelations to you and sent them to those who lived before you.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 483,
            "ruku": 419,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4276,
            "text": "To Him belongs all that is in the heavens and the earth. He is the Most High and the Most Great.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 483,
            "ruku": 419,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4277,
            "text": "(When the revelation passes through) the heavens, they almost break apart. At that time the angels glorify their Lord with His praise and seek forgiveness for those who live on earth. God is certainly All-forgiving and All-merciful.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 483,
            "ruku": 419,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4278,
            "text": "God is the guardian of even those who have chosen others (idols) besides Him as their guardians (Muhammad), you will not have to answer for them.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 483,
            "ruku": 419,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4279,
            "text": "We have revealed the Quran to you in the Arabic language so that you could warn the people of the Mother Town (Mecca) and those around it of the inevitable Day of Resurrection when some will go to Paradise and others to hell.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 483,
            "ruku": 419,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4280,
            "text": "Had God wanted, He could have made them all one single nation, but He grants mercy to whomever He wills. The unjust will have no guardian or helper.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 483,
            "ruku": 419,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4281,
            "text": "Have they chosen other guardians besides Him? God is the real Guardian and it is He who will bring the dead back to life. He has power over all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 483,
            "ruku": 419,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4282,
            "text": "Whatever differences you may have about the Quran, the final decision rests with God. In Him do I trust and to Him do I turn in repentance.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 483,
            "ruku": 420,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4283,
            "text": "He is the Originator of the heavens and the earth. He has made you and the cattle in pairs and has multiplied you by His creation. There is certainly nothing like Him. He is All-hearing and All-aware.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 484,
            "ruku": 420,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4284,
            "text": "In His hands are the keys of the heavens and the earth. He increases and determines the sustenance of whomever He wants. He has the knowledge of all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 484,
            "ruku": 420,
            "hizbQuarter": 193,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4285,
            "text": "He has plainly clarified the religion which is revealed to you and that which Noah, Abraham, Moses, and Jesus were commanded to follow (He has explained it) so that you would be steadfast and united in your religion. What you call the pagans to is extremely grave for them. God attracts to (the religion) whomever He wants and guides to it whoever turns to Him in repentance.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 484,
            "ruku": 420,
            "hizbQuarter": 194,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4286,
            "text": "Only after receiving the knowledge did people divide themselves into different groups because of rebellion among themselves. Had it not been for your Lord's giving them respite for an appointed time, He would certainly have settled their differences once and for all. Those who inherited the Book, from their quarrelsome predecessors, also have doubts and suspicions about it.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 484,
            "ruku": 420,
            "hizbQuarter": 194,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4287,
            "text": "Thus, (Muhammad), preach (My revelation) to the people and be steadfast (in your faith) as you have been commanded. Do not follow their desires but say, 'I believe in the Book which God has sent down and I have been commanded to exercise justice among you. God is our Lord and your Lord. Each of us will be responsible for his own deeds. Let there be no disputes among us. God will bring us all together and to Him we shall all return'.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 484,
            "ruku": 420,
            "hizbQuarter": 194,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4288,
            "text": "The disputes of those who quarrel about God, after pledging obedience to Him, will be void in the eyes of their Lord. Such people will be subject to His wrath and will suffer a severe torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 485,
            "ruku": 420,
            "hizbQuarter": 194,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4289,
            "text": "It is God who revealed the Book and the Balance for a truthful purpose. You never know. Perhaps the Hour of Doom is close at hand.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 485,
            "ruku": 420,
            "hizbQuarter": 194,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4290,
            "text": "The disbelievers want you to show them the Day of Judgment immediately while the believers are afraid of it for they know it to be the truth. Those who insist on disputing the Hour of Doom are certainly in plain error.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 485,
            "ruku": 420,
            "hizbQuarter": 194,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4291,
            "text": "God is kind to His servants. He gives sustenance to whomever He wants. He is All-powerful and Majestic.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 485,
            "ruku": 420,
            "hizbQuarter": 194,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4292,
            "text": "We shall increase the harvest of those who seek a good harvest in the life hereafter. However, those who want to have their harvest in this life will be given it but will have no share in the hereafter.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 485,
            "ruku": 421,
            "hizbQuarter": 194,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4293,
            "text": "Do they have idols who have established a religion without the permission of God? Had not it been for your Lord's giving them respite for an appointed time, He would certainly have settled their differences once and for all. The unjust will certainly suffer a painful torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 485,
            "ruku": 421,
            "hizbQuarter": 194,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4294,
            "text": "You can see that the unjust are afraid of the consequences of their deeds which will inevitably strike them. However, the righteously striving believers will live in the gardens wherein they will have whatever they want from their Lord. This is certainly the greatest reward.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 485,
            "ruku": 421,
            "hizbQuarter": 194,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4295,
            "text": "This is the glad news which God gives to His servants, the righteously striving believers. (Muhammad), say, 'I do not ask you for any payment for my preaching to you except (your) love of (my near) relatives.' Whoever achieves virtue will have its merit increased. God is All-forgiving and Appreciating.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 486,
            "ruku": 421,
            "hizbQuarter": 194,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4296,
            "text": "Do they say that he, (Muhammad), has invented falsehood against God? Had God wanted, He could have sealed up your heart. God causes falsehood to vanish and, by His words, firmly establishes the truth. He has full knowledge of what the hearts contain.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 486,
            "ruku": 421,
            "hizbQuarter": 194,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4297,
            "text": "It is He who accepts the repentance of His servants, forgives their evil deeds and knows all about what you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 486,
            "ruku": 421,
            "hizbQuarter": 194,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4298,
            "text": "He answers the prayers of the righteously striving believers and grants them increasing favors. The unbelievers will suffer a severe punishment.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 486,
            "ruku": 421,
            "hizbQuarter": 194,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4299,
            "text": "Had God given abundant sustenance to His servants, they would have certainly rebelled on earth, but He sends them a known measure of sustenance as He wills. He is All-aware of His servants and watches over them all.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 486,
            "ruku": 421,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4300,
            "text": "It is He who sends down the rain after they had lost hope and spreads out His mercy. He is the Guardian and the Most Praiseworthy.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 486,
            "ruku": 421,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4301,
            "text": "Some of the evidence (of His existence) are His creation of the heavens and the earth and the beasts which inhabit it. He has all the power to bring them together if He wishes this to be so.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 486,
            "ruku": 421,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4302,
            "text": "Whatever hardship befalls you is the result of your own deeds. God pardons many of your sins.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 486,
            "ruku": 422,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4303,
            "text": "You cannot challenge God on earth and you will have no one besides Him as your guardian or helper.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 486,
            "ruku": 422,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4304,
            "text": "Further evidence (of His existence) are the ships which stand as mountains in the sea.",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 487,
            "ruku": 422,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4305,
            "text": "Had He wanted, He could have stopped the wind and let the ships remain motionless on the surface of the sea, in this there is evidence (of the Truth) for all those who are patient and grateful,",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 487,
            "ruku": 422,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4306,
            "text": "or He could have destroyed them as punishment for the human being's deeds. However, God pardons many sins.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 487,
            "ruku": 422,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4307,
            "text": "He knows all those who dispute His revelations. They will find no way to escape from (His torment).",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 487,
            "ruku": 422,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4308,
            "text": "Whatever you have received is just a means of enjoyment for this life but the reward of God for the believers and those who trust in their Lord will be better and everlasting.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 487,
            "ruku": 422,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4309,
            "text": "(This reward will be for) those who keep away from major sins and indecency, who forgive when they are made angry,",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 487,
            "ruku": 422,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4310,
            "text": "who have pledged their obedience to the Lord, who are steadfast in prayer, who conduct their affairs with consultation among themselves, who spend for the cause of God out of what We have given them,",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 487,
            "ruku": 422,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4311,
            "text": "and those who, when suffering a great injustice, seek to defend themselves.",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 487,
            "ruku": 422,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4312,
            "text": "The recompense for evil will be equivalent to the deed. He who pardons (the evil done to him) and reforms himself, will receive his reward from God. God certainly does not love the unjust.",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 487,
            "ruku": 422,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4313,
            "text": "Those who successfully defend themselves after being wronged will not be questioned.",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 487,
            "ruku": 422,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4314,
            "text": "Only those who do injustice to people and commit rebellion on earth for no reason will be questioned. They will suffer a painful torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 487,
            "ruku": 422,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4315,
            "text": "To exercise patience and forgive (the wrong done to one) is the proof of genuine determination.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 487,
            "ruku": 422,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4316,
            "text": "Whomever God has caused to go astray will find no guardian after this. You will see the unjust, on facing the torment, say, 'Is there any way to turn back?",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 487,
            "ruku": 423,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4317,
            "text": "You will see them exposed to the fire, subdued in humiliation, looking sideways at it pleadingly. However, at the same time, the believers will say, 'The true losers are those who will lose their souls and families on the Day of Judgment. The unjust will certainly suffer everlasting torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 488,
            "ruku": 423,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4318,
            "text": "They will have no guardian or helper besides God. Whoever God has caused to go astray will never find the right direction'.",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 488,
            "ruku": 423,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4319,
            "text": "Pledge obedience to your Lord before the coming of the inevitable Day when you will find no refuge to escape from God's wrath and no one to defend you.",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 488,
            "ruku": 423,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4320,
            "text": "(Muhammad), if they turn away from your message, know that We have not sent you as their keeper. Your duty is only to deliver the message. When We grant mercy to the human being, he becomes joyous, but when he is afflicted by evil as a result of his own deeds, he proves to be ungrateful.",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 488,
            "ruku": 423,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4321,
            "text": "To God belongs the heavens and the earth. He created whatever He wanted. He grants males, female, or pairs of.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 488,
            "ruku": 423,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4322,
            "text": "offspring to whomever He wants. He causes whomever He wants to be childless. He is All-Knowing and All-Powerful.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 488,
            "ruku": 423,
            "hizbQuarter": 195,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4323,
            "text": "To no mortal does God speak but through revelation, from behind a curtain, or by sending a Messenger who reveals, by His permission whatever He pleases. He is the Most High and the All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 488,
            "ruku": 423,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4324,
            "text": "Thus, We have revealed a Spirit to you, (Muhammad), by Our command. Before, you did not even know what a Book or Faith was, but We have made the Quran as a light by which We guide whichever of Our servants We want. You certainly guide (people) to the right path,",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 489,
            "ruku": 423,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4325,
            "text": "the path of God who is the owner of all that is in the heavens and the earth. To God certainly do all matters return.",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 489,
            "ruku": 423,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 43,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الزُّخۡرُفِ",
        "englishName": "Az-Zukhruf",
        "englishNameTranslation": "Ornaments of gold",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4326,
            "text": "Ha. Mim.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 489,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4327,
            "text": "I swear by the illustrious Book.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 489,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4328,
            "text": "We have made it an Arabic reading text so that perhaps you may understand.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 489,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4329,
            "text": "It (the Quran) exists in the original Book with Us which is certainly Most Exalted, full of wisdom and (beyond linguistic structures).",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 489,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4330,
            "text": "Can We ignore sending you the Quran just because you are a transgressing people?",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 489,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4331,
            "text": "How many Messengers did We send to the ancient people?",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 489,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4332,
            "text": "No Prophet came to them whom they did not mock.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 489,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4333,
            "text": "We destroyed the strongest among them in power. The stories of the ancient people have already been mentioned.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 489,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4334,
            "text": "(Muhammad), if you ask them, 'Who has created the heavens and the earth?' They will certainly say, 'The Majestic and All-knowing God has created them'.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 489,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4335,
            "text": "It is He who has made the earth for you as a cradle and has made roads therein so that you will perhaps seek guidance.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 489,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4336,
            "text": "It is He who has sent down water from the sky in a known measure by which He has given life to the dead earth. In the same way will you also be resurrected.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 490,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4337,
            "text": "It is He who has created everything in pairs and the ships and cattle for you to ride,",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 490,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4338,
            "text": "so that perhaps when you ride them, you will recall the bounties of your Lord and when you establish your control over it you would say, 'Glory belongs to Him who has made it subservient to us when we would not have been able to do so ourselves.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 490,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4339,
            "text": "To our Lord we shall all return'.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 490,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4340,
            "text": "The pagans have considered some of His servants as His children. There is no doubt that the human being is simply ungrateful.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 490,
            "ruku": 424,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4341,
            "text": "Has God chosen some of His own creatures as daughters for Himself and has given you the preference of having sons?",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 490,
            "ruku": 425,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4342,
            "text": "When one of them is given the glad news of the birth of a daughter, which they believe to be the only kind of child that the Beneficent God can have, his face blackens with anger.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 490,
            "ruku": 425,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4343,
            "text": "Does God choose for Himself the kind of children who grow up wearing ornaments and who are not strong enough to defend their rights?",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 490,
            "ruku": 425,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4344,
            "text": "Do they say that the angels, who are the servants of the Beneficent God, are females? Have they witnessed their creation? Their words as such will be recorded and they will be questioned for it.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 490,
            "ruku": 425,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4345,
            "text": "The pagans say, 'Had the Beneficent God wanted, we would not have worshipped them (idols).' Whatever they say is not based on knowledge. It is only a false conjecture.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 490,
            "ruku": 425,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4346,
            "text": "Had We, before sending the Quran, given them a book to which they now refer as an authority?",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 490,
            "ruku": 425,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4347,
            "text": "In fact, they say, 'We found our fathers following a certain belief and we now follow in their footsteps for our guidance'.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 490,
            "ruku": 425,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4348,
            "text": "In the same way, whenever We had sent a Messenger before you to warn a town, the rich ones therein said, 'We found our fathers following a certain belief and we follow in their footsteps.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 491,
            "ruku": 425,
            "hizbQuarter": 196,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4349,
            "text": "The Messengers would say, 'Would you still follow in the footsteps of your fathers even if I was to bring you better guidance?' They would say, 'We have no faith in your message'.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 491,
            "ruku": 425,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4350,
            "text": "We took revenge on them. See how terrible the end of those who rejected (Or revelations) was!",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 491,
            "ruku": 425,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4351,
            "text": "When Abraham said to his father and his people, 'I boldly renounce what you worship",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 491,
            "ruku": 426,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4352,
            "text": "except for the One who has created me and will guide me'.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 491,
            "ruku": 426,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4353,
            "text": "God made (belief in one God) an everlasting task for his successors, so that perhaps they would return (to Him).",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 491,
            "ruku": 426,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4354,
            "text": "In fact, We allowed them and their fathers to enjoy themselves until the truth and a strong Messenger came to them.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 491,
            "ruku": 426,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4355,
            "text": "When the truth came to them, they said, 'This is magic and we have no faith in it'.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 491,
            "ruku": 426,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4356,
            "text": "Then they said, 'Why this Quran had not been revealed to a man from either of the two great towns'.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 491,
            "ruku": 426,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4357,
            "text": "Do they distribute the mercy of your Lord? It is We who have distributed their sustenance in this world and raised the positions of some of them above the others so that they would mock each other. The mercy of your Lord is better than what they can amass.",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 491,
            "ruku": 426,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4358,
            "text": "Were it not for the fear that all people would become one in disbelief, We would have made for the disbelievers in the Beneficent God ceilings out of silver and ladders by which they would climb up,",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 491,
            "ruku": 426,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4359,
            "text": "doors for their houses, couches on which to recline,",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 492,
            "ruku": 426,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4360,
            "text": "and other ornament of gold. All these are only the means of enjoyment in this world, but the pious will receive their reward from your Lord in the life hereafter.",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 492,
            "ruku": 426,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4361,
            "text": "We shall make satan the companion of whoever ignores the remembrance of the Beneficent God.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 492,
            "ruku": 427,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4362,
            "text": "Satan will prevent them from the right path while they think that they have the right guidance.",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 492,
            "ruku": 427,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4363,
            "text": "When he returns to us, he will say (to satan), 'Would that there had been as long a distance between me and you as that between the East and West. What a terrible companion you have been'.",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 492,
            "ruku": 427,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4364,
            "text": "They will be told on the Day of Judgment, 'Regret will never be of any benefit to you. You have done injustice to your souls and you will share the torment'.",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 492,
            "ruku": 427,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4365,
            "text": "(Muhammad), can you make the deaf hear or guide the blind or the one who is clearly in error?",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 492,
            "ruku": 427,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4366,
            "text": "We shall revenge them either after your death",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 492,
            "ruku": 427,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4367,
            "text": "or show them to you suffering the torment with which We had threatened them. We are certainly dominant over them all.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 492,
            "ruku": 427,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4368,
            "text": "Follow devotedly that which is revealed to you. You are certainly on the right path.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 492,
            "ruku": 427,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4369,
            "text": "The Quran is a reminder to you and to your people and you will soon be questioned about it.",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 492,
            "ruku": 427,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4370,
            "text": "You can ask Our Messengers whom We sent before you if We had commanded them to worship other gods besides the Beneficent God?'",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 492,
            "ruku": 427,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4371,
            "text": "We sent Moses to the Pharaoh and his nobles with Our miracles and he said, 'I am the Messenger of the Lord of the Universe'.",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 492,
            "ruku": 428,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4372,
            "text": "When he showed them Our miracles, they started to laugh at them.",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 492,
            "ruku": 428,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4373,
            "text": "Of all the miracles which We showed to them the latter ones were greater than the former. We struck them with torment so that perhaps they would return to Us.",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 493,
            "ruku": 428,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4374,
            "text": "They said, 'Magician, pray to your Lord for us through your covenant with Him (If he saves us from the torment), we shall certainly seek guidance'.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 493,
            "ruku": 428,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4375,
            "text": "When We relieved them from the torment they suddenly turned back on their heels.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 493,
            "ruku": 428,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4376,
            "text": "The Pharaoh shouted to his people, 'My people, is the kingdom of Egypt not mine? and can you not see that the streams flow from beneath my palace?",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 493,
            "ruku": 428,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4377,
            "text": "Am I not better than this lowly man who can barely express himself?",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 493,
            "ruku": 428,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4378,
            "text": "Why have bracelets of gold not been given to him and why have some angels not accompanied him?'",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 493,
            "ruku": 428,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4379,
            "text": "Thus, he made dimwits out of his people and they followed him. They, certainly, were a sinful people. When they invoked Our anger,",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 493,
            "ruku": 428,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4380,
            "text": "We took revenge on them by drowning them all together.",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 493,
            "ruku": 428,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4381,
            "text": "We made them become of the people of the past and an example for the coming generations.",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 493,
            "ruku": 428,
            "hizbQuarter": 197,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4382,
            "text": "When the son of Mary was mentioned as an example, you people cried out in protest, saying,",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 493,
            "ruku": 429,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4383,
            "text": "'Are our gods any better than Jesus (for according to Muhammad), if our gods go to hell so too will Jesus. What they say is only a false argument. In fact, they are a quarrelsome people.",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 493,
            "ruku": 429,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4384,
            "text": "Jesus was a servant of Ours to whom We had granted favors and whom We made as an example for the Israelites.",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 493,
            "ruku": 429,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4385,
            "text": "Had We wanted, We could have made the angels as your successors on the earth.",
            "numberInSurah": 60,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 493,
            "ruku": 429,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4386,
            "text": "(Muhammad), tell them, 'Jesus is a sign of the Hour of Doom. Have no doubt about it and follow me; this is the straight path.",
            "numberInSurah": 61,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 494,
            "ruku": 429,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4387,
            "text": "Let satan not prevent you from the right path. He is your sworn enemy'.",
            "numberInSurah": 62,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 494,
            "ruku": 429,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4388,
            "text": "When Jesus came with clear proof (in support of his truthfulness), he said, 'I have come to you with wisdom to clarify for you some of the matters in which you have disputes. Have fear of God and obey me.",
            "numberInSurah": 63,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 494,
            "ruku": 429,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4389,
            "text": "God is your Lord and my Lord, so worship Him. This is the right path'.",
            "numberInSurah": 64,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 494,
            "ruku": 429,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4390,
            "text": "But certain groups created differences among themselves. Woe to the unjust. They will face a painful torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 65,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 494,
            "ruku": 429,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4391,
            "text": "Are they waiting for the Hour of Doom when the torment will suddenly strike them and they will not even realize from where it came?",
            "numberInSurah": 66,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 494,
            "ruku": 429,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4392,
            "text": "All intimate friends on that day will become each others enemies except for the pious,",
            "numberInSurah": 67,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 494,
            "ruku": 429,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4393,
            "text": "whom God will tell, 'My servants, you need have no fear on this day, nor will you be grieved'.",
            "numberInSurah": 68,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 494,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4394,
            "text": "Those who have faith in Our revelations and have submitted themselves to Our will,",
            "numberInSurah": 69,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 494,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4395,
            "text": "will be told, 'Enter Paradise with your spouses in delight.",
            "numberInSurah": 70,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 494,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4396,
            "text": "Golden dishes and cups will be passed among them. All that the souls may desire and that may delight their eyes will be available therein. You will live therein forever.",
            "numberInSurah": 71,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 494,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4397,
            "text": "This is the Paradise which you have received as your inheritance by virtue of what you have done.",
            "numberInSurah": 72,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 494,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4398,
            "text": "You will have abundant fruits therein to consume'.",
            "numberInSurah": 73,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 494,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4399,
            "text": "The criminals will live forever in the torment of hell. Their torment will not be relieved and they will despair of escaping.",
            "numberInSurah": 74,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4400,
            "text": "We had not done any injustice to them but they had wronged themselves.",
            "numberInSurah": 75,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4401,
            "text": "They will cry out, 'Guard, let your Lord destroy us'.",
            "numberInSurah": 76,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4402,
            "text": "The angelic guard will say, 'You will have to stay.",
            "numberInSurah": 77,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4403,
            "text": "We brought you the truth but most of you disliked it'.",
            "numberInSurah": 78,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4404,
            "text": "If the disbelievers persist in their disbelief, We shall also persist in punishing them.",
            "numberInSurah": 79,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4405,
            "text": "Do they think that We do not hear their secrets and whispers? We certainly can hear them and Our Messengers record it all.",
            "numberInSurah": 80,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4406,
            "text": "(Muhammad), say, 'Had the Beneficent God really had a son, I would certainly have been the first one to worship him.",
            "numberInSurah": 81,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4407,
            "text": "The Lord of the heavens and the earth and the Throne is too glorious to be described in the way they describe Him.",
            "numberInSurah": 82,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4408,
            "text": "Leave them (to indulge) in their desires and play around until they face that day which has been promised to them.",
            "numberInSurah": 83,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4409,
            "text": "It is God who is the Lord of the heavens and is the Lord on earth. He is All-wise and All-knowing.",
            "numberInSurah": 84,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4410,
            "text": "Blessed is He to whom belongs the heavens, the earth and all that is between them and who has the knowledge of the Hour of Doom. To Him you will all return.",
            "numberInSurah": 85,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4411,
            "text": "Those whom they worship besides God are not able to intercede, except for those among them who believe in the Truth (God) and who know whom to intercede for.",
            "numberInSurah": 86,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4412,
            "text": "(Muhammad), if you ask them, 'Who had created the idols?' They will certainly say, 'God has created them.' Why do you then turn away from God?",
            "numberInSurah": 87,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4413,
            "text": "(God has knowledge of Muhammad's words when he complains to Him), 'My Lord, these, my people, do not believe'.",
            "numberInSurah": 88,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4414,
            "text": "We have told him, 'Ignore them and say to them 'farewell'. They will soon know the consequences of their deeds",
            "numberInSurah": 89,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 495,
            "ruku": 430,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 44,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الدُّخَانِ",
        "englishName": "Ad-Dukhaan",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Smoke",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4415,
            "text": "Ha. Mim.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4416,
            "text": "I swear by the illustrious Book.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4417,
            "text": "that We have revealed the Quran on a blessed night to warn mankind.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4418,
            "text": "On this night, every absolute command coming from Us becomes distinguishable.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4419,
            "text": "The command that We have been sending",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4420,
            "text": "as a mercy (for the human being) from your Lord. Your Lord is All-hearing and All-knowing.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4421,
            "text": "He is the Lord of the heavens and the earth and all that is between them, if only you would have strong faith.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4422,
            "text": "There is only One Lord. It is He who gives life and causes things to die. He is your Lord and the Lord of your forefathers.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4423,
            "text": "In fact, the unbelievers have doubts because of excessive involvement in worldly affairs.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4424,
            "text": "Wait for the day (which will come before the Day of Judgment) when the sky will give out dense smoke",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4425,
            "text": "which will smother the people. They will say, 'This is a painful torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4426,
            "text": "Lord, remove this torment from us for we are believers'.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4427,
            "text": "How could this punishment bring them to their senses when a Messenger evidently had come to them,",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4428,
            "text": "and they turned away, saying, 'He is a trained and insane person'.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4429,
            "text": "We shall remove the torment for a while but you will revert to your old ways.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4430,
            "text": "However, We shall truly take Our revenge on the day when the great seizure takes place.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 198,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4431,
            "text": "We had certainly tested the people of the Pharaoh before them to whom a noble Messengers had come, saying,",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4432,
            "text": "'Send the servants of God with me. I am a trustworthy Messenger sent to you.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 496,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4433,
            "text": "Do not consider yourselves above God? I shall show you a manifest authority (in support of my truthfulness).",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4434,
            "text": "I seek protection from my Lord and your Lord from your decision of stoning me.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4435,
            "text": "If you do not want to believe, leave me alone'.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4436,
            "text": "Moses addressed his Lord, saying, 'Lord, these people are sinners'.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4437,
            "text": "We told him, 'Leave the city with My servants during the night. You will be pursued.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4438,
            "text": "Cross the sea by cutting a path through it. Pharaoh's army will be drowned.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4439,
            "text": "How many were the gardens, springs,",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4440,
            "text": "corn-fields, gracious mansions,",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4441,
            "text": "and other bounties which they enjoyed yet left behind!",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4442,
            "text": "We gave these as an inheritance to other people.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4443,
            "text": "The sky nor the earth cried for them, nor were they given respite.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 431,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4444,
            "text": "We rescued the Israelites from the humiliating torment",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 432,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4445,
            "text": "and from the Pharaoh. He was the chief of the transgressors.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 432,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4446,
            "text": "We gave preference to the Israelites over the other people with Our knowledge",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 432,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4447,
            "text": "and sent them revelations of which some were a clear trial for them.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 432,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4448,
            "text": "These people say,",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 432,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4449,
            "text": "'After we die, we shall never be raised to life again.",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 432,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4450,
            "text": "Bring back to life our fathers if what you say is true'.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 432,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4451,
            "text": "Are they better than the tribe of Tubba (name of a Yemenite tribal chief) and those who lived before them? We destroyed them. They were criminals.",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 432,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4452,
            "text": "We have not created the heavens and the earth and all that is between them for Our own amusement.",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 432,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4453,
            "text": "We have created them for a genuine purpose, but most people do not know.",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 497,
            "ruku": 432,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4454,
            "text": "The appointed time for all of them will be the Day of Judgment",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 432,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4455,
            "text": "(when wrong will be distinguished from right). On this day friends will be of no benefit to one another, nor will they receive any help",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 432,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4456,
            "text": "except for those to whom God grants mercy. He is Majestic and All-merciful.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 432,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4457,
            "text": "The tree of Zaqqum",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4458,
            "text": "is food for the sinner.",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4459,
            "text": "It will be like molted brass which will boil in the bellies",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4460,
            "text": "like water.",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4461,
            "text": "(It will be said of such sinners), 'Seize them and drag them into the middle of hell.",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4462,
            "text": "Then pour unto their heads the boiling water to torment them'.",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4463,
            "text": "They will be told, 'Suffer the torment. You had thought yourselves to be majestic and honorable.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4464,
            "text": "This is the torment that you persistently doubted'.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4465,
            "text": "The pious ones will be in a secure place",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4466,
            "text": "amid gardens and springs,",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4467,
            "text": "clothed in fine silk and rich brocade, sitting face to face with one another.",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4468,
            "text": "We shall unite them to maidens with big black and white lovely eyes.",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4469,
            "text": "They will be offered all kinds of fruits, in peace and security.",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4470,
            "text": "They will not experience any death other than that which they have already been through.",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4471,
            "text": "God will protect them from the torment of hell as a favor from your Lord. (Muhammad), this is certainly the greatest triumph.",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4472,
            "text": "We have made the Quran easy for you to recite so that perhaps they may take heed.",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4473,
            "text": "Wait (for God's decree) and they too will be waiting.",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 498,
            "ruku": 433,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 45,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الجَاثِيَةِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Jaathiya",
        "englishNameTranslation": "Crouching",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4474,
            "text": "Ha. Mim.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 499,
            "ruku": 434,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4475,
            "text": "This Book is revealed from God, the Majestic and All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 499,
            "ruku": 434,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4476,
            "text": "In the heavens and the earth there is evidence (of the Truth) for the believers.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 499,
            "ruku": 434,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4477,
            "text": "In your creation and in that of the beasts living on earth there is evidence of the Truth for the people who have strong faith.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 499,
            "ruku": 434,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4478,
            "text": "In the alternation of the night and the day, the sustenance which God has sent down from the sky to revive the barren earth, and in the changing of the direction of the winds there is evidence of the truth for the people of understanding.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 499,
            "ruku": 434,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4479,
            "text": "These are the revelations of God which We recite to you for a genuine purpose. In what statements other than God's and His revelations will they then believe?",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 499,
            "ruku": 434,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4480,
            "text": "Woe to every sinful liar!",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 499,
            "ruku": 434,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4481,
            "text": "He hears the revelations of God which are recited to him, then persists in his arrogance as if he had not even heard them. Tell him that he will suffer a painful torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 499,
            "ruku": 434,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4482,
            "text": "When he learns about some of Our revelations, he mocks them. Such people will suffer a humiliating torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 499,
            "ruku": 434,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4483,
            "text": "Hell is awaiting them and none of their deeds will be of any benefit to them, nor will any guardian whom they have chosen besides God. They will suffer a great torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 499,
            "ruku": 434,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4484,
            "text": "This (Quran) is a guidance. Those who reject the revelations of their Lord will suffer the most painful punishment.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 499,
            "ruku": 434,
            "hizbQuarter": 199,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4485,
            "text": "God has made the sea subservient to you so that ships sail on by His command and you seek His favors. Perhaps you will be grateful.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 499,
            "ruku": 435,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4486,
            "text": "He has also made subservient to you all that is in the heavens and the earth. In this there is evidence (of the Truth) for those who use their minds.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 499,
            "ruku": 435,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4487,
            "text": "Tell the believers to forgive those who do not have faith in the days of God (Day of Judgment) and Resurrection. God will give due recompense to all the people for their deeds.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 500,
            "ruku": 435,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4488,
            "text": "One who acts righteously does so for his own benefit and one who commits evil does so against his own soul. To your Lord you will all return.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 500,
            "ruku": 435,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4489,
            "text": "We gave the Book to the Israelites, the commandments, and prophethood, granted them pure sustenance, and gave them preference above all people.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 500,
            "ruku": 435,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4490,
            "text": "We also gave them clear evidence in support of the true religion. Only after having received knowledge did they create differences among themselves because of their rebelliousness. Your Lord will issue His decree concerning their differences on the Day of Judgment.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 500,
            "ruku": 435,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4491,
            "text": "We have established for you a code of conduct and a religion. Follow it and do not follow the desires of the ignorant people.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 500,
            "ruku": 435,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4492,
            "text": "They will never be sufficient (protection) for you in place of God. The unjust are each other's friends, but God is the guardian of the pious ones.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 500,
            "ruku": 435,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4493,
            "text": "This (Quran) is an enlightenment for the people and a guide and mercy for the people who have strong faith.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 500,
            "ruku": 435,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4494,
            "text": "Do the people who commit evil think that We shall make their life and death like that of the righteously striving believers? How terrible is their Judgment!",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 500,
            "ruku": 435,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4495,
            "text": "God has created the heavens and the earth for a genuine purpose so that every soul will be duly recompensed for its deeds without being wronged.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 500,
            "ruku": 436,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4496,
            "text": "Have you seen the one who has chosen his desires as his lord? God has knowingly caused him to go astray, sealed his ears and heart and veiled his vision. Who besides God can guide him? Will they, then, not take heed?",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 501,
            "ruku": 436,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4497,
            "text": "They have said, 'The only life is this worldly life and here we shall live and die. It is only time which will destroy us' They have no knowledge about this. It is only their guesswork.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 501,
            "ruku": 436,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4498,
            "text": "When Our enlightening revelations are recited to them, their only argument against it is, 'Bring our forefathers back to life if what you say is true'.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 501,
            "ruku": 436,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4499,
            "text": "(Muhammad), say, 'It is God who gives you life and causes you to die. He will bring you together on the inevitable Day of Judgment,' but most people do not know.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 501,
            "ruku": 436,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4500,
            "text": "To God belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. On the day when the Hour of Doom arrives, the followers of falsehood will be lost.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 501,
            "ruku": 437,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4501,
            "text": "You will see all the people kneeling down. Everyone will be summoned to the Book (containing the record of their deeds). They will be told, 'On this day you will be recompensed for what you have done'.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 501,
            "ruku": 437,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4502,
            "text": "This is Our Book. It will tell you the truth. We have made a copy of all that you have done.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 501,
            "ruku": 437,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4503,
            "text": "The Lord will admit the righteously striving, believing people into His mercy. This is certainly a clear victory.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 501,
            "ruku": 437,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4504,
            "text": "To the unbelievers the Lord will say, 'Were not Our revelations recited to you and did not you arrogantly reject them? You were a sinful people'.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 501,
            "ruku": 437,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4505,
            "text": "When it was said that the promise of God is true and that the Hour would inevitably come, you said, 'We do not know what the Hour of Doom is, we are suspicious about it and we are not convinced'.",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 501,
            "ruku": 437,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4506,
            "text": "Their evil deeds will be revealed to them and (the torment) which they had mocked will surround them.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 502,
            "ruku": 437,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4507,
            "text": "They will be told, 'On this day We shall forget you in the same way that you had forgotten your coming into Our presence. Your dwelling will be hell fire and no one will help you.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 502,
            "ruku": 437,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4508,
            "text": "This is only because you had mocked the revelations of God and the worldly life had deceived you. On this day they will not be taken out of hell, nor will they be granted any favors.",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 502,
            "ruku": 437,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4509,
            "text": "It is only God, Lord of the heavens and the earth and Lord of the Universe who deserves all praise.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 502,
            "ruku": 437,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4510,
            "text": "It is His greatness that dominates the heavens and the earth. He is the Majestic and All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 25,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 502,
            "ruku": 437,
            "hizbQuarter": 200,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 46,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الأَحۡقَافِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Ahqaf",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Dunes",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4511,
            "text": "Ha. Mim.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 502,
            "ruku": 438,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4512,
            "text": "This Book is revealed from God the Majestic and All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 502,
            "ruku": 438,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4513,
            "text": "We have created the heavens and the earth and all that is between them ONLY for a genuine purpose and an appointed time. The unbelievers ignore that of which they have been warned.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 502,
            "ruku": 438,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4514,
            "text": "(Muhammad), ask them, 'Have you thought about what you worship besides God? Show me which part of the earth they have created. Do they have a share in the creation of the heavens? Bring me a Book, revealed before this Quran, or any other proof based on knowledge to support your belief, if indeed you are truthful'.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 502,
            "ruku": 438,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4515,
            "text": "Who is more astray than one who prays to things besides God; things that would not be able to answer his prayers even if he would wait till the Day of Judgment. They are not even aware of his prayers.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 502,
            "ruku": 438,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4516,
            "text": "When people will be resurrected, such gods will become their enemies and will reject their worship.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 503,
            "ruku": 438,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4517,
            "text": "When Our enlightening revelations are recited to them, the disbelievers, of the truth which has come to them, say, 'This is plain magic'.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 503,
            "ruku": 438,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4518,
            "text": "They say, '(Muhammad) has invented it (Quran) by himself.' Say, 'Had I invented it, you would not have been able to rescue me from God. He knows best what you say about it. He is our witness and He is All-forgiving and All-merciful'.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 503,
            "ruku": 438,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4519,
            "text": "Say, 'I am not the first Messenger. I do not know what will be done to me or to you. I follow only what has been revealed to me and my duty is only to give clear warning'.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 503,
            "ruku": 438,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4520,
            "text": "Say, 'What do you think will happen if this Quran is from God and you have rejected it? Besides, a witness from among the Israelites has testified to the divinity of a Book like it and believed in it (Quran) while you have arrogantly denied it. God does not guide the unjust.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 503,
            "ruku": 438,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4521,
            "text": "The disbelievers have said about the believers, 'Had there been anything good in it (Quran), they could not have accepted it before us' Since they do not benefit from its guidance, they say, 'It (Quran) is only a fabricated legend'.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 503,
            "ruku": 439,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4522,
            "text": "Before this (Quran), the Book of Moses was a guide and a blessing. This Book confirms the Torah. It is in the Arabic language so that it may warn the unjust people, and give glad news to the righteous ones.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 503,
            "ruku": 439,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4523,
            "text": "Those who have said, 'Our Lord is God,' and are steadfast in their belief need have no fear or be grieved.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 503,
            "ruku": 439,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4524,
            "text": "They will be the dwellers of Paradise wherein they will live forever as a reward for what they have done.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 503,
            "ruku": 439,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4525,
            "text": "We have advised the human being to be kind to his parents; his mother bore him with hardship and delivered him while suffering a great deal of pain. The period in which his mother bore and weaned him lasted for thirty months. When he grew-up to manhood and became forty years old, he then said, 'Lord, inspire me to give You thanks for the bounties you have granted to me and my parents, and to act righteously to please You. Lord, make my offspring virtuous. Lord I turn to you in repentance; I am a Muslim'.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 504,
            "ruku": 439,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4526,
            "text": "These are the ones from whom We accept righteous deeds and ignore their bad deeds. They will be among the dwellers of Paradise. It is the true promise which was given to them.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 504,
            "ruku": 439,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4527,
            "text": "There are people who say to their parents, 'Fie upon you! Are you telling us that we shall be raised from our graves? So many people have died before us and (none of them have been raised)' Their parents plead to God and say to their child, 'Woe to you! Have faith; the promise of God is certainly true' They reply, 'What you say is only ancient legends'.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 504,
            "ruku": 439,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4528,
            "text": "Such people will be subject to the punishment of God, which was also decreed for many human beings and jinn before them. These people are certainly lost.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 504,
            "ruku": 439,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4529,
            "text": "Everyone will have a position proportionate to the degree of his deeds. Finally, God will recompense them for their deeds and they will not be wronged.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 504,
            "ruku": 439,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4530,
            "text": "On the day when the disbelievers will be exposed to the fire, they will be told, 'You have spent your happy days during your worldly life and enjoyed them. On this day you will suffer a humiliating torment for your unreasonably arrogant manners on earth and for the evil deeds which you have committed'.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 504,
            "ruku": 439,
            "hizbQuarter": 201,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4531,
            "text": "(Muhammad), recall the brother of the people of Ad, when he warned his people in the valley of al-ahqaf saying, 'There existed many warners before and after him. Do not worship anything other than God. I am afraid for you about the torment of the great Day'.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 505,
            "ruku": 440,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4532,
            "text": "They said, 'Have you come to turn us away from our gods? Show us that with which you threaten us if you are truthful'.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 505,
            "ruku": 440,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4533,
            "text": "He said, 'Only God has the knowledge (of the coming of such torment). I preach to you the message that I have brought, but I can see that you are an ignorant people'.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 505,
            "ruku": 440,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4534,
            "text": "When they saw the torment as a cloud proceeding to their valleys, they said, 'This cloud will bring us rain.' He said, 'No, it is the torment which you wanted to suffer immediately. It is a wind bearing and painful torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 505,
            "ruku": 440,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4535,
            "text": "It will destroy everything by the will of its Lord' (Not very long after) nothing could be seen of them except their dwellings. Thus do We recompense the sinful people.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 505,
            "ruku": 440,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4536,
            "text": "We had established them more firmly in the land than you are. We had given them ears, eyes, and hearts but none of their ears, eyes, and hearts proved to be of any benefit to them; they rejected the revelations of God and the torment which they mocked brought upon them utter destruction.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 505,
            "ruku": 440,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4537,
            "text": "We destroyed some towns around you and showed you the evidence (of the Truth) so that perhaps you would turn (to God).",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 505,
            "ruku": 441,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4538,
            "text": "Why did the idols, whom they worshipped as a means of pleasing God, not help them? In fact, they proved to be the cause of their going astray and it were lies which they had falsely invented lies.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 505,
            "ruku": 441,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4539,
            "text": "We turned a party of jinn towards you to listen to the Quran. When they attended a Quranic recitation, they said to each other, 'Be silent,' and, when it was over, they turned back to their people, in warning,",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 506,
            "ruku": 441,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4540,
            "text": "and said, 'Our people, we have listened to the recitation of a Book revealed after Moses. It confirms the Books revealed before and guides to the Truth and the right path.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 506,
            "ruku": 441,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4541,
            "text": "Our people, respond favorably to the Messenger of God and believe in Him. He will forgive your sins and rescue you from the painful torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 506,
            "ruku": 441,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4542,
            "text": "Those who do not favorably respond to the Messenger of God should know that they cannot challenge God on earth and will not have anyone as their guardian besides Him. Such people are in plain error'.",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 506,
            "ruku": 441,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4543,
            "text": "Have they not seen that God has created the heavens and the earth and that He experienced no fatigue in doing this. He has the power to bring the dead back to life. Certainly He has power over all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 506,
            "ruku": 441,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4544,
            "text": "On the day when the disbelievers will be exposed to the fire, they will be asked, 'Is this not real?' They will say, 'Yes, Our Lord, it is real' He will say, 'Suffer the torment for your disbelief'.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 506,
            "ruku": 441,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4545,
            "text": "(Muhammad), exercise patience as did the steadfast Messengers. Do not try to make them suffer the torment immediately; on the day when they will see the torment with which they were threatened, they will think that they had lived no more than an hour. The message has been delivered. No one else will be destroyed except the evil doing people.",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 506,
            "ruku": 441,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 47,
        "name": "سُورَةُ مُحَمَّدٍ",
        "englishName": "Muhammad",
        "englishNameTranslation": "Muhammad",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4546,
            "text": "God has made devoid of all virtue the deeds of those who have disbelieved and prevented others from the way of God.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 507,
            "ruku": 442,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4547,
            "text": "God forgives the sins and reforms the hearts of the righteously striving believers who have faith in what is revealed to Muhammad - which is the Truth from his Lord.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 507,
            "ruku": 442,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4548,
            "text": "This is because the disbelievers have followed falsehood and the believers have followed the Truth from their Lord. Thus God explains to the human being their own prospects.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 507,
            "ruku": 442,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4549,
            "text": "If you encounter the disbelievers in a battle, strike-off their heads. Take them as captives when they are defeated. Then you may set them free as a favor to them, with or without a ransom, when the battle is over. This is the Law. Had God wanted, He could have granted them (unbelievers) victory, but He wants to test you through each other. The deeds of those who are killed for the cause of God will never be without virtuous results.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 507,
            "ruku": 442,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4550,
            "text": "God will lead them to everlasting happiness and improve their condition.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 507,
            "ruku": 442,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4551,
            "text": "He will admit them into the Paradise which He has made known to them.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 507,
            "ruku": 442,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4552,
            "text": "Believers, if you help God, He will help you and make you steadfast (in your faith).",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 507,
            "ruku": 442,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4553,
            "text": "The fate of the disbelievers will be to stumble and their deeds will have no virtuous results;",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 507,
            "ruku": 442,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4554,
            "text": "they have hated God's revelation, and thus, He has made their deeds devoid of all virtue.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 507,
            "ruku": 442,
            "hizbQuarter": 202,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4555,
            "text": "Have they not travelled through the land and seen the terrible end of those who lived before them? God brought upon them utter destruction and the disbelievers will also faced similar perdition.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 507,
            "ruku": 442,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4556,
            "text": "God is the guardian of the believers, but the disbelievers have no guardian.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 507,
            "ruku": 442,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4557,
            "text": "God will admit the righteously striving believers into the gardens wherein streams flow. However, the disbelievers who enjoyed themselves and ate like cattle will have for their dwelling hell fire.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 508,
            "ruku": 443,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4558,
            "text": "(Muhammad), how many towns, much more powerful than the one from which you have been expelled, have We destroyed and left helpless?",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 508,
            "ruku": 443,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4559,
            "text": "Can the one who follows the authority of his Lord be considered equal to the one whose evil deeds are made to seem attractive to him and who follows his own desires?",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 508,
            "ruku": 443,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4560,
            "text": "The garden, which is promised to the pious, is like one in which there are streams of unpolluted water, streams of milk of unchangeable taste, streams of delicious wine, and streams of crystal clear honey. Therein they will have all kinds of fruits and forgiveness from their Lord. On the other hand (can these people be considered like), those who will live forever in hell fire and will drink boiling water which will rip their intestines to bits?",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 508,
            "ruku": 443,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4561,
            "text": "(Muhammad), some of them listen to you, but when they leave you they ask those who have received knowledge, 'What did he say a few moments ago?' God has sealed the hearts of such people who have followed their worldly desires.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 508,
            "ruku": 443,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4562,
            "text": "God will increase the guidance and piety of those who seek guidance.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 508,
            "ruku": 443,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4563,
            "text": "Are they waiting for the Hour of Doom to suddenly approach them? Its signs have already appeared. How will they then come to their senses when the Hour itself will approach them?",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 508,
            "ruku": 443,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4564,
            "text": "Know that God is the only Lord. Ask forgiveness for your sins and for the sins of the believing men and women. God knows when you move and when you rest.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 508,
            "ruku": 443,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4565,
            "text": "The believers say, 'Why is a chapter about jihad - fighting for the cause of God - not revealed?' But when such a chapter, with clear commands and a mention of jihad is revealed, you will see those whose hearts are sick look at you as if suffering the agony of death. One can expect nothing better from them!",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 509,
            "ruku": 444,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4566,
            "text": "Since they have (pledged) Us obedience and to speak reasonably, it would be more proper for them, when it is decided (that everyone must take part in the battle), to remain true (in their pledge to God).",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 509,
            "ruku": 444,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4567,
            "text": "If you ignore the commands of God would you then also spread evil in the land and sever the ties of kinship?",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 509,
            "ruku": 444,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4568,
            "text": "God has condemned these people and made them deaf, dumb, and blind.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 509,
            "ruku": 444,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4569,
            "text": "Is it that they do not think about the Quran or are their hearts sealed?",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 509,
            "ruku": 444,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4570,
            "text": "Those who have reverted to disbelief after guidance has become manifest to them, have been seduced and given false hopes by satan.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 509,
            "ruku": 444,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4571,
            "text": "This is because they have said to those who hate God's revelation, 'We shall obey you in some matters.' But God knows all their secrets.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 509,
            "ruku": 444,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4572,
            "text": "How terrible it will be for them when the angels take away their souls by striking their faces and their backs.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 509,
            "ruku": 444,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4573,
            "text": "for their following that which had incurred God's anger, and their hatred to please God. Thus, God has made their deeds devoid of all virtue.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 509,
            "ruku": 444,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4574,
            "text": "Do those whose hearts are sick think that God will never make their malice public?",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 509,
            "ruku": 445,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4575,
            "text": "Had We wanted, We could have made you recognize their faces. You will certainly recognize them by the tone of their speech. God knows all your deeds.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 510,
            "ruku": 445,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4576,
            "text": "We shall certainly test you until We know those who strive hard for the cause of God and those who exercise patience. We will also examine your deeds.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 510,
            "ruku": 445,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4577,
            "text": "The disbelievers who prevent others from the way of God and give the Messengers a hard time - even after the guidance has been made clear to them - will never be able to cause any harm to God, and He will turn their deeds devoid of all virtue.",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 510,
            "ruku": 445,
            "hizbQuarter": 203,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4578,
            "text": "Believers, obey God and the Messenger and do not invalidate your deeds.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 510,
            "ruku": 445,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4579,
            "text": "God will never forgive the disbelievers who prevent others from the way of God and who die as disbelievers.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 510,
            "ruku": 445,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4580,
            "text": "Do not be weak hearted and do not appeal for an (unjust) settlement; you have the upper hand. God is with you and He will never reduce the reward for your deeds.",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 510,
            "ruku": 445,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4581,
            "text": "The worldly life is only a childish game. If you have faith and piety, you will receive your rewards and God will not ask you to pay for them.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 510,
            "ruku": 445,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4582,
            "text": "Should He ask for your possessions you would be niggardly as it would be hard for you to give. Thus, He would make your malice become public.",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 510,
            "ruku": 445,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4583,
            "text": "It is you who are asked to spend for the cause of God, but some of you behave in a niggardly way. Whoever behaves miserly does so against his own soul. God is Self-sufficient and you are poor. If you were to turn away from Him, He would just replace you with another people, who will not be like you.",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 510,
            "ruku": 445,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 48,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الفَتۡحِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Fath",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Victory",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4584,
            "text": "We have granted to you, (Muhammad), a manifest victory,",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 511,
            "ruku": 446,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4585,
            "text": "so that God will redeem the sins (which the pagans think you have committed against them) in the past or (you will commit) in the future. He will complete His favors to you, guide you to the right path,",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 511,
            "ruku": 446,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4586,
            "text": "and grant you a majestic triumph.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 511,
            "ruku": 446,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4587,
            "text": "It is God who has given confidence to the hearts of the believers to increase and strengthen their faith. To God belongs the armies of the heavens and the earth. He is All-knowing and All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 511,
            "ruku": 446,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4588,
            "text": "So that He would admit the believers (both male and female) to the gardens wherein streams flow, to live therein forever. He will redeem them. This is the greatest triumph in the sight of God,",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 511,
            "ruku": 446,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4589,
            "text": "so that He would punish the hypocrites and the pagans who have evil suspicions about God. It is they who are surrounded by evil and have become subject to the wrath and condemnation of God. He has prepared for them hell, a terrible place to live.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 511,
            "ruku": 446,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4590,
            "text": "To God belong the armies of the heavens and the earth. God is Majestic and All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 511,
            "ruku": 446,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4591,
            "text": "We have sent you as a witness, a bearer of glad news, and a warner,",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 511,
            "ruku": 446,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4592,
            "text": "so that you (people) may believe in God and His Messenger, help, and respect God and glorify Him in the morning and the evening.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 511,
            "ruku": 446,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4593,
            "text": "Those who pledge obedience to you are, in fact, pledging obedience to God. The hands of God are above their hands. As for those who disregard their pledge, they do so only against their own souls. Those who fulfill their promise to God will receive a great reward.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 512,
            "ruku": 446,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4594,
            "text": "The bedouins who lag behind in taking part in the battle say to you, 'Ask forgiveness for us; we were busy with our property and household.' They speak what is not in their hearts. (Muhammad), tell them, 'Who will help you against God, if He intends to harm you, who will prevent Him from benefitting you? In fact, God is Well Aware of whatever you do'.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 512,
            "ruku": 447,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4595,
            "text": "You thought the Messenger and the believers would never ever return to their families and this attracted your hearts and caused you to develop evil suspicions. You are a wrong doing people.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 512,
            "ruku": 447,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4596,
            "text": "Those who do not believe in God and His Messenger should know that We have prepared hell for the disbelievers.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 512,
            "ruku": 447,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4597,
            "text": "To God belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. He forgives or punishes whomever He wants. God is All-forgiving and All-merciful.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 512,
            "ruku": 447,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4598,
            "text": "The laggardly Bedouins will say, 'When you leave to collect the spoils, let us follow you.' They want to alter the command of God (that only the participating believers are entitled to such benefit). Tell them, 'You can never follow us for such a purpose. God has said before and He will say again (what type of people you are). In fact, you are jealous of us.' The truth is that they understand very little.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 512,
            "ruku": 447,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4599,
            "text": "Tell the laggardly Bedouins, 'You will be called to face strong people whom you will fight right to the end or who will submit to you. If you obey the Messenger, God will give you a good reward. But if you turn away as you did before, God will make you suffer a painful torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 513,
            "ruku": 447,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4600,
            "text": "It is not an offense for the blind, the lame, or the sick not to take part in the battle. Whoever obeys God and His Messenger will be admitted to the gardens wherein streams flow. God will make whoever turns away suffer a painful torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 513,
            "ruku": 447,
            "hizbQuarter": 204,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4601,
            "text": "God is pleased with the believers for their pledging obedience to you under the tree. He knew whatever was in their hearts, thus, He granted them confidence and rewarded them with an immediate victory",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 513,
            "ruku": 448,
            "hizbQuarter": 205,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4602,
            "text": "and the booty which they received from it (the Battle). God is Majestic and All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 513,
            "ruku": 448,
            "hizbQuarter": 205,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4603,
            "text": "God has promised that you will receive much booty. He has enabled you to receive this at this time and has protected you from enemies to make it an evidence (of the Truth) for the believers. He will guide you to the right path.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 513,
            "ruku": 448,
            "hizbQuarter": 205,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4604,
            "text": "Besides these, there were other gains which you could not receive, but God has full control over them. God has power over all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 513,
            "ruku": 448,
            "hizbQuarter": 205,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4605,
            "text": "Had the disbelievers fought against you, they would have run away from the battle and would have found no guardian or helper.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 513,
            "ruku": 448,
            "hizbQuarter": 205,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4606,
            "text": "This is the tradition of God which existed before, and you will never find any change in His tradition.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 513,
            "ruku": 448,
            "hizbQuarter": 205,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4607,
            "text": "It is He who kept peace between you and the people of the valley of Mecca after having given you a victory over them. God is Well Aware of what you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 514,
            "ruku": 448,
            "hizbQuarter": 205,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4608,
            "text": "It was the disbelievers who kept you from the Sacred Mosque and prevented your sacrificial offering from reaching its proper place. God would not have kept you from fighting the disbelievers, had there not been believing men and women (among them) whom you did not know and whom you might have unknowingly harmed. God did this because He grants mercy to whomever He wants. Had they been distinguishable from the believers, We would certainly have punished them with a painful torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 514,
            "ruku": 448,
            "hizbQuarter": 205,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4609,
            "text": "Since the disbelievers held zealous ignorance in their hearts, like that of the pre-Islamic age of darkness, God gave confidence to His Messenger and to the believers, binding them to the principle of piety which they deserve. God has the knowledge of all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 514,
            "ruku": 448,
            "hizbQuarter": 205,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4610,
            "text": "God made the dream of His Messenger come true for a genuine purpose. (In this he was told), 'If God wills You (believers) will enter the Sacred Mosque, in security, with your heads shaved, nails cut, and without any fear in your hearts.' He knew what you did not know. Besides this victory, He will give you another immediate victory.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 514,
            "ruku": 449,
            "hizbQuarter": 205,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4611,
            "text": "It is He who has sent His Messenger with guidance and the true religion to make it prevail over all other religions. God is a Sufficient witness to this Truth'.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 514,
            "ruku": 449,
            "hizbQuarter": 205,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4612,
            "text": "Muhammad is the Messenger of God and those with him are stern to the disbelievers yet kind among themselves. You can see them bowing and prostrating before God, seeking His favors and pleasure. Their faces (foreheads) are marked due to the effect of their frequent prostrations. That is their description in the Torah and in the Gospel they are mentioned as the seed which shoots out its stalk then becomes stronger, harder and stands firm on its stumps, attracting the farmers. Thus, God has described the believers to enrage the disbelievers. God has promised forgiveness and a great reward to the righteously striving believers.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 515,
            "ruku": 449,
            "hizbQuarter": 205,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 49,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الحُجُرَاتِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Hujuraat",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Inner Apartments",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4613,
            "text": "Believers, do not be presumptuous with the Messenger of God (in your deeds and in your words). Have fear of God; He is All-hearing and All-knowing.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 515,
            "ruku": 450,
            "hizbQuarter": 206,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4614,
            "text": "Believers, do not raise your voices above the voice of the Prophet, do not be too loud in speaking to him [as you may have been to one another], lest your deeds will be made devoid of all virtue without your realizing it.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 515,
            "ruku": 450,
            "hizbQuarter": 206,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4615,
            "text": "The hearts of those who lower their voices in the presence of the Messenger of God are tested by God through piety. They will have forgiveness and a great reward.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 515,
            "ruku": 450,
            "hizbQuarter": 206,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4616,
            "text": "Most of those who call you from behind the private chambers do not have any understanding.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 515,
            "ruku": 450,
            "hizbQuarter": 206,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4617,
            "text": "Had they exercised patience until you had come out, it would have been better for them. God is All-forgiving and All-merciful.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 516,
            "ruku": 450,
            "hizbQuarter": 206,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4618,
            "text": "Believers, if one who publicly commits sins brings you any news, ascertain its truthfulness carefully, lest you harm people through ignorance and then regret what you have done.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 516,
            "ruku": 450,
            "hizbQuarter": 206,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4619,
            "text": "Know that the Messenger of God is with you. Had he yielded to you on many of the matters, you would have been in great trouble. But God has endeared the faith to you and has made it attractive to your hearts. He has made disbelief, evil deeds and disobedience hateful to you. Such people will have the right guidance",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 516,
            "ruku": 450,
            "hizbQuarter": 206,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4620,
            "text": "as a favor and a blessing from God. God is All-knowing and All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 516,
            "ruku": 450,
            "hizbQuarter": 206,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4621,
            "text": "If two parties among the believers start to fight against each other, restore peace among them. If one party rebels against the other, fight against the rebellious one until he surrenders to the command of God. When he does so, restore peace among them with justice and equality; God loves those who maintain justice.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 516,
            "ruku": 450,
            "hizbQuarter": 206,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4622,
            "text": "Believers are each other's brothers. Restore peace among your brothers. Have fear of God so that perhaps you will receive mercy.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 516,
            "ruku": 450,
            "hizbQuarter": 206,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4623,
            "text": "Believers, let not a group of you mock another. Perhaps they are better than you. Let not women mock each other; perhaps one is better than the other. Let not one of you find faults in another nor let anyone of you defame another. How terrible is the defamation after having true faith. Those who do not repent are certainly unjust.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 516,
            "ruku": 451,
            "hizbQuarter": 206,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4624,
            "text": "Believers, stay away from conjecture; acting upon some conjecture may lead to sin. Do not spy on one another or back-bite. Would any of you like to eat the disgusting dead flesh of your brother? Have fear of God; God accepts repentance and is All-merciful.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 517,
            "ruku": 451,
            "hizbQuarter": 206,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4625,
            "text": "People, We have created you all male and female and have made you nations and tribes so that you would recognize each other. The most honorable among you in the sight of God is the most pious of you. God is All-knowing and All-aware.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 517,
            "ruku": 451,
            "hizbQuarter": 206,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4626,
            "text": "The bedouin Arabs have said, 'We are believers.' Tell them, 'You are not believers, but you should say that you are Muslims. In fact, belief has not yet entered your hearts. If you obey God and His Messenger, nothing will be reduced from your deeds. God is All-forgiving and All-merciful.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 517,
            "ruku": 451,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4627,
            "text": "The believers are those who believe in God and His Messenger, who do not change their belief into doubt and who strive hard for the cause of God with their property and persons. They are the truthful ones'.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 517,
            "ruku": 451,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4628,
            "text": "(Muhammad), say, 'Do you teach God about your religion? God knows whatever is in the heavens and the earth. He has the knowledge of all things'.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 517,
            "ruku": 451,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4629,
            "text": "(The bedouins tell you that) you owe them (a great deal) for their embracing Islam. Tell them, 'You are not doing me any favors by embracing Islam. In fact, it is God who has done you a great favor by guiding you to the faith. (Think about this) if you are people of truth.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 517,
            "ruku": 451,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4630,
            "text": "God knows whatever is unseen in the heavens and in the earth. He is Well Aware of what you do'.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 6,
            "page": 517,
            "ruku": 451,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 50,
        "name": "سُورَةُ قٓ",
        "englishName": "Qaaf",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The letter Qaaf",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4631,
            "text": "By Qaf and the glorious Quran, (you are the Messenger of God).",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4632,
            "text": "In fact, it seems odd (to the pagans) that a warner from their own people has come to them. The disbelievers have said, 'It is very strange",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4633,
            "text": "that after we die and become dust, we shall be brought back to life again. This seems far from reality'.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4634,
            "text": "We already know how much of them (of their bodies) the earth will consume. With Us there is a Book that contains all records.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4635,
            "text": "In fact, they have rejected the truth that has come to them, thus, they live in confusion.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4636,
            "text": "Have they not seen how We have established the sky above them and decked it without gaps and cracks?",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4637,
            "text": "(Have they not seen) how We have spread out the earth, placed on it firm mountains and have made all kinds of flourishing pairs of plants grow?",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4638,
            "text": "This is a reminder and it sharpens the insight of every servant of God who turns to Him in repentance.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4639,
            "text": "We have sent blessed water down from the sky to grow gardens, harvestable crops",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4640,
            "text": "and tall palm-trees with clusters of dates",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4641,
            "text": "as sustenance for My servants. With this We have brought the dead land back to life. Thus, will also be your resurrection.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4642,
            "text": "The people of Noah, dwellers of the Ra's, Thamud,",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4643,
            "text": "Ad, the Pharaoh, Lot,",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4644,
            "text": "dwellers of the forest, and the people of Tubba had all rejected the Prophets. Thus, they became subject to Our torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4645,
            "text": "Did We fail to accomplish the first creation? Of course, We did not; We have all power over all things. Yet they are confused about a new creation.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 518,
            "ruku": 452,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4646,
            "text": "We swear that We have created the human being and We know what his soul whispers to him. We are closer to him than even his jugular vein.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 453,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4647,
            "text": "Since the two scribes are sitting on each of his shoulders, he does not utter a word which is not recorded immediately by the watchful scribes.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 453,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4648,
            "text": "The human being will certainly experience the agony of death",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 453,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4649,
            "text": "and (the human being will be told), 'This is what you had been trying to run away from'.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 453,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4650,
            "text": "The trumpet will certainly be sounded. This will be the day (about which you) were threatened.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 453,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4651,
            "text": "Every soul will be accompanied (by an angel) behind him and another as a witness.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 453,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4652,
            "text": "(He will be told), 'You were completely heedless of this day. We have removed the veil from your eyes and your vision will now be sharp and strong'.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 453,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4653,
            "text": "His (angelic) companion will say, '(Lord), the record of his deeds is with me and is all ready'.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 453,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4654,
            "text": "(They will be told,) 'Throw into hell every persistent disbelievers,",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 453,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4655,
            "text": "who is an opponent of good, a suspicious transgressor",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 453,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4656,
            "text": "and an idol worshipper. Throw him into severe torment'.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 453,
            "hizbQuarter": 207,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4657,
            "text": "His satanic companion will say, 'Our Lord, I did not mislead him, but he himself went astray'.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 453,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4658,
            "text": "The Lord will say, 'Do not argue in My presence; I had certainly sent you a warning.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 453,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4659,
            "text": "No word is to be exchanged in My presence. I am not unjust to My servants'.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 453,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4660,
            "text": "On that day We shall ask hell, 'Are you full?' It will say, 'Are there any more?'",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4661,
            "text": "Paradise will be brought near for the pious ones",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4662,
            "text": "(and they will be told), 'This is what you were promised. It is for everyone who turned in repentance to God, kept his promise,",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4663,
            "text": "feared the Beneficent God in secret, and turned to Him with a repenting heart'.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4664,
            "text": "(They will be told), 'Enter Paradise in peace and, therein, you will live forever'.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4665,
            "text": "They will have therein whatever they want and will receive from Us more rewards",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 519,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4666,
            "text": "How many an ancient town who were much stronger than them (unbelievers) did We destroy. (In vain), they wandered through the land in search of a place of refuge from Our torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4667,
            "text": "This is a reminder for everyone who understands, listens, and sees.",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4668,
            "text": "We created the heavens, the earth, and all that is between them in six days without experiencing any fatigue.",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4669,
            "text": "(Muhammad), exercise patience against what they say. Glorify your Lord with His praise before sunrise and sunset.",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4670,
            "text": "Glorify Him during the night and also glorify Him after prostration.",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4671,
            "text": "Wait for the day when the trumpet will be sounded from a nearby place.",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4672,
            "text": "On that day they will certainly hear the sound of the trumpet and that will be the Day of Resurrection.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4673,
            "text": "We give life and cause things to die. To Us all things will return.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4674,
            "text": "On the day when the earth is rent asunder, they will quickly come out of their graves. This is how easy it is for Us to bring about the Day of Resurrection.",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4675,
            "text": "We know best what they say and you cannot compel them. Remind, by way of the Quran, those who have fear of My warnings.",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 454,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 51,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الذَّارِيَاتِ",
        "englishName": "Adh-Dhaariyat",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Winnowing Winds",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4676,
            "text": "By the winds which carry dust particles,",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4677,
            "text": "by the clouds which are heavily loaded with water,",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4678,
            "text": "by the ships which smoothly sail on the oceans,",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4679,
            "text": "by the angels which distribute the affairs,",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4680,
            "text": "that what you are promised is certainly true",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4681,
            "text": "and the Day of Judgment will inevitably take place.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 520,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4682,
            "text": "By the beautiful heavens,",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4683,
            "text": "your ideas are confused.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4684,
            "text": "Let whoever wishes, turn away from Our Quran.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4685,
            "text": "Death to those whose opinions are merely baseless conjectures.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4686,
            "text": "and who wander in the abyss of confusion.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4687,
            "text": "They ask, 'When it will be the Day of Judgment?'",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4688,
            "text": "On the Day of Judgment they will be punished by the fire",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4689,
            "text": "and will be told, 'Suffer the torment which you wanted to experience immediately'.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4690,
            "text": "The pious ones will live amidst gardens and springs,",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4691,
            "text": "receiving their reward from their Lord. They had been righteous people before the Day of Judgment.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4692,
            "text": "They slept very little during the night",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4693,
            "text": "and asked for forgiveness in the early morning.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4694,
            "text": "They assigned a share of their property for the needy and the destitute.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4695,
            "text": "In the earth there is evidence (of the Truth) for those who have strong faith.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4696,
            "text": "There is also evidence of the Truth within your own selves. Will you then not see?",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4697,
            "text": "In the heavens there is your sustenance and that which you were promised (Paradise).",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4698,
            "text": "This, by the Lord of the heavens and the earth is as certain as your ability to speak.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 455,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4699,
            "text": "Have you heard the story of the honorable guests of Abraham?",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4700,
            "text": "When they came to him saying, 'Peace be with you,' he replied to their greeting in the same manner and said to himself, 'These are a strange people'.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4701,
            "text": "He went quietly to his wife and returned to his guests with a fat, roasted calf.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4702,
            "text": "He placed it before them. Then he said, 'Why are you not eating?'",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4703,
            "text": "He began to feel afraid. They said, 'Do not be afraid,' and then gave him the glad news of the birth of a knowledgeable son.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4704,
            "text": "His wife came forward, crying and beating her face, saying, 'I am an old barren woman!'",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4705,
            "text": "They said, 'This is true but your Lord has said, (that you will have a son); He is All-wise and All-knowing'.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 26,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 521,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 208,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4706,
            "text": "Abraham asked, 'Messengers, what is your task?'",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4707,
            "text": "They replied, 'We have been sent to a sinful people",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4708,
            "text": "to bring down upon them showers of marked lumps of clayy.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4709,
            "text": "They are transgressors in the presence of your Lord'.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4710,
            "text": "We saved the believers among them,",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4711,
            "text": "but We found only one Muslim house.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4712,
            "text": "We left therein evidence for those who fear the painful torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4713,
            "text": "There is also evidence (of the Truth) in the story of Moses when We sent him to the Pharaoh with clear authority.",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4714,
            "text": "The Pharaoh and his forces turned away from him, saying, 'He is either a magician or an insane person'.",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4715,
            "text": "We seized him and his army and threw them into the sea. He himself was to be blamed.",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4716,
            "text": "There is also evidence of the Truth in the story of Ad whom We struck with a violent wind",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4717,
            "text": "which turned everything it approached into dust.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4718,
            "text": "There is also evidence (of the Truth) in the story of the Thamud, who were told to enjoy themselves for an appointed time.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4719,
            "text": "They transgressed against the command of their Lord. So a blast of sound struck them and they were unable to do anything but stare.",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4720,
            "text": "They were unable to stand up, nor were they helped.",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4721,
            "text": "The people of Noah who lived before them were also evil doing people.",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 456,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4722,
            "text": "We have made the heavens with Our own hands and We expanded it.",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 457,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4723,
            "text": "We have spread out the earth and how brilliantly it is spread!",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 457,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4724,
            "text": "We have created everything in pairs so that perhaps you may take heed.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 457,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4725,
            "text": "(Muhammad), tell them,'Seek refuge in God. I have been sent from Him to plainly warn you.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 457,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4726,
            "text": "Do not choose other gods besides Him. I have been sent from Him to plainly warn you'.",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 522,
            "ruku": 457,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4727,
            "text": "In the same way no Messenger came to those who lived before them without his people calling him a magician or an insane person.",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 457,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4728,
            "text": "Have they inherited such dealings with the Prophets from their predecessors or are they a rebellious people?",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 457,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4729,
            "text": "(Muhammad), leave them alone and you will not be blamed.",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 457,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4730,
            "text": "Keep on reminding them. This benefits the believers.",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 457,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4731,
            "text": "We have created jinn and human beings only that they might worship Me.",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 457,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4732,
            "text": "I do not expect to receive any sustenance from them or that they should feed Me.",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 457,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4733,
            "text": "It is God Who is the Sustainer and the Lord of invincible strength.",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 457,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4734,
            "text": "The unjust will bear a burden like that of their unjust predecessors. Let them not make Me bring immediate punishment upon them.",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 457,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4735,
            "text": "Woe to the disbelievers when the day with which they have been threatened comes!",
            "numberInSurah": 60,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 457,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 52,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الطُّورِ",
        "englishName": "At-Tur",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Mount",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4736,
            "text": "By the Mount (Sinai),",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4737,
            "text": "by the book (Torah) written",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4738,
            "text": "on parchment for distribution,",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4739,
            "text": "by the established House (Mecca),",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4740,
            "text": "by the high ceiling (heaven),",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4741,
            "text": "and by the swelling ocean,",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4742,
            "text": "the torment of your Lord will inevitably take place",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4743,
            "text": "and no one will be able to prevent it.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4744,
            "text": "On the day when the heavens will swiftly fly",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4745,
            "text": "and the mountains quickly move.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4746,
            "text": "Woe will be to those who rejected the Truth",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4747,
            "text": "and who indulged in false disputes against (God's revelations).",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4748,
            "text": "On that day they will be violently pushed into the fire",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4749,
            "text": "and they will be told, 'This is the fire which you called a lie.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 523,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4750,
            "text": "Is it magic or do you not still see?",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4751,
            "text": "Burn in its heat. It is all the same for you whether you exercise patience or not; This is the recompense for your deeds'.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4752,
            "text": "The pious will live in bountiful Paradise,",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4753,
            "text": "talking of what they have received from their Lord and of how their Lord has saved them from the torment of hell.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4754,
            "text": "They will be told, 'Eat and drink to your heart's delight for what you have done'.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4755,
            "text": "They will recline on couches arranged in rows and We shall couple them with maidens with large, lovely eyes.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4756,
            "text": "The offspring of the believers will also follow them to Paradise. So shall We join their offspring to them because of their faith. We shall reduce nothing from their deeds. Everyone will be responsible for his own actions.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4757,
            "text": "We shall provide them with fruits and the meat of the kind which they desire.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4758,
            "text": "They will pass cups of un-intoxicating and unsinful wine to one another.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 209,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4759,
            "text": "They will be served by youths who will be as beautiful as pearls.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4760,
            "text": "They will turn to one another ask questions,",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4761,
            "text": "saying, 'We were afraid while in the world.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4762,
            "text": "But God has granted us favors and saved us from the scorching heat of the torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4763,
            "text": "We had prayed to Him; He is Kind and All-merciful'.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 458,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4764,
            "text": "(Muhammad), remind them, by the Grace of your Lord, that you are neither a soothsayer or an insane person.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4765,
            "text": "Do they say, 'He is only a poet and we are waiting to see him die!?'",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4766,
            "text": "Say, 'Wait, I too am waiting with you'.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 524,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4767,
            "text": "Does their reason tell them to say this or is it because they are a rebellious people?",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4768,
            "text": "Do they say, 'He has falsely invented it (the Quran)?' In fact, they themselves have no faith.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4769,
            "text": "Let them produce a discourse like it if they are true in their claim.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4770,
            "text": "Have they been created from nothing or are they themselves their own creators?",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4771,
            "text": "Have they created the heavens and the earth? In fact, they have no strong faith.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4772,
            "text": "Do they own the treasures of your Lord? Have they any authority over God?",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4773,
            "text": "Do they have a ladder (by which they can climb up to the heavens) and listen (to the angels) and come back to the rest of the people with clear authority?",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4774,
            "text": "Do the daughters belong to Him and the sons to you?",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4775,
            "text": "Do you (Muhammad) ask them for any payment (for your preaching) which they cannot afford?",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4776,
            "text": "Do they have knowledge of the unseen, thus, are able to predict (the future)?",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4777,
            "text": "Do they design evil plans? The disbelievers themselves will be snared by their evil plots.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4778,
            "text": "Do they have another god besides God? God is too exalted to be considered equal to the idols.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4779,
            "text": "Even if they were to see a part of the heavens falling down upon them, they would say, 'It is only dense cloud'.",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4780,
            "text": "So leave them alone until they face the day when they will be struck dead from terror",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4781,
            "text": "and when their evil plans will be of no benefit to them nor will they be helped.",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4782,
            "text": "The unjust will suffer other torments besides this but most of them do not know.",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4783,
            "text": "Wait patiently for the command of your Lord. We are watching over you. Glorify your Lord when you rise during the night",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4784,
            "text": "and glorify Him after the setting of the stars.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 525,
            "ruku": 459,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 53,
        "name": "سُورَةُ النَّجۡمِ",
        "englishName": "An-Najm",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Star",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4785,
            "text": "By the declining star,",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4786,
            "text": "your companion is not in error nor has he gone astray.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4787,
            "text": "He does not speak out of his own desires.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4788,
            "text": "It is a revelations which has been revealed to him",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4789,
            "text": "and taught to him",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4790,
            "text": "by the great mighty one (Gabriel),",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4791,
            "text": "the strong one who appeared on the uppermost horizon.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4792,
            "text": "He (Gabriel) then came nearer and nearer.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4793,
            "text": "until he was as close to him as the distance of two bows, or even less.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4794,
            "text": "He revealed to God's servant whatever he wanted.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4795,
            "text": "His (Muhammad's) heart did not lie to him about what his eyes had seen.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4796,
            "text": "Will you then argue with him about what he saw?",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4797,
            "text": "He certainly saw him (Gabriel) during his other ascent",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4798,
            "text": "to the Lot-tree (in the seven heavens)",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4799,
            "text": "near which is Paradise.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4800,
            "text": "When the tree was covered with a covering,",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4801,
            "text": "(Muhammad's) eyes did not deceive him, nor did they lead him to falsehood.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4802,
            "text": "He certainly saw the greatest (signs) of the existence of his Lord.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4803,
            "text": "(Can anything as such be considered true) of al-Lat, al-Uzza,",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4804,
            "text": "and your third idol al-Manat (whom you considered as God's daughters)?",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4805,
            "text": "Do sons belong to you and daughters to God?",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4806,
            "text": "This is an unfair distinction!",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4807,
            "text": "These are only names given by yourselves and your fathers. God has not given them any authority. They, (unbelievers), only follow mere conjecture and the desires of their souls, even though guidance has already come to them from their Lord.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4808,
            "text": "Can the human being have whatever he wishes?",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4809,
            "text": "All that is in the life to come and all that is in this life belongs only to God.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 460,
            "hizbQuarter": 210,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4810,
            "text": "There are many angels in the heavens whose intercession will be of no benefit unless God grants such permission to whichever of them He wants.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 526,
            "ruku": 461,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4811,
            "text": "Only those who do not believe in the life hereafter call the angels, females. They have no knowledge about it.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 461,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4812,
            "text": "They only follow mere conjecture which can never sufficiently replace the Truth.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 461,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4813,
            "text": "(Muhammad), stay away from those who turn away from Our guidance and who do not desire anything except the worldly life.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 461,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4814,
            "text": "This is what the extent of their knowledge amounts to. Your Lord knows best who has gone astray from His path and who has been rightly guided.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 461,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4815,
            "text": "To God belongs whatever is in the heavens and the earth. In the end God will re-compense the evil doers for their deeds and reward the righteous ones for their deeds.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 461,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4816,
            "text": "Those who stay away from grave sins and indecency (should know that) for their trivial sins your Lord's forgiveness is vast. He knows best about you. When He created you from the earth and when you were embryos in your mother's wombs. Do not consider yourselves very great. God knows best who is the most righteous person.",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 461,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4817,
            "text": "(Muhammad), have you ever seen the one who has turned away (from guidance),",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4818,
            "text": "and grudgingly spends very little for the cause of God?",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4819,
            "text": "Does he possess the knowledge of the unseen, thus, he sees (all things)?",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4820,
            "text": "Has not he been informed of the contents of the Book of Moses",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4821,
            "text": "and about Abraham who fulfilled his duty (to God)?",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4822,
            "text": "Certainly no one will bear the responsibility of the sins of another,",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4823,
            "text": "nor can man achieve anything without hard labor.",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4824,
            "text": "He will certainly see the result of his labor",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4825,
            "text": "and will be fully recompensed for his deeds.",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4826,
            "text": "To your Lord will all things eventually return.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4827,
            "text": "It is He who causes laughter and weeping.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4828,
            "text": "It is He who causes death and gives life.",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 527,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4829,
            "text": "It is He who has created spouses, male and female,",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4830,
            "text": "from a discharged living germ",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4831,
            "text": "and on Him depends the life hereafter.",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4832,
            "text": "It is He who grants people temporary and durable wealth.",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4833,
            "text": "It is He who is the Lord of Sirius.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4834,
            "text": "It is He who utterly destroyed the ancient tribes of Ad,",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4835,
            "text": "Thamud,",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4836,
            "text": "and the people of Noah; they were the most unjust and rebellious people.",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4837,
            "text": "It is He who turned upside down the people of Lot",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4838,
            "text": "and covered them with torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4839,
            "text": "About which of the bounties of your Lord can they persistently dispute?",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4840,
            "text": "This is a (Prophet) like that of the ancient warners (Prophets).",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4841,
            "text": "The Day of Judgment is drawing nearer.",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4842,
            "text": "No one besides God can rescue a soul from hardship.",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4843,
            "text": "Does this statement seem strange to them",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4844,
            "text": "and do they laugh instead of weeping,",
            "numberInSurah": 60,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4845,
            "text": "indulging in carelessly idle games?",
            "numberInSurah": 61,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4846,
            "text": "So prostrate yourselves before God and worship him.",
            "numberInSurah": 62,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 462,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": {
              "id": 13,
              "recommended": false,
              "obligatory": true
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 54,
        "name": "سُورَةُ القَمَرِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Qamar",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Moon",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 4847,
            "text": "The Hour of Doom is drawing near and the moon is rent asunder.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4848,
            "text": "Whenever they see a miracle, they turn away from it and say, 'This is just a powerful magic'.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4849,
            "text": "They have rejected it and have followed their own desires, but all matters will be settled (by God).",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4850,
            "text": "They have certainly received the kind of news in which there is a lesson and strong words of wisdom,",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4851,
            "text": "but the warnings have proved to have no effect on them.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4852,
            "text": "(Muhammad), leave them alone. On the day when they will be called to a terrible punishment,",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 528,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4853,
            "text": "they will come out of their graves, their eyes cast down, hastening towards their Summoner as locusts rushing about.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4854,
            "text": "These disbelievers will say, 'This is a hard day'.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 211,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4855,
            "text": "The people of Noah, who lived before them, had also rejected (Our guidance). They rejected Our servant and said, 'He is an insane person so let us drive him away'.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4856,
            "text": "Noah prayed, 'Lord, help me; I am defeated'.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4857,
            "text": "We opened the gates of the sky and water started to pour down.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4858,
            "text": "We caused the earth to burst forth with springs so that the waters could come together for a predestined purpose.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4859,
            "text": "We carried him, (Noah), on a vessel built with boards fixed together with nails,",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4860,
            "text": "which floated on the water before Our very eyes. The flood was a recompense for the deeds of the disbelievers.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4861,
            "text": "We made (the story of Noah) as evidence of the Truth. However, is there anyone who would take heed?",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4862,
            "text": "How terrible was My torment and the result of (their disregard) of My warning.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4863,
            "text": "We have made the Quran easy to understand, but is there anyone who would pay attention?",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4864,
            "text": "The people of `Ad rejected Our guidance. How terrible was My torment and the result (of their disregard) of My warning.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4865,
            "text": "On an unfortunate day We sent upon them a continuous violent wind",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4866,
            "text": "which hurled people around like uprooted trunks of palm-trees.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4867,
            "text": "How terrible was Our torment and the result of (their disregard) of Our warning.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4868,
            "text": "We have made the Quran easy to understand, but is there anyone who would pay attention?",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 463,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4869,
            "text": "The people of Thamud rejected Our warnings.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4870,
            "text": "They said, 'Should we follow only one person among us. We shall be clearly in error and in trouble (if we do so).",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4871,
            "text": "How is it that he has received guidance? In fact, he is the most untruthfull and arrogant person'.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4872,
            "text": "(We told Salih), 'Tomorrow they will know who is the most arrogant liar.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4873,
            "text": "We are sending the she-camel to them to test them. So watch them and be patient.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 529,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4874,
            "text": "Tell them that each one of them has the right to have a certain share of water'.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4875,
            "text": "They called together their companions and agreed to slay the she-camel.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4876,
            "text": "How terrible was My punishment and warning.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4877,
            "text": "We sent upon them a single blast of sound and they were left like hay to be used by the cattle.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4878,
            "text": "We made the Quran easy to understand, but is there anyone who would take heed?",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4879,
            "text": "The people of Lot rejected Our warning.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4880,
            "text": "We sent down upon them a violent sandstorm (which destroyed them all) except for the family of Lot, whom We saved in the early morning by Our favor.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4881,
            "text": "Thus do We recompense the grateful ones.",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4882,
            "text": "Lot warned them against Our torment, but they persistently disputed it.",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4883,
            "text": "They demanded that he turn over his guests to them.",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4884,
            "text": "We struck their faces, blinded them and said, 'Suffer Our torment of which you were warned'.",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 530,
            "ruku": 464,
            "hizbQuarter": 212,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 4885,
            "text": "One early morning Our torment brought upon them utter destruction. We said, 'Suffer Our torment of which you were warned'.",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
