            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5037,
            "text": "Have you seen sperm?",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5038,
            "text": "Did you create it or was it We who created it?",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5039,
            "text": "We have destined death for you and no one can challenge Us",
            "numberInSurah": 60,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5040,
            "text": "in replacing you with another creation like you, changing you into a form which you do not know.",
            "numberInSurah": 61,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5041,
            "text": "You certainly knew about (your) first development. Why do you not take heed?",
            "numberInSurah": 62,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5042,
            "text": "Have you seen what you sow?",
            "numberInSurah": 63,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5043,
            "text": "Do you make it grow or is it We who make it grow?",
            "numberInSurah": 64,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5044,
            "text": "Had We wanted, We could have crushed it to bits and you would have been left to lament,",
            "numberInSurah": 65,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5045,
            "text": "crying, 'We have been left to suffer loss.",
            "numberInSurah": 66,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5046,
            "text": "Surely, we have been deprived (of the benefits)'.",
            "numberInSurah": 67,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5047,
            "text": "Have you seen the water which you drink?",
            "numberInSurah": 68,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5048,
            "text": "Is it you who sent it down from the clouds or is it We who have sent it down?",
            "numberInSurah": 69,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5049,
            "text": "Had We wanted, We could have made it salty. Why then do you not give thanks?",
            "numberInSurah": 70,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5050,
            "text": "Have you seen the fire which you kindle?",
            "numberInSurah": 71,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5051,
            "text": "Is it you who have produced its tree or is it We who have produced it?",
            "numberInSurah": 72,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5052,
            "text": "It is We who have made it as a reminder and a means of comfort for the people.",
            "numberInSurah": 73,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5053,
            "text": "(Muhammad), glorify your Lord, the Great One.",
            "numberInSurah": 74,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5054,
            "text": "I do not need to swear by the setting of the stars",
            "numberInSurah": 75,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5055,
            "text": "- which is indeed a great oath if only you knew it -",
            "numberInSurah": 76,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5056,
            "text": "that this is an honorable Quran",
            "numberInSurah": 77,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5057,
            "text": "preserved in a hidden Book which",
            "numberInSurah": 78,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5058,
            "text": "no one can touch it except the purified ones.",
            "numberInSurah": 79,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5059,
            "text": "(This Quran) is a revelation from the Lord of the Universe.",
            "numberInSurah": 80,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5060,
            "text": "Would you say that this statement is a lie?",
            "numberInSurah": 81,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5061,
            "text": "Would you reject the sustenance that you receive rather than give thanks?",
            "numberInSurah": 82,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5062,
            "text": "Why can you not help a soul dying",
            "numberInSurah": 83,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5063,
            "text": "right before your very eyes?",
            "numberInSurah": 84,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5064,
            "text": "We are closer to him than you, but you cannot see.",
            "numberInSurah": 85,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5065,
            "text": "If you are true to your claim that there is no Day of Judgment,",
            "numberInSurah": 86,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5066,
            "text": "why can you not bring it (the soul) back (to life)?",
            "numberInSurah": 87,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5067,
            "text": "(If a dying soul) is of those near to God,",
            "numberInSurah": 88,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5068,
            "text": "it will have rest, happiness, and a beautiful Paradise.",
            "numberInSurah": 89,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5069,
            "text": "If it is of the people of the right hand,",
            "numberInSurah": 90,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5070,
            "text": "it will be with the people of the right hand, living in peace and security.",
            "numberInSurah": 91,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5071,
            "text": "If it is of those who have rejected the Truth and have gone astray,",
            "numberInSurah": 92,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5072,
            "text": "its dwelling will be boiling water",
            "numberInSurah": 93,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5073,
            "text": "and the heat of hell fire.",
            "numberInSurah": 94,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5074,
            "text": "This is the absolute Truth and certainty.",
            "numberInSurah": 95,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5075,
            "text": "So glorify the name of your Lord, the Great One.",
            "numberInSurah": 96,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 57,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الحَدِيدِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Hadid",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Iron",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5076,
            "text": "All that is in the heavens and the earth glorify God. He is Majestic and All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5077,
            "text": "To Him belongs the Kingdom of the heavens and the earth. He gives life and causes things to die. He has power over all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5078,
            "text": "He is the First, the Last, the Manifest, and the Unseen and He knows all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5079,
            "text": "It is He who created the heavens and the earth in six days and then established His Dominion over the Throne. He knows whatever enters into the earth, what comes out of it, what descends from the sky, and what ascends to it. He is with you wherever you may be and He is Well Aware of what you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 538,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5080,
            "text": "To Him belong the heavens and the earth and to Him all things return.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 538,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5081,
            "text": "He causes night to enter into day and day into night. He knows best what all hearts contain.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 538,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5082,
            "text": "Have faith in God and His Messenger and spend for His cause out of what is entrusted to you. Those who believe and spend for the cause of God will have a great reward.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 538,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5083,
            "text": "If you are true indeed to this covenant, why do you not believe in God, when His Messenger invites you to believe in your Lord with whom you have made a solemn covenant?",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 538,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5084,
            "text": "It is He who sends illustrious revelations to His servant to take you out of darkness to light. God is Compassionate and All-merciful to you.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 538,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5085,
            "text": "Why do you not spend for the cause of God when to Him belongs the heritage of the heavens and the earth? Those who spend for the cause of God and fight before victory will have higher positions than those who spend for the cause of God and fight after victory. However, to both parties God has promised good rewards. God is Well Aware of what you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 538,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5086,
            "text": "Whoever gives a virtuous loan to God will receive double from Him in addition to an honorable reward.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 538,
            "ruku": 473,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5087,
            "text": "On the Day of Judgment you will see the believers with their light shining in front of them and to their right. They will be told, 'Paradise wherein streams flow is the glad news for you today. You will live therein forever. This is the greatest triumph'.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 539,
            "ruku": 473,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5088,
            "text": "On that day the hypocrites will say to the believers, 'Please look at us so that we might benefit from your light.' They will be told, 'Go back and search for your own light.' A barrier with a door will be placed between them. Inside it there will be mercy but outside of it there will be torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 539,
            "ruku": 473,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5089,
            "text": "(Those outside) will call out, 'Were we not with you?' (Those inside) will reply, 'Yes, you were with us but you spent your life in disbelief and hypocrisy, wished death to (Muhammad), had doubts about his message and let your longings deceive you until the decree of God came to pass. The devil deceived you about the mercy of God.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 539,
            "ruku": 473,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5090,
            "text": "So on this day no ransom will be accepted from you nor from the disbelievers. Your dwelling will be fire. It will be your friend and a terrible end'.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 539,
            "ruku": 473,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5091,
            "text": "Is it not time for the hearts of the believers to become humbled by the remembrance of God and by the Truth which has been revealed so that they will not be like the followers of the Bible who lived before them and whose hearts have become hard like stone through the long years. Many of them are evil doers.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 539,
            "ruku": 473,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5092,
            "text": "Know that God brings the dead earth back to life. We have explained Our revelations to you so that you may perhaps have understanding.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 539,
            "ruku": 473,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5093,
            "text": "The charitable men and women who give a virtuous loan to God will receive double from Him in addition to their honorable reward.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 539,
            "ruku": 473,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5094,
            "text": "Those who believe in God and His Messenger are the truthful ones and are witness (to the deeds of others) before their Lord. They will have their reward and their light. Those who disbelieve and reject Our revelations shall be the dwellers of hell.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 540,
            "ruku": 473,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5095,
            "text": "Know that the worldly life is only a game, a temporary attraction, a means of boastfulness among yourselves and a place for multiplying your wealth and children. It is like the rain which produces plants that are attractive to the unbelievers. These plants flourish, turn yellow, and then become crushed bits of straw. In the life hereafter there will be severe torment or forgiveness and mercy from God. The worldly life is only an illusion.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 540,
            "ruku": 474,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5096,
            "text": "Compete with one another to achieve forgiveness from your Lord and to reach Paradise, which is as vast as the heavens and the earth, and is prepared for those who believe in God and His Messenger. This is the blessing of God and He grants it to whomever He wants. The blessings of God are great.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 540,
            "ruku": 474,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5097,
            "text": "Whatever hardships you face on earth and in your souls were written in the Book before the creation of the souls. This is certainly easy for God",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 540,
            "ruku": 474,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5098,
            "text": "so that you would not grieve over what you have lost nor become too happy about what God has granted to you. God does not love the arrogant boastful ones who are niggardly and who try to make other people also niggardly.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 540,
            "ruku": 474,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5099,
            "text": "Those who turn away (from guidance) should know that God is Self-sufficient and Praiseworthy.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 540,
            "ruku": 474,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5100,
            "text": "We sent Our Messengers with clear evidence (to support their truthfulness), and sent with them the Book and the Balance so that people would maintain justice. We sent down iron - in which there is strong power and benefit for the people - so that God would know who would help Him and His Messenger without seeing the unseen. God is All-powerful and Majestic.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 541,
            "ruku": 474,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5101,
            "text": "We sent Noah and Abraham and placed prophethood and the Book among their offsprings, some of whom have the right guidance. However, most of them are evil doers.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 541,
            "ruku": 475,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5102,
            "text": "Then We sent Our other Messengers to follow their traditions. After them We sent Jesus, the son of Mary, to whom We gave the Gospel. In the hearts of his followers We placed compassion and mercy. We did not command them to lead the monastic life. This was their own method of seeking the pleasure of God. Despite this intention, they did not properly observe it (the monastic life). To the believers among them, We gave their reward but many of them are evil-doers.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 541,
            "ruku": 475,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5103,
            "text": "Believers, have fear of God and believe in His Messenger. God will grant you a double share of mercy, a light by which you can walk, and forgive your sins. God is All-forgiving and All-merciful.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 541,
            "ruku": 475,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5104,
            "text": "(Have fear of God and believe in His Messenger) so that the followers of the Bible will know that they can receive no reward from God. They should know that all favors are in the hands of God. He grants them to whomever He wants. The favors of God are great.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 541,
            "ruku": 475,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 58,
        "name": "سُورَةُ المُجَادلَةِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Mujaadila",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Pleading Woman",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5105,
            "text": "God has certainly heard the words of the woman who disputed with you about her husband and who (after not having received a favorable response from you) complained to God. God was listening to your argument. He is All-hearing and All-aware.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 542,
            "ruku": 476,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5106,
            "text": "Those who renounce their wives by calling them mothers should know that their wives could never become their mothers. Their mothers are those who have given birth to them. The words that they speak are certainly detestable and sinful. But God is Pardoning and All-forgiving.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 542,
            "ruku": 476,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5107,
            "text": "Those who renounce their wives by calling them mothers and then change their minds about what they have said will have to set free a slave as a ransom and only then will their carnal relations be lawful. This is what you have been commanded. God is Well Aware of whatever you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 542,
            "ruku": 476,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5108,
            "text": "If one cannot set free a slave, he must fast for two consecutive months, and only then can he have lawful carnal relations. If this is also not possible, he must feed sixty destitute people. This is the command of God, so that perhaps you will have faith in God and His Messenger. Such are the Laws of God, and those who disbelieve them will suffer a painful torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 542,
            "ruku": 476,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5109,
            "text": "Those who oppose God and His Messenger will be humiliated like those who lived before. We have sent illustrious revelations and those who disbelieve will suffer a humiliating torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 542,
            "ruku": 476,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5110,
            "text": "On the day when everyone will be resurrected, God will tell them about their deeds which He has recorded in their entirety - while they themselves have forgotten them. God is the witness over all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 542,
            "ruku": 476,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5111,
            "text": "Have you not considered that God knows all that is in the heavens and the earth? There is not a single place wherein any secret counsel can take place between any three people without God being the fourth, nor five people without His being the sixth nor any gathering of more or less people, wherever it may be, without His being with them. On the Day of Judgment, He will tell them about their deeds. God has the knowledge of all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 543,
            "ruku": 477,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5112,
            "text": "Have you not seen those who have been forbidden to have secret counsels violate this prohibition and resume their secret counsels for sinful and hostile purposes and to disobey the Messenger? When they come to you (Muhammad), they greet you with a greeting with which even God has not greeted you and say to themselves, 'Why has God not punished us for what we say (if he is a true Prophet)?' The heat of hell is a sufficient torment for them. This is the most terrible fate.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 543,
            "ruku": 477,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5113,
            "text": "Believers, when you hold a secret counsel, let it not be for a sinful, hostile purpose or to disobey the Messenger, but let your counsel take place for virtuous and pious reasons. Have fear of God in whose presence you will all be brought together.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 543,
            "ruku": 477,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5114,
            "text": "Holding secret counsels for (evil purposes) is a work of satan to cause grief to the believers, but he can do no harm to them except by the will of God. Let the believers trust in God.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 543,
            "ruku": 477,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5115,
            "text": "Believers, when you are told to make room in a meeting for others, do so. God will then make room for you. When you are told to disperse, do so. God will raise the position of the believers and of those who have received knowledge. God is Well-Aware of what you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 543,
            "ruku": 477,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5116,
            "text": "Believers, whenever you consult the Prophet, offer charity before your consultation. This will be better for you and more pure. However, if you do not find anything to give in charity, then God is All-forgiving and All-merciful.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 477,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5117,
            "text": "Were you afraid that giving in charity before your consultation would make you poor? Since you did not offer such charity, God forgave you for this. At least be steadfast in prayer, pay the religious tax, and obey God and His Messenger. God is Well Aware of what you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 477,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5118,
            "text": "Have you not seen those who have established friendship with the people who are subject to the wrath of God? They do not belong to you nor you to them, yet they knowingly try to prove their point by using false oaths.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 478,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5119,
            "text": "God has prepared a severe torment for them. What an evil deed they have committed!",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 478,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5120,
            "text": "They have made their oaths as a shield to obstruct others from the way of God. They will suffer a humiliating torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 478,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5121,
            "text": "Neither their wealth nor their children will be able to protect them against God. They will be the dwellers of hell fire wherein they will live forever.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 478,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5122,
            "text": "On the day when God will resurrect them all together, they will swear to Him as they swore to you and they will think that they have a good case but they are certainly liars.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 478,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5123,
            "text": "Satan has dominated them and has made them forget the guidance of God. They are Satan's party and the party of Satan will certainly suffer a great loss.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 478,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5124,
            "text": "Disgrace will strike those who oppose God and His Messenger.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 478,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5125,
            "text": "God has decreed, 'I and My Messenger shall certainly triumph.' God is All-powerful and Majestic.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 478,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5126,
            "text": "You will not find any people of faith in God and the Day of Judgment who would establish friendship with those who oppose God and His Messenger, even if it would be in the interest of their fathers, sons, brothers, and kinsmen. God has established faith in their hearts and supported them by a Spirit from Himself. He will admit them to Paradise wherein streams flow to live therein forever. God is pleased with them and they are pleased with God. These are members of the party of God and the party of God will certainly have everlasting happiness.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 545,
            "ruku": 478,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 59,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الحَشۡرِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Hashr",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Exile",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5127,
            "text": "All that is in the heavens and the earth glorify God. He is the Majestic and All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 545,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5128,
            "text": "It is He who drove the disbelievers among the followers of the Bible out of their homes (in the Arabian Peninsula) as the first time exiles. You did not think that they would leave their homes and they thought that their fortresses would save them from God. The decree of God came upon them in a way that even they did not expect. He caused such terror to enter their hearts that they started to destroy their own homes by their own hands and by those of the believers. People of vision, learn from this a lesson.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 545,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5129,
            "text": "Had God not decreed exile for them, He would have certainly punished them (in some other way). In this life and in the next life they would have suffered the torment of hell fire.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 545,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5130,
            "text": "This is because they opposed God and His Messenger and whoever opposes God should know that God's retribution is severe.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 546,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5131,
            "text": "All the productive palm-trees (of the Jews hostile to you) which you cut down or left untouched were the will of God to bring disgrace upon the evil-doers.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 546,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5132,
            "text": "Since you did not have to exhaust your horses and camels or (even fight), God granted to His Messenger their property. God gives authority to His Messenger over whomever He wants. God has power over all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 546,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5133,
            "text": "Whatever God grants to His Messenger (out of the property) of the people of the towns, belongs to God, the Messenger, the kinsfolk, the orphans, the destitute and to those who may become needy while on a journey, so that it will not circulate only in the hands of rich ones among them. Take only what the Messenger gives to you and desist from what he forbids you. Have fear of God; God is severe in His retribution.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 546,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5134,
            "text": "The poor immigrants who were deprived of their homes and property, who seek favors and pleasures from God, and help Him and His Messenger will also have (a share in the said property). These people are the truthful ones.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 546,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5135,
            "text": "Those who established a community center and embraced the faith before the arrival of the immigrants love those who have come to their town. They are not jealous of what is given to the immigrants. They give preference to them over themselves - even concerning the things that they themselves urgently need. Whoever controls his greed will have everlasting happiness.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 546,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5136,
            "text": "Those who migrated later (to Medina) say, 'Lord, forgive us and our brothers who preceded us in the faith, and clear our hearts of any ill will against the believers. Lord, You are Compassionate and All-merciful'.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 547,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5137,
            "text": "Have you not seen the hypocrites who say to their disbelieving brothers among the People of the Book, 'If you are driven out, we shall, also, leave the town with you and we shall never obey whoever seeks to harm you. If you are attacked, we shall help you.' God testifies that they are liars.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 547,
            "ruku": 480,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5138,
            "text": "If they were to be expelled, they would not go with them. If they were to be attacked they would not help them. Even if they were to help them, they would run away from the battle and leave them helpless.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 547,
            "ruku": 480,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5139,
            "text": "They are more afraid of you than of God. They are a people who lack understanding.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 547,
            "ruku": 480,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5140,
            "text": "They will not fight you united except with the protection of fortified towns or from behind walls. They are strong among themselves. You think that they are united, but in fact, their hearts are divided. They are a people who have no understanding.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 547,
            "ruku": 480,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5141,
            "text": "They are like those who, a short time before, suffered the consequences of their deeds. They, too, will suffer a painful torment.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 547,
            "ruku": 480,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5142,
            "text": "They are like satan who said to people, 'Reject the faith,' but when the people rejected the faith he said, 'I have nothing to do with you. I fear the Lord of the Universe'.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 547,
            "ruku": 480,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5143,
            "text": "The fate of both of them will be hell fire wherein they will live forever. Thus will be the recompense for the unjust.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 548,
            "ruku": 480,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5144,
            "text": "Believers, have fear of God. A soul must see what it has done for the future. Have fear of God for He is All-aware of what you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 548,
            "ruku": 481,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5145,
            "text": "Do not be like those who forget about God. He will make them forget themselves. These are the sinful people.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 548,
            "ruku": 481,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5146,
            "text": "The Companions of the Fire and the Companions of the Garden are not equal. The Companions of the Garden will achieve felicity.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 548,
            "ruku": 481,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5147,
            "text": "The people of Paradise and hell are not alike; the people of Paradise are the successful ones. Had We sent down this Quran on a mountain, you would have seen it humbled and rent asunder for fear of God. These are parables which We tell to people so that perhaps they will think.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 548,
            "ruku": 481,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5148,
            "text": "He is God, the only Lord, Who knows the unseen and the seen. He is the Beneficent and All-merciful One.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 548,
            "ruku": 481,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5149,
            "text": "He is the only Lord, the King, the Holy, the Peace, the Forgiver, the Watchful Guardian, the Majestic, the Dominant, and the Exalted. God is too exalted to have any partner.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 548,
            "ruku": 481,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5150,
            "text": "He is the Creator, the Designer, the Modeler, and to Him belong all virtuous names. All that is in the heavens and the earth glorify Him. He is All-majestic and All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 548,
            "ruku": 481,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 60,
        "name": "سُورَةُ المُمۡتَحنَةِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Mumtahana",
        "englishNameTranslation": "She that is to be examined",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5151,
            "text": "Believers, do not choose My enemies and your own enemies for friends, and offer them strong love. They have rejected the Truth which has come to you, and have expelled the Messenger and you from your homes because of your belief in your Lord. When you go to fight for My cause and seek My pleasure, you secretly express your love of them. I know best what you reveal or conceal. Whichever of you does this has indeed gone astray from the right path.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 549,
            "ruku": 482,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5152,
            "text": "If they find an opportunity to turn against you, they will become your enemies and will stretch out their hands and tongues at you with evil intent. They would love to see you turn away from your faith.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 549,
            "ruku": 482,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5153,
            "text": "Your relatives and children will never be of any benefit to you on the Day of Judgment. God will separate you from them. He is All-aware of what you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 549,
            "ruku": 482,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5154,
            "text": "Abraham and those with him are the best examples for you to follow. They told the people, 'We have nothing to do with you and with those whom you worship besides God. We have rejected you. Enmity and hatred will separate us forever unless you believe in One God.' Abraham told his father, 'I shall ask forgiveness for you only, but I shall not be of the least help to you before God'.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 549,
            "ruku": 482,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5155,
            "text": "They prayed, 'Lord, we have trust in You, turned to You in repentance, and to You we shall all return. Lord, save us from the evil intentions of the disbelievers. Our Lord, forgives us. You are Majestic and All-wise'.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 549,
            "ruku": 482,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5156,
            "text": "They are the best examples for those who have hope in God and the Day of Judgment. Whoever turn away should know that God is Self-sufficient and Praiseworthy.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 550,
            "ruku": 482,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5157,
            "text": "God will perhaps bring about love between you and those of the disbelievers with whom you were enemies. God is All-powerful, All-merciful, and All-forgiving.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 550,
            "ruku": 483,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5158,
            "text": "God does not forbid you to deal kindly and justly with those who have not fought against you about the religion or expelled you from your homes. God does not love the unjust people.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 550,
            "ruku": 483,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5159,
            "text": "He only forbids you to be friends with those who have fought against you about the religion, expelled you from your homes or supported others in expelling you. Whoever loves these people are unjust.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 550,
            "ruku": 483,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5160,
            "text": "Believers, when believing immigrant women come to you, test them. God knows best about their faith. If you know that they are believers, do not return them to the disbelievers. Such women are not lawful for them and disbelievers are not lawful for such women. Give the disbelievers whatever they have spent (on such women for their dowry). There is no offense for you to marry them if you agree to give them their dowry. Do not hold unto your disbelieving wives; you may get back what you have spent on them for their dowry and the disbelievers may also ask for what they have spent. This is the command of God by which He judges you. God is All-knowing and All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 550,
            "ruku": 483,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5161,
            "text": "If your wives go away from you to disbelievers who will not give you back the dowry which you spent on them, let the Muslims pay back such dowry from the property of the disbelievers which may come into their hands. Have fear of God in whom you believe.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 550,
            "ruku": 483,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5162,
            "text": "Prophet, when believing women come to you pledging not to consider anything equal to God, not to steal, or to commit fornication, not to kill their children, or to bring false charges against anyone (such as ascribing others children to their husbands), and not to disobey you in lawful matters, accept their pledge, and ask forgiveness for them from God. God is All-forgiving and All-merciful.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 551,
            "ruku": 483,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5163,
            "text": "Believers, do not establish friendship with the people who have become subject to the wrath of God. They do not have any hope in the life to come, just as the disbelievers have no hope in those who are in their graves.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 551,
            "ruku": 483,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 61,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الصَّفِّ",
        "englishName": "As-Saff",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Ranks",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5164,
            "text": "All that is in the heavens and the earth glorify God. He is the Majestic and All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 551,
            "ruku": 484,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5165,
            "text": "Believers, why do you preach what you do not practice?",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 551,
            "ruku": 484,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5166,
            "text": "It is most hateful in the sight of God if you say something and do not practice it.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 551,
            "ruku": 484,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5167,
            "text": "God loves those who fight for His cause in battlefield formations firm as an unbreakable concrete wall.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 551,
            "ruku": 484,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5168,
            "text": "Moses said to his people, 'Why do you create difficulties for me when you know that I am God's Messenger to you?' When they deviated (from the right path), God led their hearts astray. God does not guide the evil-doing people.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 551,
            "ruku": 484,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5169,
            "text": "Jesus, son of Mary, said to the Israelites, 'I am the Messenger of God sent to you. I confirm the Torah which is in existence and give you the glad news of the coming of a Messenger who will come after me named Ahmad.' When this Messenger came to them with all the proofs (to support his truthfulness), they said, 'He is simply a magician'.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 552,
            "ruku": 484,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5170,
            "text": "Who is more unjust than one who creates falsehood against God when he has already been invited to Islam? God does not guide the unjust people.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 552,
            "ruku": 484,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5171,
            "text": "They want to put out the light of God with their mouths, but God will certainly make His light shine forever - even though the disbelievers may dislike this.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 552,
            "ruku": 484,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5172,
            "text": "It is He who has sent His Messenger with guidance and the true religion to stand supreme over all religions, even though the pagans may dislike it.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 552,
            "ruku": 484,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5173,
            "text": "Believers, shall I show you a bargain which will save you from the painful torment?",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 552,
            "ruku": 485,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5174,
            "text": "Have faith in God and His Messenger and strive hard for His cause with your wealth and in persons. This is better for you if only you knew it.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 552,
            "ruku": 485,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5175,
            "text": "God will forgive your sins and admit you into Paradise wherein streams flow, and you live in the lofty mansions of the garden of Eden. This is indeed the greatest triumph.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 552,
            "ruku": 485,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5176,
            "text": "(Besides forgiveness) you will receive other favors which you will love: help from God and an immediate victory (Muhammad), give such glad news to the believers.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 552,
            "ruku": 485,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5177,
            "text": "Believers, be the helpers of God just as when Jesus, the son of Mary, asked the disciples, 'Who will be my helpers for the cause of God?' and the disciples replied, 'We are the helpers of God.' A group of the Israelites believed in him and others rejected him. We helped the believers against their enemies and they became victorious.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 552,
            "ruku": 485,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 62,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الجُمُعَةِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Jumu'a",
        "englishNameTranslation": "Friday",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5178,
            "text": "All that is in the heavens and the earth glorify God, the King, the Holy, the Majestic and the All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 553,
            "ruku": 486,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5179,
            "text": "It is He who has sent to the illiterate a Messenger from among their own people to recite to them His revelations and purify them. He will teach the Book to them",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 553,
            "ruku": 486,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5180,
            "text": "and others who have not yet joined, and He will give them wisdom. Before this they had been in plain error. God is Majestic and All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 553,
            "ruku": 486,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5181,
            "text": "Such is the favor of God which He grants to whomever He wants. God's favor is great.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 553,
            "ruku": 486,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5182,
            "text": "Those who were to carry the responsibility of the Torah but ignored, are like donkeys laden with books. How terrible is the example of the people who reject the revelations of God. God does not guide the unjust.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 553,
            "ruku": 486,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5183,
            "text": "(Muhammad), ask the Jews, 'If you believe that you are the chosen people of God to the exclusion of all other people, wish for death if you are truthful'.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 553,
            "ruku": 486,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5184,
            "text": "They will never wish for death because of what they have done! God knows best about the unjust people.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 553,
            "ruku": 486,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5185,
            "text": "(Muhammad), tell them, 'The death from which you run away will certainly approach you. Then you will be returned to the One who knows the unseen and the seen, and He will tell you what you have done'.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 553,
            "ruku": 486,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5186,
            "text": "Believers, on Friday when the call for prayer is made, try to attend prayer (remembering God) and leave off all business. This would be better for you if only you knew it.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 554,
            "ruku": 487,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5187,
            "text": "When the prayer ends, disperse through the land and seek the favor of God. Remember Him often so that perhaps you will have everlasting happiness.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 554,
            "ruku": 487,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5188,
            "text": "When they see some merchandise or some sport, they rush towards it and leave you alone standing. Say, '(God's rewards for good deeds) are better than merriment or merchandise; God is the best Sustainer'.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 554,
            "ruku": 487,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 63,
        "name": "سُورَةُ المُنَافِقُونَ",
        "englishName": "Al-Munaafiqoon",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Hypocrites",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5189,
            "text": "When the hypocrites come to you, they say, 'We testify that you are the Messenger of God.' God knows that you are His Messenger. God testifies that they hypocrites are liars.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 554,
            "ruku": 488,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5190,
            "text": "They have chosen their oaths as a shield for them to obstruct others from the way of God. How terrible is what they do!",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 554,
            "ruku": 488,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5191,
            "text": "This is because they accepted the faith and then rejected it. God has sealed their hearts, thus, they do not have any understanding.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 554,
            "ruku": 488,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5192,
            "text": "Their physical appearance attracts you when you see them and when they speak, you carefully listen to them. In fact, they are like propped up hollow trunks of wood (They are so cowardly) they think that every cry which they hear is against them. They are the enemy, so beware of them. May God condemn them. Where are they turning to, leaving behind the Truth?",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 554,
            "ruku": 488,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5193,
            "text": "When they are told, 'Come and let the Prophet of God seek forgiveness for you,' they shake their heads and you can see them arrogantly turning away.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 555,
            "ruku": 488,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5194,
            "text": "It is all the same whether you seek forgiveness for them or not; God will never forgive them. God does not guide the evil-doing people.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 555,
            "ruku": 488,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5195,
            "text": "It is they who say, 'Give nothing to those who are around the Messenger of God so that they will desert him.' To God belongs the treasures of the heavens and the earth, but the hypocrites have no understanding.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 555,
            "ruku": 488,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5196,
            "text": "They say, 'When we return to Medina, the honorable ones will certainly drive out the mean ones.' Honor belongs to God, His Messenger and the believers, but the hypocrites do not know.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 555,
            "ruku": 488,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5197,
            "text": "Believers, do not let your wealth and children divert you from remembering God. Wwhoever is diverted will suffer a great loss.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 555,
            "ruku": 489,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5198,
            "text": "Spend for the cause of God out of what We have given you before death approaches you, and say, 'Lord, would that you would give me respite for a short time so that I could spend for Your cause and become one of those who do good'.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 555,
            "ruku": 489,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5199,
            "text": "God will never grant respite to any soul when its appointed time has come. God is Well-Aware of what you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 555,
            "ruku": 489,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 64,
        "name": "سُورَةُ التَّغَابُنِ",
        "englishName": "At-Taghaabun",
        "englishNameTranslation": "Mutual Disillusion",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5200,
            "text": "All that is in the heavens and the earth glorify God. To Him belongs the Kingdom and all praise. He has power over all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 556,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5201,
            "text": "It is He who has created you all but some of you have accepted the faith and some of you have not. God is Well Aware of what you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 556,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5202,
            "text": "He has created the heavens and the earth for a genuine purpose and has formed you in the best shape. To Him all things return.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 556,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5203,
            "text": "He knows all that is in the heavens and the earth and all that you reveal or conceal. God knows best whatever the hearts contain.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 556,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5204,
            "text": "Have you not received the news about the disbelievers living before you who suffered the consequences of their deeds and will suffer a painful torment?",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 556,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5205,
            "text": "This was because their messengers came to them with clear proof (to support their prophethood) and they said, 'Can mere mortals provide us with guidance?' They rejected the Messengers and turned away. God does not need the worship of anyone. He is Self-sufficient and Praiseworthy.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 556,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5206,
            "text": "The disbelievers have thought that they would never be resurrected (Muhammad). Say, 'I swear by my Lord that you will certainly be resurrected and will be told about all that you have done.' All this is certainly very easy for God.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 556,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5207,
            "text": "Thus, have faith in God, His Messenger and the Light which We have revealed. God is Well-Aware of what you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 556,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5208,
            "text": "On the day when We shall gather you all together (for the Day of Judgment), all cheating will be exposed. Those who believe in God and act righteously will receive forgiveness for their sins. They will be admitted into Paradise wherein streams flow and they will live forever. This certainly is the greatest triumph.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 556,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5209,
            "text": "As for those who have disbelieved and rejected Our revelations, they will dwell forever in hell fire, a terrible fate.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 557,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5210,
            "text": "No one will be afflicted with any hardship without it being the will of God. The hearts of whoever believed in God will receive guidance. God has the knowledge of all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 557,
            "ruku": 491,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5211,
            "text": "Obey God and the Messenger, but if you turn away, know that the only duty of Our Messenger is to clearly preach.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 557,
            "ruku": 491,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5212,
            "text": "God is the only Lord and in Him the believers should trust.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 557,
            "ruku": 491,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5213,
            "text": "Believers, some of your wives and children may prove to be your enemies so beware of them. However, if you would pardon, ignore and forgive, know that God is All-forgiving and All-merciful.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 557,
            "ruku": 491,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5214,
            "text": "Your property and children are a trial for you, but the reward (which one may receive from God) is great.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 557,
            "ruku": 491,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5215,
            "text": "Have as much fear of God as best as you can. Listen to the Messenger, obey him, and spend for your own sake good things for the cause of God. Those who control their greed will have everlasting happiness.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 557,
            "ruku": 491,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5216,
            "text": "If you give a virtuous loan to God, He will pay back double and forgive your sins. God is the Most Appreciating and the Most Forbearing.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 557,
            "ruku": 491,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5217,
            "text": "He knows the unseen and the seen. He is the Majestic and All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 557,
            "ruku": 491,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 65,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الطَّلَاقِ",
        "englishName": "At-Talaaq",
        "englishNameTranslation": "Divorce",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5218,
            "text": "Prophet and believers, if you want to divorce your wives, you should divorce them at a time after which they can start their waiting period. Let them keep an account of the number of the days in the waiting period. Have fear of God, your Lord. (During their waiting period) do not expel them from their homes and they also must not go out of their homes, unless they commit proven indecency. These are the Laws of God. Whoever transgresses against the laws of God has certainly wronged himself. You never know, perhaps God will bring about some new situation.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 558,
            "ruku": 492,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5219,
            "text": "When their waiting period is about to end, keep them or separate from them lawfully. Let two just people witness the divorce and let them bear witness for the sake of God. Thus does God command those who have faith in Him and the Day of Judgment.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 558,
            "ruku": 492,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5220,
            "text": "God will make a way (out of difficulty) for one who has fear of Him and will provide him with sustenance in a way that he will not even notice. God is Sufficient for the needs of whoever trusts in Him. He has full access to whatever He wants. He has prescribed a due measure for everything.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 558,
            "ruku": 492,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5221,
            "text": "If you have any doubt whether your wives have reached the stage of menopause, the waiting period will be three months. This will also be the same for those who do not experience menstruation. The end of the waiting period for a pregnant woman is the delivery. God will make the affairs of one who fears Him easy.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 558,
            "ruku": 492,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5222,
            "text": "This is the command of God which He has revealed to you. God will expiate the evil deeds of those who fear Him and will increase their rewards.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 558,
            "ruku": 492,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5223,
            "text": "Lodge them (your wives) where you lived together if you can afford it. Do not annoy them so as to make life intolerable for them. If they are pregnant, provide them with maintenance until their delivery. Pay their wage if they breast-feed your children and settle your differences lawfully. If you are unable to settle them, let another person breast-feed the child.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 559,
            "ruku": 492,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5224,
            "text": "Let the well-to-do people spend abundantly (for the mother and the child) and let the poor spend from what God has given them. God does not impose on any soul that which he cannot afford. God will bring about ease after hardship.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 559,
            "ruku": 492,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5225,
            "text": "How many a town has disobeyed its Lord and His Messenger! For them Our questioning was strict and Our punishment severe.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 559,
            "ruku": 493,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5226,
            "text": "They suffered the consequences of their deeds and their end was perdition.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 559,
            "ruku": 493,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5227,
            "text": "God has prepared severe retribution for them. People of understanding and believers, have fear of God. God has certainly sent you a reminder,",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 559,
            "ruku": 493,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5228,
            "text": "a Messenger who recites to you the illustrious revelations of God, to bring the righteously striving believers out of darkness into light. God will admit those who believe in Him and act righteously to Paradise wherein streams flow, and they will live therein forever. God will provide them with excellent sustenance.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 559,
            "ruku": 493,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5229,
            "text": "It is God who has created the seven heavens and a like number of earths. His commandments are sent between them, so that you would know that God has power over all things and that His knowledge encompasses all.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 559,
            "ruku": 493,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 66,
        "name": "سُورَةُ التَّحۡرِيمِ",
        "englishName": "At-Tahrim",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Prohibition",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5230,
            "text": "Prophet, in seeking the pleasure of your wives, why do you make unlawful that which God has made lawful. God is All-forgiving and All-merciful.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 560,
            "ruku": 494,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5231,
            "text": "God has shown you how to absolve yourselves of your oaths. He is your Guardian and is All-knowing and All-wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 560,
            "ruku": 494,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5232,
            "text": "The Prophet told a secret to one of his wives telling her not to mention it to anyone else. When she divulged it, God informed His Prophet about this. The Prophet told his wife part of the information which he had received from God and ignored the rest. Then she asked, 'Who informed you about this?' He replied, 'The All-aware and All-knowing one has told me'.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 560,
            "ruku": 494,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5233,
            "text": "Would that you two (wives of the Prophet) had turned to God in repentance. Your hearts have sinned. If you conspire with each other against him, know that God is his Guardian. Gabriel, the righteous (ones) among the believers and the angels will all support him.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 560,
            "ruku": 494,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5234,
            "text": "If he divorces you, perhaps his Lord will replace you with better wives, either widows or virgins who will be Muslims: believers, faithful, obedient, repentant, and devout in prayer and fasting.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 560,
            "ruku": 494,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5235,
            "text": "Believers, save yourselves and your families from the fire which is fueled by people and stones and is guarded by stern angels who do not disobey God's commands and do whatever they are ordered to do.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 560,
            "ruku": 494,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5236,
            "text": "Disbelievers (will be told on the Day of Judgment), 'Do not make any excuses on this day; you are only receiving recompense for what you have done'.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 560,
            "ruku": 494,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5237,
            "text": "Believers, turn to God in repentance with the intention of never repeating the same sin. Perhaps your Lord will expiate your evil deeds and admit you to Paradise wherein streams flow. On the Day of Judgment, God will not disgrace the Prophet and those who have believed in him. Their lights will shine in front of them and to their right. They will say, 'Our Lord, perfect our light for us and forgive our sins. You have power over all things'.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 561,
            "ruku": 495,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5238,
            "text": "Prophet, fight against the disbelievers and the hypocrites and be stern against them. Their dwelling will be hell fire, the most terrible fate.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 561,
            "ruku": 495,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5239,
            "text": "God has told the disbelievers the story of the wives of Noah and Lot as a parable. They were married to two of Our righteous servants but were unfaithful to them. Nothing could protect them from the (wrath) of God and they were told to enter hell fire with the others.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 561,
            "ruku": 495,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5240,
            "text": "To the believers, as a parable, God has told the story of the wife of the Pharaoh who said, 'Lord, establish for me a house in Paradise in your presence. Rescue me from Pharaoh and his deeds and save me from the unjust people.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 561,
            "ruku": 495,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5241,
            "text": "He has also told, as a parable, the story of Mary, daughter of Imran who preserved her virginity and (into whose womb) We breathed Our spirit. She made the words of her Lord and the predictions in His Books come true. She was an obedient woman.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 561,
            "ruku": 495,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 67,
        "name": "سُورَةُ المُلۡكِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Mulk",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Sovereignty",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5242,
            "text": "Blessed is He in whose hands is the Kingdom and who has power over all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5243,
            "text": "It is He who has created death and life to put you to the test and see which of you is most virtuous in your deeds. He is Majestic and All-forgiving.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5244,
            "text": "It is He who has created seven heavens, one above the other. You can see no flaw in the creation of the Beneficent God. Look again. Can you see faults?",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5245,
            "text": "Look twice (and keep on looking), your eyes will only become dull and tired.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5246,
            "text": "We have decked the lowest heavens with torches. With these torches We have stoned the devils and We have prepared for them the torment of hell.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5247,
            "text": "For those who have disbelieved in their Lord, We have prepared the torment of hell, the most terrible place to return.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5248,
            "text": "When they are thrown into hell, they will hear its roaring while it boils.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5249,
            "text": "It almost explodes in rage. Whenever a group is thrown into it, its keepers will ask them, 'Did no one come to warn you?'",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5250,
            "text": "They will say, 'Yes, someone did come to warn us, but we rejected him saying, 'God has revealed nothing. You are in great error'.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5251,
            "text": "They will also say, 'Had We listened or used our minds, we would not have become the dwellers of hell'.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5252,
            "text": "They will confess to their sins, but the dwellers of hell will be far away from God's (mercy).",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5253,
            "text": "Those who fear their Lord in secret will receive forgiveness and a great reward.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5254,
            "text": "Whether you conceal what you say or reveal it, God knows best all that the hearts contain.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5255,
            "text": "Does the One Who is Subtle, All-aware, and Who created all things not know all about them?",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5256,
            "text": "It is He who has made the earth subservient to you. You walk through its vast valleys and eat of its sustenance. Before Him you will all be resurrected.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5257,
            "text": "Do you feel secure that the One in the heavens will not cause you to sink into the earth when it is violently shaking?",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5258,
            "text": "Do you feel secure that the One in the heavens will not strike you with a sandstorm? You will soon know, with the coming of the torment, how serious Our warning was.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5259,
            "text": "Those who lived before them had also rejected Our warning, and how terrible was Our retribution!",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5260,
            "text": "Did they not see the birds above them, stretching out, and flapping their wings. No one keeps them up in the sky except the Beneficent God. He certainly watches over all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5261,
            "text": "Do you have any armies who will help you against the Beneficent God? The disbelievers are certainly deceived (by satan).",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5262,
            "text": "Is there anyone who will provide you with sustenance if God were to deny you sustenance? In fact, they obstinately persist in their transgression and hatred.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5263,
            "text": "Can one who walks with his head hanging down be better guided that one who walks with his head upright?",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5264,
            "text": "(Muhammad), say, 'It is God who has brought you into being and made ears, eyes, and hearts for you, but you give very little thanks'.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5265,
            "text": "Say, 'It is God who has settled you on the earth and to Him you will be resurrected'.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5266,
            "text": "They say, 'When will this torment take place if what you say is true?'",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5267,
            "text": "Say, 'God knows best. I am only one who gives warning'.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5268,
            "text": "When they see the torment approaching, the faces of the disbelievers will blacken and they will be told, 'This is what you wanted to (experience)'.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5269,
            "text": "(Muhammad), say, 'Have you not considered that regardless whether God forgives me and my followers or grants us mercy, but who will protect the disbelievers from a painful torment?",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5270,
            "text": "Say, 'He is the Beneficent One in whom we have faith and trust. You will soon know who is in manifest error'.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5271,
            "text": "Say, 'Have you not thought that if your water was to dry up, who would bring you water from the spring?'",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 68,
        "name": "سُورَةُ القَلَمِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Qalam",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Pen",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5272,
            "text": "Nun. By the pen and by what you write,",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5273,
            "text": "(Muhammad), you are not insane, thanks to the bounty of your Lord.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5274,
            "text": "You will certainly receive a never-ending reward.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5275,
            "text": "You have attained a high moral standard.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5276,
            "text": "You will see and they will also see",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5277,
            "text": "which of you has been afflicted by insanity.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5278,
            "text": "Your Lord knows best who has gone astray from His path and who is rightly guided.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5279,
            "text": "Do not yield to those who reject the Truth.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5280,
            "text": "They would like you to relent to them so that they could also relent towards you.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5281,
            "text": "Do not yield to one persistent in swearing,",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5282,
            "text": "back-biting, gossiping,",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5283,
            "text": "obstructing virtues, a sinful transgressor,",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5284,
            "text": "ill-mannered, and moraly corrupt or that because he may possess wealth and children.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5285,
            "text": "When Our revelations are recited to him,",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5286,
            "text": "he says, 'These are ancient legends'.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5287,
            "text": "We shall brand him on his nose.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5288,
            "text": "We have tested them in the same way as we tested the dwellers of the garden (in Yemen) when they swore to pluck all the fruits of the garden in the morning,",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5289,
            "text": "without adding ('if God wills').",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5290,
            "text": "A visitor from your Lord circled around the garden during the night while they were asleep",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5291,
            "text": "and the garden was turned into a barren desert.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5292,
            "text": "In the morning they called out to one another,",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5293,
            "text": "'Go early to your farms, if you want to pluck the fruits'.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5294,
            "text": "They all left, whispering to one another,",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5295,
            "text": "'Let no beggar come to the garden'.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5296,
            "text": "They were resolved to repel the beggars.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5297,
            "text": "When they saw the garden, they said, 'Surely we have lost our way.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5298,
            "text": "(No, we are not lost.) In fact, we have been deprived of everything'.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5299,
            "text": "A reasonable one among them said, 'Did I not tell you that you should glorify God?'",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5300,
            "text": "They said, 'All glory belongs to God. We have certainly been unjust'.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5301,
            "text": "Some of them started to blame others.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5302,
            "text": "They said, 'Woe to us. We have been arrogant.",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5303,
            "text": "Perhaps our Lord will replace it with a better garden. We turn in repentance to our Lord'.",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5304,
            "text": "Such is the torment if only they knew that the torment in the life hereafter will certainly be greater.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5305,
            "text": "The pious ones will receive a beautiful Paradise from their Lord.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5306,
            "text": "Shall We treat the Muslims like criminals?",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5307,
            "text": "What is the matter with you? How could you judge this to be so?",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5308,
            "text": "Do you have a book from which you study",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5309,
            "text": "that tells you to do whatever you want?",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5310,
            "text": "Do you have a covenant with Us which allows you to do whatever you want until the Day of Judgment?",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5311,
            "text": "(Muhammad), ask which of them can guarantee that on the Day of Judgment.",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5312,
            "text": "they will receive the same thing that the Muslims will? Do they have any witness to such an agreement? Let them bring out such witness, if they are truthful.",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5313,
            "text": "On the day when the terrible torment approaches, they will be told (in a mocking way) to prostrate themselves, but they will not be able to do it.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5314,
            "text": "Their eyes will be lowered and disgrace will cover them. They had certainly been told to prostrate themselves before God when they were safe and sound.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5315,
            "text": "Leave those who reject the Quran to Me and I shall lead them step by step to destruction, without their being aware of it.",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5316,
            "text": "I shall give them respite, however, My plan is so strong that they will never be able to escape from it.",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5317,
            "text": "(Muhammad), do you ask for your preaching any recompense which is too heavy a price for them to pay?",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5318,
            "text": "Do they possess the knowledge of the unseen which confirms the truthfulness of their belief?",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5319,
            "text": "Exercise patience until the promise of your Lord (to punish the unbelievers) comes true. Do not be like Jonah (who left his people without the permission of God; he wanted them to be punished immediately),",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5320,
            "text": "and who cried (for help) to his Lord, while imprisoned and helpless inside the fish. Had it not been for a favor from his Lord, he would have been left out in the open, deserving blame for his shortcomings.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5321,
            "text": "But his Lord chose him as His Prophet and made him one of the righteous ones.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5322,
            "text": "When the disbelievers listen to you reciting the Quran they almost try to destroy you with their piercing eyes. Then they say, 'He is certainly insane'.",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5323,
            "text": "The Quran is nothing but a reminder from God to mankind.",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 69,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الحَاقَّةِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Haaqqa",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Reality",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5324,
            "text": "The Inevitable! (Day of Judgment).",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5325,
            "text": "What is the Inevitable?",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5326,
            "text": "Would that you knew (in detail) what the Inevitable is!",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5327,
            "text": "The people of Thamud and Ad denied the Day of Judgment.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5328,
            "text": "The Thamuds were destroyed by a violent blast of sound.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5329,
            "text": "The Ads were destroyed by a swift, destructive gale",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5330,
            "text": "which continued to strike them for seven and eight days so that eventually you could see the people lying dead like the hollow trunks of uprooted palm-trees.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5331,
            "text": "Can you see any of their survivors?",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5332,
            "text": "The Pharaoh, those who lived before him and the people of the Subverted Cities all persisted in doing evil.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5333,
            "text": "They disobeyed the Messenger of their Lord and He seized them with torment which increased with time.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5334,
            "text": "When the flood rose high and covered the whole land, We carried you in the Ark.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5335,
            "text": "as a lesson for you, but only attentive ears will retain it.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5336,
            "text": "With the first blast of sound from the trumpet,",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5337,
            "text": "the earth and mountains will be raised up high and crushed all together.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5338,
            "text": "On that day, the inevitable event will take place",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5339,
            "text": "and the heavens will be rent asunder,",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5340,
            "text": "and will turn frail, losing all force. The angels will be around the heavens and on that day eight of them will carry the Throne of your Lord above all the creatures.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5341,
            "text": "On that day all your secrets will be exposed.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5342,
            "text": "Those who will receive the books of the records of their deeds in their right hands will say, 'Come and read my record.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5343,
            "text": "I was sure that the record of my deeds would be shown to me'.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5344,
            "text": "They will have a pleasant life",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5345,
            "text": "in an exalted garden",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5346,
            "text": "with fruits within easy reach.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5347,
            "text": "Such people will be told, 'Eat and drink with pleasure as the reward for what you did in the past'.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5348,
            "text": "However, those who will receive the books of the records of their deeds in their left hands will say, 'We wish that this record had never been given to us",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5349,
            "text": "and that we would never knew what our records contained.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5350,
            "text": "Would that death had taken us away for good.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5351,
            "text": "Our wealth is of no benefit to us",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5352,
            "text": "and our belief has destroyed us'.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5353,
            "text": "The angels will be told, 'Seize and chain them,",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
